('ed44e2d2-61ed-11f1-98fa-60cf847a2597', 'podcast', 'Catch Up With the New Media!  This Week’s Podcast Is Here.', 'catch-up-with-the-new-media-this-weeks-podcast-is-here', NULL, '<figure id=\"attachment_1345\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-1345\" style=\"width: 640px\" class=\"wp-caption aligncenter\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"wp-image-1345 size-full\" src=\"uploads/Your-New-Media-Update-Console.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"640\" height=\"320\" srcset=\"https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/Your-New-Media-Update-Console.png 640w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/Your-New-Media-Update-Console-600x300.png 600w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/Your-New-Media-Update-Console-300x150.png 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" /><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-1345\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Media Majors Making Media!</figcaption></figure>\n<h4 style=\"text-align: center;\">Your New Media News Update for This Week!</h4>\n<audio class=\"wp-audio-shortcode\" id=\"audio-1332-1\" preload=\"none\" style=\"width: 100%;\" controls=\"controls\"><source type=\"audio/mpeg\" src=\"http://www.oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/GMN-4-Web-022218.mp3?_=1\" /><a href=\"http://www.oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/GMN-4-Web-022218.mp3\">http://www.oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/GMN-4-Web-022218.mp3</a></audio>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/GMN-4-Web-022218.mp3\">Click Here to Listen or Download!</a></p>\n<p><strong>This Week:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Is Snapchat Gobbling Up Facebook Users?</li>\n<li>Snap Discover Goes to College to Deliver the News.</li>\n<li>Unilever&#8217;s Warning to Social: Clean Up Your Act!</li>\n<li>Should Insta&#8217;s New Features Scare the Competition?</li>\n<li>Political Memes &amp; Democracy: Just Good Fun?</li>\n<li>Will It Be Twitch or Youtube?  Gamers Are Choosing.</li>\n<li>Is Facebook Getting Old?</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Global Media News is a weekly webcast covering new media news from around the world.  GMN is a production of  Media Studies students from the <a href=\"http://www.oldwestbury.edu/\" target=\"_self\">SUNY College @ Old Westbury.</a>   We scour the web for news about new media, journalism and technology.</p>\n<p>Listen to our next podcast streaming live on OWWR: Thursday March 1, 2018 @ 10 am EST.</p>\n<p>Can&#8217;t listen live? Our next podcast  will be posted by 2:00pm, Thursday March 1, 2018,  2018.</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/GlobalMediaNews\" target=\"_self\">Subscribe Now!</a></p>\n', NULL, 'APPROVED', 'AM327', NULL, '2018-02-23 22:49:41', 0, 'Your New Media News Update for This Week! Click Here to Listen or Download! This Week: Is Snapchat Gobbling Up Facebook Users? Snap Discover Goes to College to Deliver the News. Unilever’s Warning to Social: Clean Up Your Act! Should Insta’s New Features Scare the Competition? Political Memes & Democracy: Just Good Fun? Will It…\n', NULL, NULL, 1),
('ed4524b4-61ed-11f1-98fa-60cf847a2597', 'podcast', 'It’s New Media News Time: Our Podcast for Aspiring Media Professionals!', 'its-new-media-news-time-our-podcast-for-aspiring-media-professionals', NULL, '<figure id=\"attachment_1504\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-1504\" style=\"width: 610px\" class=\"wp-caption aligncenter\"><a href=\"http://www.oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/GMN-5-Web-030118.mp3\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"wp-image-1504 size-large\" src=\"http://www.oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/GMN-5-Crop-2-030118-1024x1024.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"610\" height=\"610\" /></a><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-1504\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Gregg Mandel Reporting on Twitter&#8217;s War on Bots!</figcaption></figure>\n<audio class=\"wp-audio-shortcode\" id=\"audio-1502-1\" preload=\"none\" style=\"width: 100%;\" controls=\"controls\"><source type=\"audio/mpeg\" src=\"http://www.oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/GMN-5-Web-030118.mp3?_=1\" /><a href=\"http://www.oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/GMN-5-Web-030118.mp3\">http://www.oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/GMN-5-Web-030118.mp3</a></audio>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/GMN-5-Web-030118.mp3\">Download or Listen with this Link</a></p>\n<p><strong>This Week:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>What Gives? Print Journalism in the Digital Age.</li>\n<li>Is Pokémon Go All You Need to Know About Augmented Reality?</li>\n<li>IM Over Email?</li>\n<li>One Better Than 4G?</li>\n<li>Celebrity Death Threats on Twitter.</li>\n<li>Twitter&#8217;s War on Bots.</li>\n<li>YouTube&#8217;s Conspiracy Video Problem.</li>\n<li>Social Media, Social Justice? Or Just a Publicity Stunt?</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Global Media News is a weekly webcast covering new media news from around the world.  GMN is a production of  Media Studies students from the <a href=\"http://www.oldwestbury.edu/\" target=\"_self\">SUNY College @ Old Westbury.</a>   We scour the web for news about new media, journalism and technology.</p>\n<p>Listen to our next podcast streaming live on OWWR: Thursday March 8, 2018 @ 10 am EST.</p>\n<p>Can&#8217;t listen live? Our next podcast  will be posted by 2:00pm, Thursday March 8, 2018,  2018.</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/GlobalMediaNews\" target=\"_self\">Subscribe Now!</a></p>\n', NULL, 'APPROVED', 'AM327', NULL, '2018-03-02 21:39:36', 0, 'Download or Listen with this Link This Week: What Gives? Print Journalism in the Digital Age. Is Pokémon Go All You Need to Know About Augmented Reality? IM Over Email? One Better Than 4G? Celebrity Death Threats on Twitter. Twitter’s War on Bots. YouTube’s Conspiracy Video Problem. Social Media, Social Justice? Or Just a Publicity…\n', NULL, NULL, 1),
('ed4568c9-61ed-11f1-98fa-60cf847a2597', 'article', 'Speaker of the Assembly Carl Heastie Meets with President Calvin Butts', 'speaker-of-the-assembly-carl-heastie-meets-with-president-calvin-butts', NULL, '<figure id=\"attachment_1548\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-1548\" style=\"width: 610px\" class=\"wp-caption aligncenter\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"size-large wp-image-1548\" src=\"http://www.oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/Ricardo-Morales-Heastie-Butts-OWTV-1024x682.jpeg\" alt=\"\" width=\"610\" height=\"406\" /><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-1548\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">The Speaker &amp; The President at  OWTV: Samuel Ariyibi, Joseph Boscia, Carl Heastie, Calvin Butts, Lauren DeLeon, Terry Phebe, Joseph Boomer. Photo by Jing Wang for The Catalyst.</figcaption></figure>\n<p>The Speaker of the New York State Assembly, Carl Heastie came to Old Westbury on Wednesday, February 21st to meet with our president, Dr. Calvin Butts.   After the meeting, the President took the Speaker on a tour of the OWTV studios in the G-Wing of Campus Center.</p>\n<p>OWTV&#8217;s new Station Manager Jing Wang and Professor Lisa Payton introduced the visitors to the students at the station.  The tour showcased a newly reorganized equipment room, Studio A and B and the editing rooms.  Dr. Butts and Speaker Heastie spoke with students taking a production course and  several professors including Director of OWTV, Laura Chipley, and Samara Smith who gave a presentation on the future of OWTV. The G-Wing is becoming a center for emerging media as well as student TV and video production.  Several interns from OWTV  helped show off the equipment and projects they are working on this semester.  According to OWTV intern Brian Vignola, “I think it’s great that President Butts with the Speaker of the Assembly came to check out what we’re doing. We have a lot of ideas and can’t wait to execute them!”</p>\n', NULL, 'APPROVED', 'AM327', NULL, '2018-03-03 01:40:28', 0, 'The Speaker of the New York State Assembly, Carl Heastie came to Old Westbury on Wednesday, February 21st to meet with our president, Dr. Calvin Butts.   After the meeting, the President took the Speaker on a tour of the OWTV studios in the G-Wing of Campus Center. OWTV’s new Station Manager Jing Wang and Professor…\n', NULL, NULL, 1);
