n<div dir=\"ltr\">\n<div dir=\"ltr\">\n<div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\">\n<div dir=\"ltr\">\n<div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\">\n<div dir=\"ltr\">\n<div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\">\n<div dir=\"ltr\">\n<div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\">\n<div dir=\"ltr\">\n<div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\">\n<div dir=\"ltr\">\n<div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\">\n<div dir=\"ltr\">\n<div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\">\n<div dir=\"ltr\">\n<div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<div>Resolved that Dr. Calvin O. Butts, III be designated President Emeritus of the State University of New York College at Old Westbury in recognition of his past service effective September 15, 2020.”</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</blockquote>\n<div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\">\n<div dir=\"ltr\">\n<div dir=\"ltr\">\n<div dir=\"ltr\">\n<div dir=\"ltr\">\n<div dir=\"ltr\">\n<div dir=\"ltr\">\n<div dir=\"ltr\">\n<div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\">\n<div dir=\"ltr\">\n<div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\">\n<div dir=\"ltr\">\n<div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\">\n<div dir=\"ltr\">\n<div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\">\n<div dir=\"ltr\">\n<div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\">\n<div dir=\"ltr\">\n<div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\">\n<div dir=\"ltr\">\n<div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\">\n<div dir=\"ltr\">\n<div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\">\n<div dir=\"ltr\">\n<div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\">\n<div dir=\"ltr\">\n<div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\">\n<div dir=\"ltr\">\n<div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\">\n<div dir=\"ltr\">\n<div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\">\n<div dir=\"ltr\">\n<div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\">\n<div dir=\"ltr\">\n<div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\">\n<div dir=\"ltr\">\n<div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\">\n<div dir=\"ltr\">\n<div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\">\n<div dir=\"ltr\">\n<div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\">\n<div dir=\"ltr\">\n<div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\">\n<div dir=\"ltr\">\n<div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\">\n<div dir=\"ltr\">\n<div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\">\n<div dir=\"ltr\">\n<div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\">\n<div dir=\"ltr\">\n<div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\">\n<div dir=\"ltr\">\n<div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\">\n<div dir=\"ltr\">\n<div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\">\n<div dir=\"ltr\">\n<div>\n<div>\n<div></div>\n<div><b>About SUNY Old Westbury</b></div>\n<p>SUNY Old Westbury is a selective public liberal arts college with more than 5,000 students studying in more than 45 undergraduate degree opportunities in its liberal arts and professional programs and 19 graduate programs in business, data analytics, education, liberal studies, and mental health counseling.  On the College’s 604-acre campus, students are challenged to take ownership of their futures through an environment that demands academic excellence, fosters intercultural understanding, and endeavors to stimulate a passion for learning and a commitment to building a more just and sustainable world.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n', NULL, 'APPROVED', 'TC527', NULL, '2020-09-17 01:31:42', 0, '  Old Westbury, New York…September 16, 2020…  SUNY Chancellor James Malatras and the SUNY Board of Trustees officially appointed Calvin O. Butts, III as President Emeritus of the State University of New York at Old Westbury, in recognition of his 20 years of distinguished service to the college. The appointment was made during the Board’s September…\n', NULL, NULL, 1);
INSERT INTO `content` (`id`, `type`, `title`, `slug`, `description`, `content`, `url`, `approval_status`, `author_id`, `editor_id`, `created_at`, `is_featured`, `excerpt`, `video_url`, `featured_image`, `category_id`) VALUES
('ed543dad-61ed-11f1-98fa-60cf847a2597', 'article', 'New COVID-19 Testing Program to Begin Immediately', 'new-covid-19-testing-program-to-begin-immediately', NULL, '<div dir=\"ltr\">\n<div>\n<div>\n<p>Good morning,</p>\n<p>Effective today, SUNY Old Westbury is launching a <a href=\"https://www.oldwestbury.edu/life/student-health/covid-19-testing\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\" data-saferedirecturl=\"https://www.google.com/url?q=https://www.oldwestbury.edu/life/student-health/covid-19-testing&amp;source=gmail&amp;ust=1601060932013000&amp;usg=AFQjCNGg2kpZl42f7azevAJWKUEwUqhJ7w\"> testing program as a means to survey the prevalence of COVID-19</a> in our campus community. This program is consistent with the <a href=\"https://www.suny.edu/suny-news/press-releases/09-2020/9-4-20-testing/covid-testing-program.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\" data-saferedirecturl=\"https://www.google.com/url?q=https://www.suny.edu/suny-news/press-releases/09-2020/9-4-20-testing/covid-testing-program.html&amp;source=gmail&amp;ust=1601060932013000&amp;usg=AFQjCNFsSXRLYg6o3oA2L5ouYLTs2q6mdw\"> recent SUNY policy</a> requiring all campuses to conduct surveillance testing for COVID-19.</p>\n<p>In short, we are asking all at Old Westbury to “Defend the Den” by adhering to the new testing protocol along with our now-standard face covering, social distancing, symptom reporting, and hygiene awareness efforts.</p>\n<p><strong>Each week, students who visit campus will be tested for COVID-19 at random and all faculty and staff who come to campus will be urged to undergo testing multiple times during the remainder of the semester.</strong> The College will collect samples using nasal swabs. This form of testing was selected due to the reduced number of people visiting campus during the semester and to ensure the fastest, most accurate results for all in our community.</p>\n<p>Professionals from our Student Health Center will be collecting samples from students and employees via pop-up testing sites on random days each week. <strong>While there is no fee related to taking the sample, your insurance company will be asked to cover the cost of the analysis, so please bring your College ID and insurance card with you any time you come to campus.</strong>  Enzo Clinical Labs will analyze the collected samples with an expected turnaround of results in 1-3 days. Results will be reported to each participant by Dr. Ellen Feit, the campus’ senior medical advisor.</p>\n<p>In addition, if you are tested outside the College’s “Defend the Den” program and receive a positive result, please report that result immediately to the Student Health Center (students) or Office of Human Resources (faculty and staff).</p>\n<p>Aggregate totals from testing and self-reported results are reported through the <a href=\"https://www.oldwestbury.edu/campus-guide/covid19-tracker\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\" data-saferedirecturl=\"https://www.google.com/url?q=https://www.oldwestbury.edu/campus-guide/covid19-tracker&amp;source=gmail&amp;ust=1601060932013000&amp;usg=AFQjCNHFOoqCBHUWFUwbqWAhMASbmczpaA\"> COVID-19 Status Page</a> on the SUNY Old Westbury website.</p>\n<p>Understanding whether and how COVID-19 is impacting our campus must be a priority for all members of our community. As we collectively “Defend the Den,” we will be able to show each other, and the greater Long Island community, that SUNY Old Westbury is committed to providing a healthy, safe and productive educational environment for all who study and work here.</p>\n<p>Thank you in advance for your cooperation as we “Defend the Den.”</p>\n<p>Teresa A. Miller<br />\nOfficer-in-Charge</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"iX\">&#8230;</div>\n', NULL, 'APPROVED', 'TC527', NULL, '2020-09-24 19:17:55', 0, 'Good morning, Effective today, SUNY Old Westbury is launching a testing program as a means to survey the prevalence of COVID-19 in our campus community. This program is consistent with the recent SUNY policy requiring all campuses to conduct surveillance testing for COVID-19. In short, we are asking all at Old Westbury to “Defend the…\n', NULL, NULL, 1),
('ed548801-61ed-11f1-98fa-60cf847a2597', 'podcast', 'NMB: New Media Beat Podcast!', 'nmb-new-media-beat-podcast', NULL, '\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"640\" height=\"320\" src=\"uploads/Your-New-Media-Update-Console.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1345\" srcset=\"https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/Your-New-Media-Update-Console.png 640w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/Your-New-Media-Update-Console-600x300.png 600w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/Your-New-Media-Update-Console-300x150.png 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" /><figcaption>Media Majors Making Media!</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Listen to our First NMB Podcast of 2022!</strong></h2>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-audio\"><audio controls src=\"https://www.oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/NMB-1-Web-2022-02-24.mp3\"></audio></figure>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><li>Romance Scams on Dating Apps: Netflix Makes the &#8220;Tinder Swindler&#8221; a Star?</li><li>Accounts for Kids? How Young is too Young for North West?</li><li>&#8220;Feed&#8221; Just &#8220;Feed&#8221; &#8211;Where Did the &#8220;News&#8221; Go on Facebook?</li><li>No More Meta for Europeans?&nbsp; Why is Meta Threatening to Stop Social in the EU?</li><li>Brand Bait: Hey Influencer! Your Platform Has a &#8220;Media Kit&#8221; Just for You.</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">The NMB Podcast streams live on <a href=\"http://www.owwrny.org/\">OId Westbury Web Radio</a> every Thursday from 10:00-11:00 AM EST.&nbsp; Can&#8217;t listen live? Our podcast will be <a href=\"https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/?cat=17\">posted</a> for your listening pleasure every Thursday by 10:00 PM.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">NMB is produced by Zachary Lasky &amp; Mohammad Shumail.&nbsp; Our engineer is Niklaus Feil. This week the podcast was edited by Mohammad Shumail and Niklaus Feil.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\"><a href=\"https://www.newmediabeat.org/\"><strong>New Media Beat</strong></a> covers new media news from around the world.&nbsp; NMB</span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">&nbsp;is a production of&nbsp; Media Studies students from the <a href=\"https://www.oldwestbury.edu/\" target=\"_self\" rel=\"noopener\">SUNY College @ Old Westbury.</a>&nbsp;&nbsp; We scour the web for news about about the world of media, journalism and technology.</span></p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">Follow<strong> <a href=\"https://twitter.com/OWWRGMN\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">@OWWRGMN</a></strong> for a curated feed of the latest new media news for aspiring media professionals.</span></p>\n', NULL, 'APPROVED', 'TC527', NULL, '2022-02-25 12:33:44', 0, 'Listen to our First NMB Podcast of 2022! Romance Scams on Dating Apps: Netflix Makes the “Tinder Swindler” a Star? Accounts for Kids? How Young is too Young for North West? “Feed” Just “Feed” –Where Did the “News” Go on Facebook? No More Meta for Europeans?  Why is Meta Threatening to Stop Social in the…\n', NULL, NULL, 1),
('ed54d1e3-61ed-11f1-98fa-60cf847a2597', 'podcast', '<strong>Listen to NMB: We Bring the News!</strong>', 'listen-to-nmb-we-bring-the-news', NULL, '\n<figure class=\"wp-block-audio\"><audio controls src=\"https://www.oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/NMB-2-Web-2022-03-03.mp3\"></audio><figcaption>From our new media newsroom at OWWR: <a href=\"https://www.newmediabeat.org/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">New Media Beat</a> delivers!</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><li>True or False? Truth Social Is Open for Business.</li><li>Meta Grapples with Apple: Will Making Opt-Out the Default Defeat the Data Trackers?</li><li>Dating Don&#8217;ts on Dating Apps: Crypto Scams for Lovers?</li><li>Shade Room Tips for Making Tea: Keep Your Roommates Happy?</li><li>Deliver Me This: Food from the TikTok Kitchen</li><li>Russian Journalists at War &#8212; With Their Government?</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">The NMB Podcast streams live on <a href=\"http://www.owwrny.org/\">Old Westbury Web Radio</a> every Thursday from 10:00-11:00 AM EST.&nbsp; Can&#8217;t listen live? Our podcast will be <a href=\"https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/?cat=17\">posted</a> for your listening pleasure every Friday.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">NMB is produced by Zachary Lasky &amp; Mohammad Shumail.&nbsp; Our engineer is Niklaus Feil. This week the podcast was edited by Mohammad Shumail.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\"><a href=\"https://www.newmediabeat.org/\"><strong>New Media Beat</strong></a> covers new media news from around the world.&nbsp; NMB</span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">&nbsp;is a production of&nbsp; Media Studies students from the <a href=\"https://www.oldwestbury.edu/\" target=\"_self\" rel=\"noopener\">SUNY College @ Old Westbury.</a>&nbsp;&nbsp; We scour the web for news about about the world of media, journalism and technology.</span></p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">Follow<strong> <a rel=\"noopener\" href=\"https://twitter.com/OWWRGMN\" target=\"_blank\">@OWWRGMN</a></strong> for a curated feed of the latest new media news for aspiring media professionals</span>.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1200\" height=\"920\" src=\"uploads/NMB-1-Polygon-Flamingo-A-1200x920.jpg\" alt=\"New Media Beat in Studio A\" class=\"wp-image-6735\" srcset=\"https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/NMB-1-Polygon-Flamingo-A-1200x920.jpg 1200w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/NMB-1-Polygon-Flamingo-A-600x460.jpg 600w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/NMB-1-Polygon-Flamingo-A-768x589.jpg 768w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/NMB-1-Polygon-Flamingo-A-1536x1178.jpg 1536w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/NMB-1-Polygon-Flamingo-A-2048x1570.jpg 2048w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/NMB-1-Polygon-Flamingo-A-300x230.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" /><figcaption><a href=\"https://www.newmediabeat.org/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\"><strong>New Media Beat</strong> </a>on <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"http://owwrny.org/\" target=\"_blank\">Old Westbury Web Radio</a>, Thursdays at 10AM. Photo: Zachary Lasky</figcaption></figure>\n', NULL, 'APPROVED', 'TC527', NULL, '2022-03-04 18:56:32', 0, 'True or False? Truth Social Is Open for Business. Meta Grapples with Apple: Will Making Opt-Out the Default Defeat the Data Trackers? Dating Don’ts on Dating Apps: Crypto Scams for Lovers? Shade Room Tips for Making Tea: Keep Your Roommates Happy? Deliver Me This: Food from the TikTok Kitchen Russian Journalists at War — With…\n', NULL, NULL, 1),
('ed5518e2-61ed-11f1-98fa-60cf847a2597', 'podcast', 'NMB: Your New Media News Update!', 'nmb-your-new-media-news-update', NULL, '\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://www.oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/NMB-3-Banner-Catalyst-1-1024x397.jpg\" alt=\"New Media Beat podcast hosts at OWWR\" class=\"wp-image-6766\"/><figcaption>Host Jake Martin  with Niklaus Feil our engineer.  <em>Photo: Zachary Lasky.</em></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-audio\"><audio controls src=\"https://www.oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/NMB-3-Web-2022-03-10.mp3\"></audio></figure>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><li><strong>Can Twitch Stop the Hate Raids?</strong></li><li><strong>Will Spacelink Bring the Internet to Ukraine from Outer Space?</strong></li><li><strong>Russia&#8217;s War on Social Media: Can Putin Hold Back the Tide?</strong></li><li><strong>Why Does Meta Have a Safety Course for Journalists?</strong></li><li><strong>Streaming Fees Are Rising: Should You Switch Back to Cable? </strong></li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">The NMB Podcast streams live on <a href=\"http://www.owwrny.org/\">Old Westbury Web Radio</a> every Thursday from 10:00-11:00 AM EST.&nbsp; Can&#8217;t listen live? Our podcast will be <a href=\"https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/?cat=17\">posted</a> for your listening pleasure every Friday afternoon.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">NMB is produced by Zachary Lasky &amp; Mohammad Shumail.  Our engineer is Niklaus Feil. This week the podcast was hosted by Jake Martin with reports by Bryan Dupuy, Niklaus Feil, and Wendy Verdieu. Mohammad Shumail edited our audio.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\"><a href=\"https://www.newmediabeat.org/\"><strong>New Media Beat</strong></a> covers new media news from around the world.&nbsp; NMB</span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">&nbsp;is a production of&nbsp; Media Studies students from the <a href=\"https://www.oldwestbury.edu/\" target=\"_self\" rel=\"noopener\">SUNY College @ Old Westbury.</a>&nbsp;&nbsp; We scour the web for news about about the world of media, journalism and technology.</span></p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">Follow<strong> <a rel=\"noopener\" href=\"https://twitter.com/OWWRGMN\" target=\"_blank\">@OWWRGMN</a></strong> for a curated feed of the latest new media news for aspiring media professionals.</span></p>\n', NULL, 'APPROVED', 'TC527', NULL, '2022-03-11 16:36:16', 0, 'Can Twitch Stop the Hate Raids? Will Spacelink Bring the Internet to Ukraine from Outer Space? Russia’s War on Social Media: Can Putin Hold Back the Tide? Why Does Meta Have a Safety Course for Journalists? Streaming Fees Are Rising: Should You Switch Back to Cable? The NMB Podcast streams live on Old Westbury Web…\n', NULL, NULL, 1),
