('ed55b8e5-61ed-11f1-98fa-60cf847a2597', 'podcast', 'Instagram & Defector Media on New Media Beat!', 'instagram-defector-media-on-new-media-beat', NULL, '\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/NMB-Stone-Wall-Bud-Branches--1024x657.jpg\" alt=\"New Media Beat Logo on Stone Wall with Budding Branches\" class=\"wp-image-3916\"/><figcaption><strong>This Week: Instagram&#8217;s Creative Lab &amp; Defector Media&#8217;s Twist on Sports!</strong></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-audio\"><audio controls src=\"uploads/NMB-5-WEB-2022-04-07.mp3\"></audio></figure>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><li>Attracting Attention: Instagram&#8217;s Creator Lab </li><li>Defector Serves Sports with a side of Culture: Are the Fans Hungry?</li></ul>\n\n\n<p><!-- /wp:post-content --></p>\n<p><!-- wp:audio {\"id\":3711,\"align\":\"center\"} --></p>\n<figure class=\"wp-block-audio aligncenter\"></figure>\n<p><!-- /wp:audio --></p>\n<p><!-- wp:list --></p>\n<p><!-- /wp:list --></p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --></p>\n<p>The NMB Podcast streams live on <a href=\"http://www.owwrny.org/\">Old Westbury Web Radio</a> every Thursday from 10:00-11:00 AM EST.&nbsp; Can&#8217;t listen live? Our podcast will be <a href=\"https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/?cat=17\">posted</a> for your listening pleasure every Friday afternoon.</p>\n<p><!-- /wp:paragraph --></p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --></p>\n<p>NMB is produced by Zachary Lasky &amp; Muhammad Shumail.&nbsp; Our engineer this week was Zachary Lasky and the audio editing was done by Muhammad Shumail.&nbsp; This week&#8217;s hosts: Tyler Carr &amp; Saaraa Sattaur!</p>\n<p><!-- /wp:paragraph --></p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\"><a href=\"https://www.newmediabeat.org/\"><strong>New Media Beat</strong></a> covers new media news from around the world.&nbsp; NMB</span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">&nbsp;is a production of&nbsp; Media Studies students from the <a href=\"https://www.oldwestbury.edu/\" target=\"_self\" rel=\"noopener\">SUNY College @ Old Westbury.</a>&nbsp;&nbsp; We scour the web for news about about the world of media, journalism and technology.</span></p>\n<p><!-- /wp:paragraph --></p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">Follow<strong> <a href=\"https://twitter.com/OWWRGMN\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">@OWWRGMN</a></strong> for a curated feed of the latest new media news for aspiring media professionals.</span></p>\n<p><!-- /wp:paragraph --></p>\n<p><!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"center\",\"id\":3713,\"sizeSlug\":\"full\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\",\"className\":\"is-style-rounded\"} --></p>\n<p><!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"center\",\"id\":3910,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} --></p>\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\">&nbsp;</div>\n<p><!-- /wp:image --></p>\n<p><!-- wp:image {\"id\":3910,\"width\":885,\"height\":369,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} --></p>\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"wp-image-3910\" src=\"https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/NMB-6-banner-green-square-1024x428.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"885\" height=\"369\"><figcaption>Producer Muhammad Shumail setting up in Studio A at <a href=\"http://www.owwrny.org/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" data-type=\"URL\" data-id=\"http://www.owwrny.org/\">Old Westbury Web Radio.</a></figcaption></figure>\n<p><!-- /wp:image --></p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --></p>\n<p><!-- /wp:paragraph --></p>', NULL, 'APPROVED', 'TC527', NULL, '2022-04-08 19:01:11', 0, 'Our Podcast: Defector Media’s Twist on Sports. Instagram’s Creator Lab Draws a Crowd. All Your Media News in less than Seven Minutes!\n', NULL, NULL, 1),
('ed56044a-61ed-11f1-98fa-60cf847a2597', 'article', 'Review: Netflix’s Interactive Game Show, Trivia Quest', 'review-netflixs-interactive-game-show-trivia-quest', NULL, '\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" src=\"uploads/hIiHt-3e8o0wyeOI8h1BxacImk31KJzIFYmABHTqnOyYNyrAtbf4vTG5fbsB86vYs2rO2ZcFJnVIfm6TVRMmtbsj2__Jn7QHsamUOvX4jCkgNgUUxIDXujFeqLUJ8BOzz9RVEdZH.jpg\" alt=\'\' width=\"617\" height=\"324\"/><figcaption>Photo Credit: Netflix.com</figcaption></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Do you prefer to compete against your friends or embark on an individual quest?</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">On April 1st, Netflix launched its first interactive game show called <em>Trivia Quest</em>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">The inspiration for <em>Trivia Quest</em> came from the 2013 smartphone application, <a href=\"https://g.co/kgs/EhRtt2\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Trivia Crack</a>. However, the show has its own individual features.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">When I clicked on the colorful icon to watch the show, an enthusiastic talking wheel named Willy invited me to play. The show follows a simple plot: Rocky, the villain, captured Willy’s friends. Willy has to free them and needs <em>your</em> help.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">The narration script uses very simple language and seems geared towards a children’s audience. However, the two different modes for the trivia questions appeal to different participating age groups. You can choose between standard mode, hard mode, or both! If you choose both, you can answer differing levels of questions.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Players also have the ability to replay the episode which leads them to answer the same questions.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">This provides a second chance for the player, who will get coins for whatever questions they previously answered wrong but got right the second time around.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Players must free Willy’s friends by earning knowledge keys. To do this, you need to get coins. When you answer a question correctly, you are rewarded with these coins.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Every day, you can continue the journey with new timed questions. The questions follow a daily theme.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">As I answered questions, an exercising football, a test tube filled with bubbly liquid in outer space, and a paintbrush in a photography studio appeared on my screen.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">So, what do I think of the interactive game show? In my opinion, I prefer experiencing a competition. When I think of a game show, I think of competing against other individuals to win a grand prize. On the Trivia Crack application, you take turns answering questions with other players. You can play against a stranger or a friend. At the end of a Trivia Crack game, one person wins. Trivia Quest has a different organization.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">For the Trivia Quest game show, I believe players should have an optional leaderboard feature to see how they are playing compared to others. This would provide a feature for those who crave competition. It would also allow people to continue to play individually if they prefer.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">If you’re searching for an activity to do by yourself such as fun trivia, I recommend playing Trivia Quest! If you’re searching for competition, I would suggest downloading the Trivia Crack application.</p>\n', NULL, 'APPROVED', 'JV368', NULL, '2022-04-11 18:47:10', 0, 'Do you prefer to compete against your friends or embark on an individual quest? On April 1st, Netflix launched its first interactive game show called Trivia Quest. The inspiration for Trivia Quest came from the 2013 smartphone application, Trivia Crack. However, the show has its own individual features. When I clicked on the colorful icon…\n', NULL, NULL, 6),
('ed5648a2-61ed-11f1-98fa-60cf847a2597', 'podcast', 'New Media Beat: Podcasting from OWWR!', 'new-media-beat-podcasting-from-owwr', NULL, '\n<figure class=\"wp-block-audio aligncenter\"><audio controls src=\"uploads/NMB-6-Web-2022-04-14.mp3\"></audio></figure>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><li> TikTok Challenge: Get Out the Vote!</li><li>What Happened to the Black News Channel?</li><li>Russian War Music: Spotify is Down. Yandex is Up.</li><li>News Regulations: Can Australia Tame the Platforms?</li><li>Why Does the Yes Network Want Jomboy Media?</li><li>Scam Alert: Meta&#8217;s Battle Against Fake &amp; Frauds on Facebook</li></ul>\n\n\n<p>The NMB Podcast streams live on <a href=\"http://www.owwrny.org/\">Old Westbury Web Radio</a> every Thursday from 10:00-11:00 AM EST.&nbsp; Can&#8217;t listen live? Our podcast will be <a href=\"https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/?cat=17\">posted</a> for your listening pleasure every Friday afternoon. &nbsp;</p>\n<p><!-- /wp:post-content --></p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --></p>\n<p>NMB was produced by Victoria Van Grembergen.&nbsp; Our engineer is Zachary Lasky.&nbsp; This week&#8217;s hosts: Jalani Gadsden &amp; Kurt Miller! &nbsp;</p>\n<p><!-- /wp:paragraph --></p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.newmediabeat.org/\"><strong>New Media Beat</strong></a> covers new media news from around the world.&nbsp;NMB&nbsp;is a production of&nbsp; Media Studies students from the <a href=\"https://www.oldwestbury.edu/\" target=\"_self\" rel=\"noopener\">SUNY College @ Old Westbury.</a>&nbsp;&nbsp; We scour the web for news about about the world of media, journalism and technology.</p>\n<p><!-- /wp:paragraph --></p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --></p>\n<p>Follow<strong> <a href=\"https://twitter.com/OWWRGMN\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">@OWWRGMN</a></strong> for a curated feed of the latest new media news for aspiring media professionals.</p>\n<p><!-- wp:image {\"id\":4119,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} --></p>\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/Dandelion-Banner-Top-Web-1-1024x320.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4119\"><figcaption><sup>Podcast are growing like weeds this spring at <a href=\"http://www.owwrny.org/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Old Westbury Web Radio!</a></sup></figcaption></figure>\n<p><!-- /wp:image --></p>', NULL, 'APPROVED', 'TC527', NULL, '2022-04-15 18:43:15', 0, 'TikTok Gets Out the Vote | Black News Channel Disappears | Spotify Says Nyet? | Aussies vs. Platforms | Jomboy Media! | Fraud on Facebook\n', NULL, NULL, 1),
('ed5697f8-61ed-11f1-98fa-60cf847a2597', 'podcast', 'At the Plate: New Media Beat!', 'at-the-plate-new-media-beat', NULL, '\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"uploads/Galvanized-Cherry-Square-Small-1.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-6927\"/><figcaption>Nothing but Media &amp; Cherry Blossoms . . .</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-audio\"><audio controls src=\"uploads/NMB-7-Web-2022-04-21.mp3\"></audio><figcaption>This Week on New Media Beat: Baseball, Apple, Youtube, &amp; Somalia!</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><li>&nbsp;Did Apple TV+ Get on Base with the Fans?</li><li>Why Did Google Drop YouTube Vanced?</li><li>Bilan: Somalia&#8217;s New All-Women Media House!</li></ul>\n\n\n<p>The NMB Podcast streams live on <a href=\"http://www.owwrny.org/\">Old Westbury Web Radio</a> every Thursday from 10:00-11:00 AM EST.&nbsp; Can&#8217;t listen live? Our podcast will be <a href=\"https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/?cat=17\">posted</a> for your listening pleasure every Friday afternoon.</p>\n<p><!-- /wp:post-content --></p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --></p>\n<p>NMB was produced by Zachary Lasky.&nbsp; Our engineer is Niklaus Feil.&nbsp; This week&#8217;s hosts: Bryan Dupuy &amp; Jake Martin!</p>\n<p><!-- /wp:paragraph --></p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.newmediabeat.org/\"><strong>New Media Beat</strong></a> covers new media news from around the world.&nbsp;NMB&nbsp;is a production of&nbsp; Media Studies students from the <a href=\"https://www.oldwestbury.edu/\" target=\"_self\" rel=\"noopener\">SUNY College @ Old Westbury.</a>&nbsp;&nbsp; We scour the web for news about about the world of media, journalism and technology.</p>\n<p><!-- /wp:paragraph --></p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --></p>\n<p>Follow<strong> <a href=\"https://twitter.com/OWWRGMN\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">@OWWRGMN</a></strong> for a curated feed of the latest new media news for aspiring media professionals.</p>\n<p><!-- wp:image {\"id\":4119,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} --></p>\n<p><!-- /wp:image --></p>\n<p><!-- wp:image {\"id\":4350,\"width\":928,\"height\":418,\"sizeSlug\":\"full\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} --></p>\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"wp-image-4350\" src=\"uploads/Galvanized-Cherry-Square-Web-1200x1200.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"928\" height=\"418\"><figcaption><sup>NMB: The Galvanized Cherry of Podcasts!</sup></figcaption></figure>\n<p><!-- /wp:image --></p>', NULL, 'APPROVED', 'TC527', NULL, '2022-04-22 15:38:50', 0, 'MLB Streaming Baseball on Apple TV+ – Google Stops Vanced from Giving Away YouTube – Somali Journalists Open Bilan!\n', NULL, NULL, 1),
('ed56e4b3-61ed-11f1-98fa-60cf847a2597', 'article', 'Silencing The Cell Phone', 'silencing-the-cell-phone', NULL, '\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"alignleft is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" src=\"uploads/anTFyYt2E11qt2Zi_pGy8g4hLUSTGy7cZLaq6R588KX4tvUaFRxJ3ERU5tzjTUDr21p7361zDseua0-SIttVCh-zPXNzVzw5CnjPCtycIfpyDTxnfiy9JOwPnN4m5XFnoxTIys5.jpg\" alt=\'\' width=\"344\" height=\"340\"/><figcaption>Photo Credit: Apple</figcaption></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Cell phones have shaped the way we function as a society. We text using small symbolic images, create trends through the use of social media, and walk around with a device in our pockets that connects us to the rest of the world. What would happen if we reduced our cell phone usage?</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">For over a month, I limited the way that I used my own cell phone by managing the time spent on certain applications. I never excessively used my phone, but I felt as if uselessly scrolling on it hindered my own productivity and restricted my capacity to enjoy life around me.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">When I embarked on this journey, I noticed that a lot of the time that I previously spent on my phone shifted to getting ahead in my schoolwork. I always completed my work on time and to the best of my ability, but with the free time that I gained, I submitted many assignments multiple days in advance. This also created more time to spend with my family.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">In the free time I gained after reducing my phone usage, I also found myself drawn to music. While I listen to music through my phone, I don’t actively have to use my phone. I discovered new feel-good songs that provided me with a positive and encouraging outlet.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">I don’t have many social media applications, so I didn’t feel extremely challenged when I decided that I would reduce and regulate the time I spent on these applications. The real challenge came when my phone’s service unexpectedly stopped working. I could not send or receive text messages or phone calls. The social media applications seemed like the only way to communicate with others. Still, I made sure I did not exceed the limits I had set for myself.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">After a month of limiting my phone usage, I scrolled on TikTok to see what trends I missed and what new, funny sounds popularized. However, I didn’t find myself missing the app the way that I thought I would. I frequently came across advertisements and most videos didn’t appeal to my interests. I realized that I can find ways to explore my interests without social media.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">I also didn’t need my phone for entertainment. I spent a weekend in a rural area in Connecticut with limited Internet access. Instead of reaching for my phone, I walked down to the lake and admired the beauty of the rippling blue water. I listened to the wind rustling the dried leaves on the ground and the sounds of the birds singing in the trees.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">In today’s world, everyone walks around with a phone in their hand. When crossing the street, they send text messages instead of looking both ways. Through my personal experience, I’ve learned that it’s important to disconnect once in a while and enjoy what life has to offer.</p>\n', NULL, 'APPROVED', 'JV368', NULL, '2022-04-28 21:01:20', 0, 'Cell phones have shaped the way we function as a society. We text using small symbolic images, create trends through the use of social media, and walk around with a device in our pockets that connects us to the rest of the world. What would happen if we reduced our cell phone usage? For over…\n', NULL, NULL, 6),
('ed57319e-61ed-11f1-98fa-60cf847a2597', 'podcast', 'Are You New Media Curious?', 'are-you-new-media-curious', NULL, '\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1200\" height=\"794\" src=\"uploads/NMB-Dogwood-Small-1200x794.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-6997\" srcset=\"https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/NMB-Dogwood-Small-1200x794.jpg 1200w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/NMB-Dogwood-Small-600x397.jpg 600w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/NMB-Dogwood-Small-768x508.jpg 768w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/NMB-Dogwood-Small-1536x1016.jpg 1536w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/NMB-Dogwood-Small-300x198.jpg 300w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/NMB-Dogwood-Small.jpg 1732w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-audio\"><audio controls src=\"uploads/NMB-8-Web-2022-04-28.mp3\"></audio><figcaption><br><strong>This Week on New Media Beat: Reddit, Pinterest, Data-Tracking, Text Scams &amp; Halo!</strong></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><li>Reddit: r/Place to Be? To Be What?</li><li>Pinterest Moderates the Climate</li><li>Who&#8217;s Tracking You Now? Data Tracking for Dummies. . .</li><li>Halo-Infinite: A Live-Streaming Success Story?</li><li>Threat or Menace? Text Scams and Spam.</li></ul>\n\n\n<p>The NMB Podcast streams live on <a href=\"http://www.owwrny.org/\">Old Westbury Web Radio</a> every Thursday from 10:00-11:00 AM EST.  Can&#8217;t listen live? Our podcast will be <a href=\"https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/?cat=17\">posted</a> for your listening pleasure every Friday afternoon.</p>\n<p><!-- /wp:post-content --></p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --></p>\n<p>NMB was produced by Zachary Lasky and Muhammad Shumail.  Our engineer is Niklaus Feil.  Our audio was edited by Muhammad Shumail. This week&#8217;s hosts: Josiah Martinez &amp; Victoria Van Grembergen!</p>\n<p><!-- /wp:paragraph --></p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.newmediabeat.org/\"><strong>New Media Beat</strong></a> covers new media news from around the world. NMB is a production of  Media Studies students from the <a href=\"https://www.oldwestbury.edu/\" target=\"_self\" rel=\"noopener\">SUNY College @ Old Westbury.</a>   We scour the web for news about about the world of media, journalism and technology.</p>\n<p><!-- /wp:paragraph --></p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --></p>\n<p>Follow<strong> <a href=\"https://twitter.com/OWWRGMN\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">@OWWRGMN</a></strong> for a curated feed of the latest new media news for aspiring media professionals.</p>\n<p><!-- wp:image {\"id\":4119,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} /--></p>\n<p><!-- wp:image {\"id\":4350,\"width\":928,\"height\":418,\"sizeSlug\":\"full\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} --></p>\n<p><!-- /wp:image --></p>\n<p><!-- wp:image {\"id\":4470,\"width\":888,\"height\":665,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} --></p>\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"wp-image-4470\" src=\"uploads/NMB-Dandelion-Square-web-1200x1103.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"888\" height=\"665\" />\n<figcaption><sup>Media news springs up like weeds in our newsroom at <a href=\"http://www.owwrny.org/\">Old Westbury Web Radio!</a></sup></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p><!-- /wp:image --></p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --></p>\n<p><!-- /wp:paragraph --></p>', NULL, 'APPROVED', 'TC527', NULL, '2022-04-29 17:46:14', 0, 'Why Was r/Place the Place to Be? | Pinterest Moderates the Climate | Data Tracking for Dummies | Halo Infinite Streams Run Out | Defense Against the Scam Texts |\n', NULL, NULL, 1),
('ed577b14-61ed-11f1-98fa-60cf847a2597', 'article', 'Will the FDA Ban Menthol Cigarettes?', 'will-the-fda-ban-menthol-cigarettes', NULL, '\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" src=\"uploads/A2mjZOeuRoHpBf3cdC5jlDbKOYc0bJp56v8kmuDOKUcewNY8c5W4U8DhGBa9b8CLf2YUvAZkSSvSc-decXbkx3ajHuqNdgbXoJut8LMk6LVffWWCLoP-DeOmMRb1oi2ik5Kv52JFkl8wdw1dpw.jpg\" alt=\'\' width=\"661\" height=\"345\"/><figcaption>Photo Credit: <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://truthinitiative.org/research-resources/traditional-tobacco-products/menthol-facts-stats-and-regulations\" target=\"_blank\">TruthInitiative.org</a></figcaption></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">On April 28, 2022, the Food and Drug Administration proposed a ban on menthol flavoring in cigarettes. </p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">According to the <a href=\"https://www.fda.gov/news-events/press-announcements/fda-proposes-rules-prohibiting-menthol-cigarettes-and-flavored-cigars-prevent-youth-initiation\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">FDA</a>, the proposal aims to minimize disease and death related to tobacco use. The organization also hopes to limit youth exposure to tobacco.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">The proposed ban will not impact individual consumers who possess or use the product. The FDA said that they “will only address manufacturers, distributors, wholesalers, importers and retailers who manufacture, distribute, or sell such products within the U.S. that are not in compliance with applicable requirements.”</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">The FDA explained that the proposition targets menthol because of its appeal to the youth and young adult population. The <a href=\"https://truthinitiative.org/research-resources/traditional-tobacco-products/menthol-facts-stats-and-regulations\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Truth Initiative</a> said that menthol “reduces the harshness of cigarette smoke due to its characteristic cooling effects on the mouth and throat.” Many smokers use menthol flavors for this reason.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">One group at high-risk for menthol use includes the youth population. The <a href=\"https://www.cdc.gov/tobacco/basic_information/tobacco_industry/menthol-cigarettes/index.html#:~:text=Young%20people%20and%20African%20Americans,menthol%20cigarettes%20than%20other%20groups.&amp;text=More%20than%20half%20(54%25),who%20smoke%20use%20menthol%20cigarettes.&amp;text=That%20percentage%20is%20higher%20than,older%20who%20smoke%20menthol%20cigarettes.\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">CDC</a> reported that fifty-four percent of youth smokers aged twelve to seventeen use menthol cigarettes. They also reported that many individuals who began to smoke as a young adult first used menthol cigarettes.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Another high-risk group regarding menthol use includes African Americans. The CDC explained that “Non-Hispanic black adults have the highest percentage of menthol cigarette use compared to other racial and ethnic groups.”</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">The FDA proposal also includes banning flavors, besides tobacco, in cigars.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">This proposal faces both opposition and support. <a href=\"https://twitter.com/USlawreview/status/1519735558964195329\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">One Twitter user</a> said, “It took a constitutional amendment to ban alcohol 100 years ago but now without any amendment to the constitution, the FDA claims it has the ‘authority’ to just ‘ban menthol’ in cigarettes and pretty much anything else it ‘decides to’. We live under a complete tyranny.”&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\"><a href=\"https://twitter.com/actiononsmoking/status/1519821164226355200\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Another Twitter user</a> said, “Great news from #FDA today regarding a proposed ban on menthol tobacco!!!&nbsp; Congrats to the many, many people who helped to make this happen. #banmenthol #tobaccocontrol.”</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">It still remains to be seen if, and when, the ban on menthol in cigarettes will go into effect.</p>\n', NULL, 'APPROVED', 'JV368', NULL, '2022-05-01 13:08:25', 0, 'On April 28, 2022, the Food and Drug Administration proposed a ban on menthol flavoring in cigarettes.  According to the FDA, the proposal aims to minimize disease and death related to tobacco use. The organization also hopes to limit youth exposure to tobacco.  The proposed ban will not impact individual consumers who possess or use…\n', NULL, NULL, 1),
('ed57d2f0-61ed-11f1-98fa-60cf847a2597', 'article', 'MAC Awards: Wednesday May 4, 7:00PM', 'mac-awards-wednesday-may-4-700pm', NULL, '<p><strong><span style=\"font-size: 18pt;\"><a href=\"https://youtu.be/0yCJYF0qfNs\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Live on Youtube at 7:00pm Wednesday May 4!</a></span></strong><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-4613 \" src=\"uploads/MAC-Square-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"519\" height=\"802\" /></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family: georgia, palatino, serif; font-size: 18pt;\"><a href=\"https://youtu.be/0yCJYF0qfNs\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Watch the show live at 7:00pm Wednesday, May 4</a>.</span></p>\n<p><strong><a href=\"http://www.macawards.org/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><span style=\"font-family: georgia, palatino, serif; font-size: 18pt;\">Check out the Work at MACAWARDS.ORG</span></a></strong></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">The MAC Awards are a celebration of the best student work in Print, Digital Arts, Radio, Television, Video and New Media from the students of <strong><a href=\"https://www.oldwestbury.edu/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">SUNY College at Old Westbury</a>.</strong>  </span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">The MAC Awards show recognizes excellence in student creativity, journalism, and production skills.  </span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\"><strong>This is our 14th year!</strong></span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">These awards are a co-production of:</span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\"><strong><a href=\"https://www.oldwestbury.edu/departments/arts\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">The Visual Arts Department</a> </strong></span></li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\"><strong><a href=\"https://www.oldwestbury.edu/academics/offerings/media-and-communications-ba\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">The American Studies/Media &amp; Communications Department</a></strong></span></li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\"><strong><a href=\"http://owwr.org/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">OWWR: Old Westbury Web Radio</a></strong></span></li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\"><strong><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/user/OldWestburyTV\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">MIC/OWTV: Media Innovation Center/Old Westbury Television</a></strong></span></li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\"><strong><a href=\"http://www.oldwestburycatalyst.org/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">The Old Westbury Catalyst</a></strong></span></li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\"><strong><a href=\"http://www.collaborativemediacenter.org/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">The Collaborative Media Center</a></strong></span></li>\n</ul>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">Don&#8217;t forget to share what you like using <a href=\"https://www.google.com/search?q=%23owmac&amp;oq=%23owmac&amp;aqs=chrome..69i57j69i60j69i61j0j5.8149j1j7&amp;sourceid=chrome&amp;ie=UTF-8\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><strong>#OWMAC</strong></a> &#8211; Support Student Creativity!</span></p>\n', NULL, 'APPROVED', 'TC527', NULL, '2022-05-04 11:14:42', 0, 'Celebrate Student Media at Old Westbury! – Digital Arts – Documentary – Journalism – Radio – TV – Video – New Media – Podcasts –\n', NULL, NULL, 1),
('ed581705-61ed-11f1-98fa-60cf847a2597', 'podcast', 'Podcast Blossoms?', 'podcast-blossoms', NULL, '\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://www.oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/NMB-Apple-Blossom-Banner-Web-1024x463.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-7044\"/><figcaption>Students, Trees, and Podcasts Bloom at SUNY Old Westbury.</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-audio\"><audio controls src=\"https://www.oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/NMB-9-WEB-2022-05-05.mp3\"></audio></figure>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">This week on New Media Beat:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><li>Hey Twitter, Edit This!</li><li>Meta Hardware Goes Bricks &amp; Mortar</li><li>Insta&#8217;s Originality Algorithm</li><li>Apple TV+&#8217;s Golden Ticket?</li><li>Has Netflix Hit Bottom?</li></ul>\n\n\n<p>The NMB Podcast streams live on <a href=\"http://www.owwrny.org/\">Old Westbury Web Radio</a> every Thursday from 10:00-11:00 AM EST.  Can&#8217;t listen live? Our podcast will be <a href=\"https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/?cat=17\">posted</a> for your listening pleasure every Friday afternoon.</p>\n<p><!-- /wp:post-content --></p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --></p>\n<p>NMB was produced by Zachary Lasky and Muhammad Shumail.  Our engineer is Niklaus Feil.  Our Script was Written by Muhammad Shumail. Our audio was edited by Muhammad Shumail. This week&#8217;s hosts: Bryan Dupuy and Jake Martin!</p>\n<p><!-- /wp:paragraph --></p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.newmediabeat.org/\"><strong>New Media Beat</strong></a> covers new media news from around the world. NMB is a production of  Media Studies students from the <a href=\"https://www.oldwestbury.edu/\" target=\"_self\" rel=\"noopener\">SUNY College @ Old Westbury.</a>   We scour the web for news about about the world of media, journalism and technology.</p>\n<p><!-- /wp:paragraph --></p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --></p>\n<p>Follow<strong> <a href=\"https://twitter.com/OWWRGMN\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">@OWWRGMN</a></strong> for a curated feed of the latest new media news for aspiring media professionals.</p>\n<p> </p>', NULL, 'APPROVED', 'TC527', NULL, '2022-05-07 08:19:55', 0, '– Editing Twitter – Meta’s Hardware Store – Instagram Originality – Apple TV+’s NFL Gamble – Watching Netflix Tumble – \n', NULL, NULL, 1);
INSERT INTO `content` (`id`, `type`, `title`, `slug`, `description`, `content`, `url`, `approval_status`, `author_id`, `editor_id`, `created_at`, `is_featured`, `excerpt`, `video_url`, `featured_image`, `category_id`) VALUES
('ed586762-61ed-11f1-98fa-60cf847a2597', 'article', 'Review: Flowerfield', 'flowerfield', NULL, '\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" src=\"uploads/q3XBm7YjZVaAwBqF-qLt_C-9C4wHE3xzsMVjAV7UytbDPpojwJwfDRZERJ6YEI0h57tIrFrKTmNHMp3ZPGJeSPRvF6XvPXpKWtVQQPuvf-IJZ9hNrwHVrmUFFzIBbhDS0iJ3BHTvtE9HhX4_cA.jpg\" alt=\'\' width=\"498\" height=\"374\"/><figcaption>Photo Credit: Joanna Vissichelli</figcaption></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\"></p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Recently, I attended a wedding at the Flowerfield venue, located in St. James, NY.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Despite rain dripping down the window of the shuttle, the features of the Flowerfield grounds caught the guests’ attention. At the entrance, a large fountain that graciously sprayed water.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">A long canopy decorated in lights led us into a cozy waiting area. Scenic and floral photos hung on the wall.A&nbsp; sign said: “Welcome to our forever.”</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Flowerfield certainly embodies its floral name. Entering the Atrium for the ceremony, I immediately was surrounded by greenery which was illuminated with small lights, and lanterns hung from the ceiling. Inside, the vast space and natural light shining through the windows created the feeling of an outdoor setting.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">A bridge for the bride to walk across spanned over a big koi pond filled with large orange and white fish. During cocktail hour, guests enjoyed their food on tables and couches that surrounded the pond.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">When the ceremony and cocktail hour concluded, the reception kicked off and all of the guests made their way to the Grand Ballroom. Blue lights filled the room and rows of drapery hung from the ceiling. Tables surrounded both sides of the dance floor, which guests would later spend much time on.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">From my experience, the Flowerfield venue provided beautiful scenery for its guests. The expansive bridge and koi pond created a focal point in the room that brought a touch of the outdoors inside the main room.For more information about the venue, you can visit the <em>Flowerfield</em> website at <a href=\"https://www.flowerfield.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">https://www.flowerfield.com</a>.</p>\n', NULL, 'APPROVED', 'JV368', NULL, '2022-05-10 10:22:38', 0, 'Recently, I attended a wedding at the Flowerfield venue, located in St. James, NY. Despite rain dripping down the window of the shuttle, the features of the Flowerfield grounds caught the guests’ attention. At the entrance, a large fountain that graciously sprayed water. A long canopy decorated in lights led us into a cozy waiting…\n', NULL, NULL, 6),
('ed58be74-61ed-11f1-98fa-60cf847a2597', 'podcast', 'Your Pavement Pounding Podcast!', 'your-pavement-pounding-podcast', NULL, '\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"uploads/NMB-Pavement-Square-Small-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4774\"/></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-audio\"><audio controls src=\"uploads/NMB-10-Web-2022-05-12.mp3\"></audio><figcaption><sup>This Week on New Media Beat:</sup></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><li>Online Privacy Policy: Who Makes the Rules?</li><li>Netflix Struggles: Too Much Competition?</li><li>Crash! Artificial Intelligence at the Wheel?</li><li>Pinterest Streaming Live with TV Studio App?</li><li>Social Backlash: SCOTUS Leak Sets Off a Social Media Storm!</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"alignleft size-large is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" src=\"uploads/NMB-Crosswalk-Small-Vertical-e1652465535958-140x300.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-7075\" width=\"166\" height=\"356\" srcset=\"https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/NMB-Crosswalk-Small-Vertical-e1652465535958-140x300.jpg 140w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/NMB-Crosswalk-Small-Vertical-e1652465535958-280x600.jpg 280w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/NMB-Crosswalk-Small-Vertical-e1652465535958-559x1200.jpg 559w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/NMB-Crosswalk-Small-Vertical-e1652465535958.jpg 633w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 166px) 100vw, 166px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n<p>This is our last podcast of the season.  Our fall season will be about the world of media.  New Media Beat: Global Edition. See you in September!</p>\n<p><!-- /wp:post-content --></p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --></p>\n<p>NMB is produced by Zachary Lasky and Muhammad Shumail.  Our engineer is Niklaus Feil.  Our audio was edited by Muhammad Shumail. This week&#8217;s hosts: Jalani Gadsden and Victoria Van Grembergen!</p>\n<p><!-- /wp:paragraph --></p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.newmediabeat.org/\"><strong>New Media Beat</strong></a> covers new media news from around the world. NMB is a production of  Media Studies students from the <a href=\"https://www.oldwestbury.edu/\" target=\"_self\" rel=\"noopener\">SUNY College @ Old Westbury.</a>   We scour the web for news about about the world of media, journalism and technology.</p>\n<p><!-- /wp:paragraph --></p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --></p>\n<p>Follow<strong> <a href=\"https://twitter.com/OWWRGMN\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">@OWWRGMN</a></strong> for a curated feed of the latest new media news for aspiring media professionals.</p>\n<p><!-- wp:image {\"id\":4774,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} --></p>\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\">\n<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p><!-- /wp:image --></p>', NULL, 'APPROVED', 'TC527', NULL, '2022-05-13 14:16:49', 0, '– Online Privacy Policy – Netflix on the Ropes? – Crash! Artificial Intelligence Behind the Wheel –  Pinterest’s TV Studio App – SCOTUS Scolded on Social –\n', NULL, NULL, 1),
('ed590d84-61ed-11f1-98fa-60cf847a2597', 'article', 'The New York Blood Center Visits SUNY Old Westbury', 'the-new-york-blood-center-visits-suny-old-westbury', NULL, '\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" src=\"uploads/image-50-1200x900.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-7096\" width=\"688\" height=\"516\" srcset=\"https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/09/image-50-1200x900.png 1200w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/09/image-50-600x450.png 600w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/09/image-50-768x576.png 768w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/09/image-50-1536x1152.png 1536w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/09/image-50-300x225.png 300w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/09/image-50.png 1600w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 688px) 100vw, 688px\" /><figcaption>Photo Credit: Joanna Vissichelli </figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">From September 7 to September 8, the New York Blood Center joined the SUNY Old Westbury community for a Blood Drive. </p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Students and faculty lined up to donate blood in the Campus Center Atrium. Informational posters and New York Blood Center Signs listing blood-related facts, eligibility criteria, and personal stories decorated the Atrium. The signs also expressed the emergency blood shortage occurring.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">The New York Blood Center Account Manager, Sharon Silva, hopes that students will become lifelong donors. Silva explained, “one out of every three people will need a blood product in their lifetime.” Silva said that she donates blood every 56 days because she has good health and recognizes the need for blood.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Student Health Services set up a booth in the Atrium with blood donation information and donor appreciation giveaways, including bags. SUNY Old Westbury Registered Nurse, Adele Gutierrez, helped at the booth. She said blood has no substitution.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">On the first day of the Blood Drive, 57 SUNY Old Westbury community members met the eligibility requirements and donated blood. Gutierrez felt touched by the support the Blood Drive received. “Doing something [as] selfless as volunteering is an indirect way to change somebody’s life outside of college,” she said.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Gutierrez continued, “when you get that text message that your blood was just used for ‘so and so’ at ‘this’ hospital, I think that is really the most rewarding feeling.”<br>If you are interested in donating in the future, the Blood Drive occurs on campus twice each semester. For more information on ways to contribute or donate blood, visit <a href=\"https://nam12.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.nybloodcenter.org%2F&amp;data=05%7C01%7Cjbecchin%40oldwestbury.edu%7C418d2c1b20ec4b215bd208da945bf1ed%7Cf5089034f2334f12a71638b7f4904370%7C0%7C0%7C637985419873918450%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&amp;sdata=%2F6rvxVzag1BRUPJ2RDDECaZvB0zfA%2BWGp9%2BwK3GAvvA%3D&amp;reserved=0\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">www.nybloodcenter.org</a> or call 1-800-933-BLOOD.</p>\n', NULL, 'APPROVED', 'JV368', NULL, '2022-09-11 21:17:54', 0, 'From September 7 to September 8, the New York Blood Center joined the SUNY Old Westbury community for a Blood Drive.  Students and faculty lined up to donate blood in the Campus Center Atrium. Informational posters and New York Blood Center Signs listing blood-related facts, eligibility criteria, and personal stories decorated the Atrium. The signs…\n', NULL, NULL, 1),
('ed595fe9-61ed-11f1-98fa-60cf847a2597', 'article', 'SUNY Old Westbury Honors 9/11 Victims', 'suny-old-westbury-honors-9-11-victims', NULL, '\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1200\" height=\"900\" src=\"uploads/image-51-1200x900.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-7099\" srcset=\"https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/09/image-51-1200x900.png 1200w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/09/image-51-600x450.png 600w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/09/image-51-768x576.png 768w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/09/image-51-1536x1152.png 1536w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/09/image-51-300x225.png 300w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/09/image-51.png 1600w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" /><figcaption>Photo Credit: Joanna Vissichelli </figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">When walking around campus, you’ve probably noticed flags hanging around the inside of the Campus Center Atrium and New Academic Building. These flags represent the United States of America and say the words “NEVER FORGET.” They list the names of those who lost their lives at the September 11, 2001 terrorist attacks twenty-one years ago, and emergency personnel and first responders who died during the attacks.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Among these names include SUNY Old Westbury alumni: <a href=\"https://nam12.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnn.com%2FSPECIALS%2F2001%2Fmemorial%2Fpeople%2F3566.html&amp;data=05%7C01%7Cjbecchin%40oldwestbury.edu%7C52e7378daca84c12fb6b08da945bff22%7Cf5089034f2334f12a71638b7f4904370%7C0%7C0%7C637985420085170433%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&amp;sdata=NQOJJjHeZag5YNVxp8Do3vvTgBZUgBL8DQ8VMY9OgEQ%3D&amp;reserved=0\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">James J. Carson</a> of Baldwin, New York (Class of 1993); <a href=\"https://nam12.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnn.com%2FSPECIALS%2F2001%2Fmemorial%2Fpeople%2F1859.html&amp;data=05%7C01%7Cjbecchin%40oldwestbury.edu%7C52e7378daca84c12fb6b08da945bff22%7Cf5089034f2334f12a71638b7f4904370%7C0%7C0%7C637985420085170433%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&amp;sdata=9o%2FsrsGSGaeIY5DFeHeVUt5z9HH4sZkKAlVFzKktThs%3D&amp;reserved=0\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Dennis Michael Edwards</a> of Huntington, New York (Class of 1988); <a href=\"https://nam12.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnn.com%2FSPECIALS%2F2001%2Fmemorial%2Fpeople%2F4362.html&amp;data=05%7C01%7Cjbecchin%40oldwestbury.edu%7C52e7378daca84c12fb6b08da945bff22%7Cf5089034f2334f12a71638b7f4904370%7C0%7C0%7C637985420085170433%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&amp;sdata=3SZ4UsV4BHkGoYOP7yusZz5%2F6N%2BdB%2FfjXAE2KesOjrU%3D&amp;reserved=0\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Wade Brian Green</a> of Westbury, New York (Class of 1984); <a href=\"https://nam12.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnn.com%2FSPECIALS%2F2001%2Fmemorial%2Fpeople%2F1883.html&amp;data=05%7C01%7Cjbecchin%40oldwestbury.edu%7C52e7378daca84c12fb6b08da945bff22%7Cf5089034f2334f12a71638b7f4904370%7C0%7C0%7C637985420085170433%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&amp;sdata=QffTNmCFBMUGfFQ%2B9TCQU%2BTnaWHpcbCdDpSUCyczqPk%3D&amp;reserved=0\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Joseph Maloney</a> of Farmingville, New York (Class of 1980); and <a href=\"https://nam12.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnn.com%2FSPECIALS%2F2001%2Fmemorial%2Fpeople%2F3377.html&amp;data=05%7C01%7Cjbecchin%40oldwestbury.edu%7C52e7378daca84c12fb6b08da945bff22%7Cf5089034f2334f12a71638b7f4904370%7C0%7C0%7C637985420085170433%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&amp;sdata=UF5OIKAAfO%2BdCLrtjpS9%2FJAgz33VYDUngUO0be5jfz0%3D&amp;reserved=0\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Anthony Perez</a> of Locust Valley, New York (Class of 2000).</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Michael Kinane, SUNY Old Westbury’s Vice President of Communications &amp; College Relations, said, “In addition to their names on the banners, these men are remembered with a monument and two trees planted outside the Student Union Rotunda.”</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\"><a href=\"https://nam12.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.history.com%2Ftopics%2F21st-century%2F9-11-attacks&amp;data=05%7C01%7Cjbecchin%40oldwestbury.edu%7C52e7378daca84c12fb6b08da945bff22%7Cf5089034f2334f12a71638b7f4904370%7C0%7C0%7C637985420085170433%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&amp;sdata=ihU3ewA18xsIcOTs67v5U8oOcftRZJ%2BrBGhFC3hV5vE%3D&amp;reserved=0\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">On September 11, 2001</a>, two planes crashed into the Twin Towers, leading to their collapse and the loss of many lives. Another plane crashed into a portion of the Pentagon in Washington D.C.. Passengers on United Flight 93 learned of the previous events while in the air, and the passengers fought against the hijackers, and the planes eventually crashed into a field in Western Pennsylvania. The final destination of this hijacked flight remained unclear but was on its way to Washington D.C..&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">2,996 people, including the five SUNY Old Westbury alumni, perished in these attacks led by Osama bin Laden, an Al Qaeda leader.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">The flags honor the SUNY Old Westbury alumni who perished and the events that took place. Although the attacks occurred twenty-one years ago, they continue to impact us today. Kinane said that the flags “remind people of these historic, life-changing events by connecting those events to the past, present and future.”</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\"><br>Kinane continued, “The campus&#8217; 9/11 memorials are meant to mark an important point in history while spurring introspection among those who see them about impacts, both immediate and over time, that the historical event has made on our lives and our society.”</p>\n', NULL, 'APPROVED', 'JV368', NULL, '2022-09-11 21:19:54', 0, 'When walking around campus, you’ve probably noticed flags hanging around the inside of the Campus Center Atrium and New Academic Building. These flags represent the United States of America and say the words “NEVER FORGET.” They list the names of those who lost their lives at the September 11, 2001 terrorist attacks twenty-one years ago,…\n', NULL, NULL, 1),
('ed59b510-61ed-11f1-98fa-60cf847a2597', 'article', 'Update on Hurricane Fiona', 'update-on-hurricane-fiona', NULL, '<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter size-large is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" src=\"uploads/image-53-1200x799.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-7110\" width=\"667\" height=\"444\" srcset=\"https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/09/image-53-1200x799.png 1200w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/09/image-53-600x400.png 600w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/09/image-53-768x511.png 768w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/09/image-53-1536x1023.png 1536w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/09/image-53-2048x1364.png 2048w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/09/image-53-300x200.png 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 667px) 100vw, 667px\" /><figcaption>Photo Credit: nbcnews.com</figcaption></figure>\n</div>\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">On September 23rd, Hurricane Fiona was strengthening as it headed towards Canada&#8217;s Atlantic Coast. Five days earlier, the category four hurricane, made landfall on the island of Puerto Rico. According to the U.S. National Hurricane Center, Fiona hit about 15 miles (25 kilometers) south-southeast of Mayaguez with maximum sustained winds of 85 mph (140 kph).</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">An article from the&nbsp;<em>Washington Post</em>&nbsp;stated that as of midmorning Wednesday, Fiona had moved to the southwest of Bermuda, leaving the British overseas territory with a tropical storm warning and a hurricane watch.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">On September 20, Bill Karins, an NBC News Climate &amp; Weather Unit Certified Broadcast Meteorologist, tweeted, &#8220;The Euro Model is in with a record-breaking (if it happens) 935mb Fiona superstorm into eastern Nova Scotia and Western Newfoundland Saturday morning. With this intensity and the strong high to its NE, the waves in the North Atlantic will be mountains! &#8220;</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">According to the White House, Biden emphasized his administration&#8217;s support for Puerto Rico&#8217;s emergency and recovery efforts in the wake of Fiona while speaking on the phone with Pierluisi from Air Force One.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">A report on the NBC News website claims that &#8220;nearly 1.5 million utility customers were left without power, and 196,000 people were without potable water.&#8221; Additionally, &#8220;Officials counted 1,033 evacuees in 130 storm shelters set up for Fiona. And about 1 in 5 cellphone towers were inoperable. &#8220;</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">The island of Puerto Rico, a territory of the United States since 1898, has been the epicenter of dozens of hurricanes that have caused catastrophic damage to the island and its people. BCSSW News reported that over 200,000 people left Puerto Rico after Hurricane Maria in 2017.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">People can get in touch with a variety of non-profit organizations to help Puerto Rico at this difficult time. Among them are Save the Children Federation, Inc., TPMG Corporation, and Friends of Hope International.</p>\n', NULL, 'APPROVED', 'LG167', NULL, '2022-09-23 13:41:55', 0, 'On September 23rd, Hurricane Fiona was strengthening as it headed towards Canada’s Atlantic Coast. Five days earlier, the category four hurricane, made landfall on the island of Puerto Rico. According to the U.S. National Hurricane Center, Fiona hit about 15 miles (25 kilometers) south-southeast of Mayaguez with maximum sustained winds of 85 mph (140 kph). An article from the Washington…\n', NULL, NULL, 1),
('ed59fb82-61ed-11f1-98fa-60cf847a2597', 'article', 'Panther Pride Homecoming Returns!', 'panther-pride-homecoming-returns', NULL, '<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" src=\"uploads/image-54.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-7115\" width=\"462\" height=\"357\" srcset=\"https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/09/image-54.png 976w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/09/image-54-600x464.png 600w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/09/image-54-768x594.png 768w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/09/image-54-300x232.png 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 462px) 100vw, 462px\" /><figcaption>Photo Credit: OldWestbury.edu</figcaption></figure>\n</div>\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">From September 28 to October 1, Panther Pride Homecoming will return to SUNY Old Westbury!</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Panther Pride Homecoming celebrates school pride. It brings the SUNY Old Westbury community together including students, faculty, staff, and even alumni through a series of events.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">The annual event last took place in Fall of 2019 due to the COVID-19 pandemic. Danielle Collins Groner, the Director of Communications and Signature Events at SUNY Old Westbury, said, “We&#8217;re thrilled to host Panther Pride Homecoming again. There are beloved traditions from the Kickoff Luncheon to the Family Day Carnival that we&#8217;re happy to have our current students have the opportunity to experience.”</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">President Sams will kick-off Panther Pride Homecoming on Wednesday, September 28 with opening remarks, as students and staff enjoy lunch in the Campus Center Atrium. On Thursday, September 29, students can “Stay Up @ The Union,” to celebrate Panther Pride!&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">The crowning of the Panther Pride Royal Court will take place at the Fraternity and Sorority Expo on September 30. The community will celebrate the Royal Court the following day, at the PantherFest Family Day &amp; Carnival, and enjoy a day of fun! Collins Groner said that students, faculty, staff, and alumni can expect “several rides, inflatables, carnival games, and carnival food.” SUNY Old Westbury invites the whole campus community to this event, including families. While not required, attendees may bring non-perishable donations for the Panther Food Pantry.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Other events throughout Homecoming include the Cake Off Competition, “Sip” and Paint, and Field Day. Students, faculty, staff, and alumni can visit <a href=\"https://nam12.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.oldwestbury.edu%2Fpantherpride&amp;data=05%7C01%7Cjbecchin%40oldwestbury.edu%7C2da8681079814939f2c608da9d81c92c%7Cf5089034f2334f12a71638b7f4904370%7C0%7C0%7C637995477989755167%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&amp;sdata=W%2BAKlshSGiRS8YeUvPHKTIW3LHYwml6Bdxv7w%2FQaNN4%3D&amp;reserved=0\">OldWestbury.edu/PantherPride</a> for a full schedule of events.<br>If alumni would like to register for Panther Pride Homecoming, they can check their emails for registration information. According to the <a href=\"https://nam12.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.oldwestbury.edu%2Fdivision%2Finstitutional-advancement%2Foffice-alumni-affairs%2Fhomecoming&amp;data=05%7C01%7Cjbecchin%40oldwestbury.edu%7C2da8681079814939f2c608da9d81c92c%7Cf5089034f2334f12a71638b7f4904370%7C0%7C0%7C637995477989755167%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&amp;sdata=Hw5hel6DUKPA5FcHuYz7K1Vu1t21rWLArWplyCWHNQ8%3D&amp;reserved=0\">Old Westbury Website</a>, due to the financial challenges associated with the COVID-19 pandemic, “the College this year is suspending most fees that might have previously been charged to alumni for PantherFest Alumni Family Day. A fee will apply for the offsite Homecoming Alumni Reception.”</p>\n', NULL, 'APPROVED', 'JV368', NULL, '2022-09-23 13:44:43', 0, 'From September 28 to October 1, Panther Pride Homecoming will return to SUNY Old Westbury! Panther Pride Homecoming celebrates school pride. It brings the SUNY Old Westbury community together including students, faculty, staff, and even alumni through a series of events. The annual event last took place in Fall of 2019 due to the COVID-19…\n', NULL, NULL, 1),
('ed5a54b1-61ed-11f1-98fa-60cf847a2597', 'article', '“Sad Songs In A Hotel Room”', 'sad-songs-in-a-hotel-room', NULL, '<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter size-large is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" src=\"uploads/image-57-1200x1200.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-7131\" width=\"466\" height=\"466\" srcset=\"https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/09/image-57-1200x1200.png 1200w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/09/image-57-600x600.png 600w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/09/image-57-70x70.png 70w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/09/image-57-768x768.png 768w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/09/image-57-1536x1536.png 1536w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/09/image-57-300x300.png 300w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/09/image-57.png 1600w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 466px) 100vw, 466px\" /><figcaption>Photo Credit: <a href=\"https://nam12.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fjoshuatbassett%2Fstatus%2F1567197172290002944%2Fphoto%2F1&amp;data=05%7C01%7Cjbecchin%40oldwestbury.edu%7C24e3626ebc9f42d0e3ed08da9f0df90d%7Cf5089034f2334f12a71638b7f4904370%7C0%7C0%7C637997179595668252%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&amp;sdata=FOpFYuCFtV2Qkhe6Mty%2BAAqyXHPvk%2FGR3Txk%2FLvcLu8%3D&amp;reserved=0\">Twitter.com (@joshuatbassett)</a></figcaption></figure>\n</div>\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Joshua Bassett’s EP, “Sad Songs In A Hotel Room,” came out at midnight on September 23 and it certainly deserves recognition!</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">“Sad Songs In A Hotel Room,” Bassett’s third EP and the title of the lead-off track, consists of six songs and highlights somber experiences.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">The fourth song on the EP, “Smoke Slow,” first debuted as a single in August. The instrumentals, including the guitar, maintain a catchy beat and rhythm. Bassett explores his creativity through his lyrics. In the first verse of the song, Bassett sings, “We&#8217;re buying more time/While we kill ourselves as we both inhale.”&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">“Smoke Slow” has one of the faster beats of the EP. The lyrics, “Addicted to illusions of a love that never was/And never will be anyway,” keeps an upbeat pace for the song. The artistic choices in “Smoke Slow” also aid in its success. When Bassett sings, “Play with fire, take me higher,” his voice progressively gets higher, showing off his talented vocal range.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Bassett also dropped a<a href=\"https://nam12.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fyoutu.be%2FmWmytXXm32o&amp;data=05%7C01%7Cjbecchin%40oldwestbury.edu%7C24e3626ebc9f42d0e3ed08da9f0df90d%7Cf5089034f2334f12a71638b7f4904370%7C0%7C0%7C637997179595668252%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&amp;sdata=Qvlywxf3oJHgpvJXbW6hX4MqLgOO1ZTzfuNbvJeJ0Ss%3D&amp;reserved=0\"> music video</a> for the fifth song on the EP, “Lifeline,” at midnight. The song and video display raw emotion. In the black-and-white music video, Bassett simply looks at the camera and sings. Its simplicity speaks volumes. Towards the end of the video, Bassett begins to cry as he sings despairing, yet heartfelt lyrics. He battles his fears of death in the song, singing, “Save me, now I&#8217;m facing/All my fears of the unknown/I&#8217;ve been shakin&#8217; in my bones.”</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\"><a href=\"https://nam12.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hitc.com%2Fen-gb%2F2022%2F09%2F23%2Fjoshua-bassett-gives-everyone-a-lifeline-by-donating-100-of-song-earnings%2F&amp;data=05%7C01%7Cjbecchin%40oldwestbury.edu%7C24e3626ebc9f42d0e3ed08da9f0df90d%7Cf5089034f2334f12a71638b7f4904370%7C0%7C0%7C637997179595668252%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&amp;sdata=rOq6KtznakkMY%2Boz0IrTZ%2Bt7uRF0U%2B0XG06%2FzmRiy%2Bo%3D&amp;reserved=0\">HITC</a> reported that “Lifeline” surrounds Bassett’s hospitalization in 2021 from septic shock and heart failure. He said that throughout this medical crisis, his mother remained his “lifeline.” Bassett<a href=\"https://nam12.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fjoshuatbassett%2Fstatus%2F1573186370935607296%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Egoogle%257Ctwcamp%255Eserp%257Ctwgr%255Etweet&amp;data=05%7C01%7Cjbecchin%40oldwestbury.edu%7C24e3626ebc9f42d0e3ed08da9f0df90d%7Cf5089034f2334f12a71638b7f4904370%7C0%7C0%7C637997179595668252%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&amp;sdata=pBLjj8oa4m0ilhDkgBwKTD6MjEa%2FmtjXaZc2PpQqLJc%3D&amp;reserved=0\"> tweeted</a>, “Fun fact the voice in the intro is indeed my mother. i love you to the moon and back forever.<a href=\"https://nam12.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fhashtag%2FLifeline%3Fsrc%3Dhashtag_click&amp;data=05%7C01%7Cjbecchin%40oldwestbury.edu%7C24e3626ebc9f42d0e3ed08da9f0df90d%7Cf5089034f2334f12a71638b7f4904370%7C0%7C0%7C637997179595668252%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&amp;sdata=ZMGeQmmRyRVpuISZQwKJRLOYys8s8zAtuWnbOU6QcL8%3D&amp;reserved=0\"> #Lifeline</a>.”&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\"><a href=\"https://nam12.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hitc.com%2Fen-gb%2F2022%2F09%2F23%2Fjoshua-bassett-gives-everyone-a-lifeline-by-donating-100-of-song-earnings%2F&amp;data=05%7C01%7Cjbecchin%40oldwestbury.edu%7C24e3626ebc9f42d0e3ed08da9f0df90d%7Cf5089034f2334f12a71638b7f4904370%7C0%7C0%7C637997179595668252%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&amp;sdata=rOq6KtznakkMY%2Boz0IrTZ%2Bt7uRF0U%2B0XG06%2FzmRiy%2Bo%3D&amp;reserved=0\">HITC</a> also said, “All earnings from Lifeline will go towards [organizations] and charities that are a ‘lifeline’ for people in need, according to [a] statement.” “Used To It,” the third song on the EP, also references Bassett’s near-death experience. He sang, “I&#8217;m not surprised you didn&#8217;t call/When I almost died, you didn&#8217;t care at all.”</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">I would definitely recommend Bassett’s EP, “Sad Songs In A Hotel Room,” particularly if you like calm music. Even if you don’t listen to “sad songs,” the mellow instrumentals invite the audience to simply listen and relax. Bassett’s emotional lyrics about his personal experiences can touch people who have and haven’t encountered similar situations. Bassett demonstrates his vocal range, musical talent, and lyrical talent throughout the EP.</p>\n', NULL, 'APPROVED', 'JV368', NULL, '2022-09-26 16:35:03', 0, 'Joshua Bassett’s EP, “Sad Songs In A Hotel Room,” came out at midnight on September 23 and it certainly deserves recognition! “Sad Songs In A Hotel Room,” Bassett’s third EP and the title of the lead-off track, consists of six songs and highlights somber experiences.  The fourth song on the EP, “Smoke Slow,” first debuted…\n', NULL, NULL, 6),
('ed5aa689-61ed-11f1-98fa-60cf847a2597', 'podcast', 'New Media Beat Podcast!', 'new-media-beat-podcast', NULL, '\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://www.oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/Fire-Banner-1024x458.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-7145\"/><figcaption>We are the fire-walkers of <em><a href=\"https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/\">New Media Beat!</a></em></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-audio aligncenter\"><audio controls src=\"https://www.oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/NMB-1-Podcast-2022-09-29.mp3\"></audio></figure>\n\n\n<p><strong>This Week on New Media Beat:</strong></p>\n<p><!-- /wp:post-content --></p>\n<p><!-- wp:list --></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Japanese Reality TV: When Is a Toddler &#8216;Old Enough&#8217; for their &#8216;First Errand&#8217;?</li>\n<li>Iranian Social: Protesting the Death of Mahsa Amini</li>\n<li>Hollywood in China: Will There Be a Happy Ending?</li>\n<li>Serbian Social: LGBTQ+ EuroPride or Hate Speech?</li>\n<li>India&#8217;s Internet Rules: Legitimate Governance or Restricted Freedom?</li>\n<li>Russia: Censorship &amp; War in Ukraine.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><!-- /wp:list --></p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --></p>\n<p><!-- /wp:paragraph --></p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.newmediabeat.org/\"><strong>New Media Beat</strong></a> covers media news from around the world. NMB is a production of  Media Studies students from the <a href=\"https://www.oldwestbury.edu/\" target=\"_self\" rel=\"noopener\">SUNY College @ Old Westbury.</a>   We scour the web for news about about the world of media, journalism and technology.</p>\n<p><!-- /wp:paragraph --></p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --></p>\n<p>Follow<strong> <a href=\"https://twitter.com/OWWRGMN\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">@OWWRGMN</a></strong> for a curated feed of the latest new media news for aspiring media professionals.</p>\n<p><!-- /wp:paragraph --></p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --></p>\n<p>The NMB Podcast streams live on <a href=\"http://www.owwrny.org/\">Old Westbury Web Radio</a> every Thursday from 10:00-11:00 AM EST.  Can&#8217;t listen live? Our podcast will be <a href=\"https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/?cat=17\">posted</a> for your listening pleasure every Friday afternoon</p>\n<p><!-- /wp:paragraph --></p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --></p>\n<p><!-- /wp:paragraph --></p>\n<p><!-- wp:post-featured-image /--></p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --></p>\n<p><!-- /wp:paragraph --></p>', NULL, 'APPROVED', 'TC527', NULL, '2022-09-30 14:54:15', 0, 'This Week on New Media Beat: Japanese Reality TV: When Is a Toddler ‘Old Enough’ for their ‘First Errand’? Iranian Social: Protesting the Death of Mahsa Amini Hollywood in China: Will There Be a Happy Ending? Serbian Social: LGBTQ+ EuroPride or Hate Speech? India’s Internet Rules: Legitimate Governance or Restricted Freedom? Russia: Censorship & War…\n', NULL, NULL, 1),
('ed5afdb3-61ed-11f1-98fa-60cf847a2597', 'article', 'The History of Halloween', 'the-history-of-halloween', NULL, '<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter size-large is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" src=\"uploads/image-59-1200x954.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-7162\" width=\"511\" height=\"405\" srcset=\"https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/image-59-1200x954.png 1200w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/image-59-600x477.png 600w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/image-59-1536x1221.png 1536w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/image-59-300x239.png 300w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/image-59.png 1600w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 511px) 100vw, 511px\" /><figcaption>Photo Credit: history.com</figcaption></figure>\n</div>\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Halloween is one of the oldest holidays celebrated on October 31st every year in the U.S. On that day, people dress up in costumes and attend parties. Also, people trick-or-treat with children.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Today, some Christians believe that Halloween shouldn’t be celebrated, arguing that this festivity is a pagan holiday during which the devil is worshiped, and evil is glorified. Other Christians disagree, claiming that Halloween is a fun, safe occasion for kids to dress up, get tons of candy, and have a good time.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\"><strong>But what’s the History of Halloween?</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Halloween has its roots in the ancient Celtic Irish Festival of Samhain, marking the end of the harvest season and the beginning of winter. At Samhain, it was believed that the barrier separating this world and the otherworld was most permeable, allowing spirits to pass through.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">People wore costumes and masks to protect themselves and be differentiated from evil spirits. Their intention was to remain anonymous in a frightening manner that suggested concepts like ghosts, witches, pumpkins, black cats, and the moon.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">The festival included a lot of food and bonfires. Households’ fires were put out and then restarted from the bonfire, using the bones of the murdered animals as fuel.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Food was prepared for both the living and the dead, and it was ritually shared with the less fortunate. Traditional food for Halloween was seasonal food such as potatoes, pumpkin, kale, cabbage, leeks, and raw onions.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">When Irish immigrants arrived in the U.S. around 1800, they brought their tradition of Samhain with them, which later became Halloween.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">On Halloween, Irish immigrants would dress up, play practical jokes on their neighbors, and ask for food and cash. Eventually, trick-or-treating, as we now know it, originated when Americans adopted the practice.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\"><strong>How has the way people celebrated Halloween changed in modern times?</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Halloween has evolved over time, due to technology, the expansion of cities, the pandemic, and attitude towards enjoying holidays as a community.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">This holiday used to be a time in which people connected with nature, socialized with other communities, did practical pranks, prepared their own treats, and fabricated their own costumes.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">In present times, due to safety concerns, people have stopped making their own candies, costumes, and practical pranks. People prefer to buy candies and costumes while staying at home, filming, and taking pictures of what they do on the night of Halloween to post them later on social media. As a result, people have lost their connection with nature and they have diminished the celebration of Halloween to almost nothing. Some people are forgetting about the spirit of Halloween.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\"><strong>What do some students at Old Westbury College think about the celebration of Halloween?</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">This are some student’s opinions about Halloween:<strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Jonathan: “I think Halloween is just a good time for people to hang out and have fun despite being pagan.”</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Nancy: “Halloween is a holiday for young ones, family and friends to get together whether that’s parties/get together or merely by going trick or treating.”</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Nick: “Today, Halloween is a business-driven holiday. It is a waste of time to celebrate it.”</p>\n', NULL, 'APPROVED', 'LG167', NULL, '2022-10-02 20:41:21', 0, 'Halloween is one of the oldest holidays celebrated on October 31st every year in the U.S. On that day, people dress up in costumes and attend parties. Also, people trick-or-treat with children. Today, some Christians believe that Halloween shouldn’t be celebrated, arguing that this festivity is a pagan holiday during which the devil is worshiped,…\n', NULL, NULL, 6),
('ed5b4ead-61ed-11f1-98fa-60cf847a2597', 'article', 'FIFA World Cup Qatar 2022', 'fifa-world-cup-qatar-2022', NULL, '\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1200\" height=\"675\" src=\"uploads/image-60-1200x675.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-7165\" srcset=\"https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/image-60-1200x675.png 1200w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/image-60-600x338.png 600w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/image-60-768x432.png 768w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/image-60-300x169.png 300w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/image-60.png 1280w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" /><figcaption>Photo Credit: mlssoccer.com</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Here you will find all the information you need about the World Cup Qatar 2022 so you don’t miss out on this amazing event!</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\"><strong>What is the World Cup?</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">The FIFA World Cup, simply known as the World Cup, is the most prestigious sport competition held every four years with soccer teams competing to determine soccer’s world champion. The World Cup is the most significant and widely followed sporting event that attracts billions of television viewers along with the millions of people who attend the tournament.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\"><strong>How did the World Cup start?</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Before the 1930s, soccer was part of the Olympics. But in the 1930s, soccer stopped being part of the Olympics to have its own tournament. Then, Jules Rimet, the president of FIFA, participated in organizing the first World Cup. There have been 21 World cups in total since 1930.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\"><strong>Why does the World Cup happen every four years?</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">The competition is held every four years so that each continent can hold its own tournaments to choose the teams that will compete in the World Cup from each continent. For the first time in World Cup history, in 2018, all 211 member countries participated in the qualification process for the tournament.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\"><strong>When and where will the World Cup take place in 2022?</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">This year, the World Cup will begin on Sunday, November 20 and will end on Sunday, December 18 in Qatar, the smallest country in the world.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\"><strong>What are the tournament&#8217;s groups or teams?</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">An article by&nbsp;<em>Road Trip&nbsp;</em>states that “Prior to the tournament, a draw is used to split the 32 teams into eight groups, consisting of four teams each. The four teams in each group will play each other once, with the winner and runner-up advancing to the next stage: the knockout stage, also referred to as the round of 16.&nbsp;There will be a total of 64 matches in the 2022 World Cup.”</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">The groups are:&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-table\"><table><tbody><tr><td><strong>Group&nbsp;</strong><strong>A</strong></td><td><strong>Group&nbsp;</strong><strong>B</strong></td><td><strong>Group&nbsp;</strong><strong>C</strong></td><td><strong>Group D</strong></td><td><strong>Group E</strong></td><td><strong>Group F</strong></td><td><strong>Group G</strong></td><td><strong>Group H</strong></td></tr><tr><td>Qatar</td><td>England</td><td>Argentina</td><td>France</td><td>Spain</td><td>Belgium</td><td>Brazil</td><td>Portugal</td></tr><tr><td>Ecuador</td><td>IR Iran</td><td>Saudi Arabia</td><td>Denmark</td><td>Germany</td><td>Canada</td><td>Serbia</td><td>Ghana</td></tr><tr><td>Senegal</td><td>USA</td><td>Mexico</td><td>Tunisia</td><td>Japan</td><td>Morocco</td><td>Switzerland</td><td>Uruguay</td></tr><tr><td>Netherlands</td><td>Wales</td><td>Poland</td><td>Australia</td><td>Costa Rica</td><td>Croatia</td><td>Cameroon</td><td>Korea Republic</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\"><strong>What is the cost of attending the World Cup Qatar 2022?&nbsp;</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">The&nbsp;<em>Road Trip</em>&nbsp;website states that it will be costly to fly to Qatar to attend the event. There are a variety of World Cup packages. The prices range between $9,275 USD and $16,850 USD.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\"><strong>What should travelers be aware of before visiting Qatar for the World Cup?</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Tourists from 80 different countries will have a free-visa entrance into the country. Also, visitors will be required to wear clothes that cover the knees and shoulders as a sign of respect for Qatar’s culture.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\"><strong>What stadiums will be available for the Tournament?</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Qatar will have eight new stadiums for the event that will have air conditioning and commodities for people to enjoy the World Cup, according to Nepali Time news.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\"><strong>How much will the winners earn?</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">According to the website&nbsp;<em>Sporting News</em>, “FIFA confirmed in April 2022 that the Qatar World Cup champions will receive a record $42 million in prize money.”&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\"><strong>How to watch and listen to the World Cup?</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">The World Cup will be televised on Fox Sports, FS1, Direct TV Sports, RTVE, Caracol TV, Telemundo, and others. Also, some radio stations also, such as BBC Radio 5 Live and ESPN will transmit the World Cup.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\"><strong>What artists will Perform in the World Cup?</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Qatar has extended an invitation to artists from all over the world to display their abilities during the FIFA World Cup to provide fans with an authentic cultural experience. Possible artists who will perform in the event are Trinidad Cardona, Davido, and Aisha. Other possibilities include&nbsp;Ozuna and Gims, BTS, and Lil Baby.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\"><strong>When is the Panini album for the tournament coming out?</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">The tangible sticker album for the upcoming FIFA World Cup will be available in the United States starting on August 24, 2022. However, the album won&#8217;t be available until September 7 in Latin America, so there will be a slight delay, according to official information from the Panini company. People can purchase the album through Panini’s official website. The album will only cost $2, while the pack of 50 envelope stamps will cost $75. Also, people can buy the album with all the stamps for approximately $1,200.</p>\n', NULL, 'APPROVED', 'LG167', NULL, '2022-10-02 20:46:09', 0, 'Here you will find all the information you need about the World Cup Qatar 2022 so you don’t miss out on this amazing event! What is the World Cup? The FIFA World Cup, simply known as the World Cup, is the most prestigious sport competition held every four years with soccer teams competing to determine…\n', NULL, NULL, 3);
INSERT INTO `content` (`id`, `type`, `title`, `slug`, `description`, `content`, `url`, `approval_status`, `author_id`, `editor_id`, `created_at`, `is_featured`, `excerpt`, `video_url`, `featured_image`, `category_id`) VALUES
('ed5b9a07-61ed-11f1-98fa-60cf847a2597', 'article', 'Mental Health Awareness at SUNY Old Westbury', 'mental-health-awareness-at-suny-old-westbury', NULL, '<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter size-large is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" src=\"uploads/image-64-1200x1200.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-7185\" width=\"456\" height=\"456\" srcset=\"https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/image-64-1200x1200.png 1200w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/image-64-600x600.png 600w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/image-64-70x70.png 70w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/image-64-768x768.png 768w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/image-64-1536x1536.png 1536w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/image-64-300x300.png 300w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/image-64.png 1600w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 456px) 100vw, 456px\" /><figcaption>Photo Credit: Freepik</figcaption></figure>\n</div>\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">On October 10, 2022, people around the world will recognize World Mental Health Day. The <a href=\"https://nam12.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.who.int%2Fcampaigns%2Fworld-mental-health-day&amp;data=05%7C01%7Cjbecchin%40oldwestbury.edu%7C72972df0446f43f4664c08daa7b2cab2%7Cf5089034f2334f12a71638b7f4904370%7C0%7C0%7C638006683582440981%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&amp;sdata=CVY%2FEm2eBsfRtiRYVvy9kNMWRIg2SM%2BHJuSZKPMegG8%3D&amp;reserved=0\">World Health Organization</a> said the day provides a chance to “raise awareness of mental health issues around the world and to mobilize efforts in support of mental health.” </p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">The <a href=\"https://nam12.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.who.int%2Fcampaigns%2Fworld-mental-health-day%2F2022&amp;data=05%7C01%7Cjbecchin%40oldwestbury.edu%7C72972df0446f43f4664c08daa7b2cab2%7Cf5089034f2334f12a71638b7f4904370%7C0%7C0%7C638006683582440981%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&amp;sdata=YleEtrW1r3T1SY8liu61bj7MBG7YEo8lCOnUq00K1Lo%3D&amp;reserved=0\">organization’s</a> theme for this year, “Make mental health &amp; well-being for all a global priority,” reflects a worldwide effort to seek mental health wellness. The COVID-19 pandemic created depression and anxiety around the world. These disorders rose “more than 25% during the first year of the pandemic,” according to estimates.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">As a college student, you may experience mental health issues. The <a href=\"https://nam12.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mayoclinichealthsystem.org%2Fhometown-health%2Fspeaking-of-health%2Fcollege-students-and-depression&amp;data=05%7C01%7Cjbecchin%40oldwestbury.edu%7C72972df0446f43f4664c08daa7b2cab2%7Cf5089034f2334f12a71638b7f4904370%7C0%7C0%7C638006683582440981%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&amp;sdata=AtAbl4lEWaXPpc9RkaL18hPnqn99ans%2BS%2Frn%2FGLBGOo%3D&amp;reserved=0\">Mayo Clinic</a> reported that “a recent study found that 1 in 3 college students experiences significant depression and anxiety.” Some influences include academic and societal pressure, financial hardship, and relationships.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">SUNY Old Westbury provides resources to those struggling with mental health. <a href=\"https://nam12.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.oldwestbury.edu%2Fdivision%2Foffice-student-affairs%2Fcounseling-psychological-wellness-services&amp;data=05%7C01%7Cjbecchin%40oldwestbury.edu%7C72972df0446f43f4664c08daa7b2cab2%7Cf5089034f2334f12a71638b7f4904370%7C0%7C0%7C638006683582597220%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&amp;sdata=YXn%2FTkgk28HSlg2Q2j789sEe8n3wkJB3hv7j%2BPmMc1Y%3D&amp;reserved=0\">Counseling &amp; Psychological Wellness Services</a> aims “to support and enhance the psychological health and wellbeing, personal growth and development of students.” The individualized services provided remain “confidential and free of charge to students.” While confidential, certain situations require a release of information for legal and/or ethical reasons. These limits are listed on the <a href=\"https://nam12.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.oldwestbury.edu%2Fdivision%2Foffice-student-affairs%2Fcounseling-psychological-wellness-services&amp;data=05%7C01%7Cjbecchin%40oldwestbury.edu%7C72972df0446f43f4664c08daa7b2cab2%7Cf5089034f2334f12a71638b7f4904370%7C0%7C0%7C638006683582597220%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&amp;sdata=YXn%2FTkgk28HSlg2Q2j789sEe8n3wkJB3hv7j%2BPmMc1Y%3D&amp;reserved=0\">Counseling &amp; Psychological Wellness Services</a> website.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">The website also provides resource links, general guidelines to help you make a plan, and advice for helping a friend. Some linked websites include <a href=\"https://nam12.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2F988lifeline.org%2F&amp;data=05%7C01%7Cjbecchin%40oldwestbury.edu%7C72972df0446f43f4664c08daa7b2cab2%7Cf5089034f2334f12a71638b7f4904370%7C0%7C0%7C638006683582597220%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&amp;sdata=78ODtaWxhVWAkk%2FN%2FAg86ITAnfANIQ6FEd8T6bSsFik%3D&amp;reserved=0\">National Suicide Prevention Lifeline</a>, <a href=\"https://nam12.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.oldwestbury.edu%2Fdivision%2Foffice-student-affairs%2Fcounseling-psychological-wellness-services%2Fresources-you-are-not&amp;data=05%7C01%7Cjbecchin%40oldwestbury.edu%7C72972df0446f43f4664c08daa7b2cab2%7Cf5089034f2334f12a71638b7f4904370%7C0%7C0%7C638006683582597220%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&amp;sdata=AHigECeQtjnpJzICOR4Tz4U9dN%2F%2BKSLro4fyoVjF5pg%3D&amp;reserved=0\">Triving Campus</a>, and <a href=\"https://nam12.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mentalhealthishealth.us%2F&amp;data=05%7C01%7Cjbecchin%40oldwestbury.edu%7C72972df0446f43f4664c08daa7b2cab2%7Cf5089034f2334f12a71638b7f4904370%7C0%7C0%7C638006683582597220%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&amp;sdata=z8k%2BGkZMpmTOxozvrslc6DmHceLF9uBawVMC5HLpdrs%3D&amp;reserved=0\">Half of Us</a> (Mental Health is Health).&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Faculty members can visit this website if they see a student needs support. There, they will find information on “Helping Students Face Emotional Difficulties… Recognizing Students in Distress… [and] Making a Referral to the Counseling Center.”</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">If you would like to contact SUNY Old Westbury’s <a href=\"https://nam12.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.oldwestbury.edu%2Fdivision%2Foffice-student-affairs%2Fcounseling-psychological-wellness-services&amp;data=05%7C01%7Cjbecchin%40oldwestbury.edu%7C72972df0446f43f4664c08daa7b2cab2%7Cf5089034f2334f12a71638b7f4904370%7C0%7C0%7C638006683582597220%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&amp;sdata=YXn%2FTkgk28HSlg2Q2j789sEe8n3wkJB3hv7j%2BPmMc1Y%3D&amp;reserved=0\">Counseling &amp; Psychological Wellness Services</a>, you can send an email to <a href=\"mailto:counselingcenter@oldwestbury.edu\">counselingcenter@oldwestbury.edu</a> or call (516)876-3053. This World Mental Health Day, make your mental health a priority.&nbsp;</p>\n', NULL, 'APPROVED', 'JV368', NULL, '2022-10-06 20:14:54', 0, 'On October 10, 2022, people around the world will recognize World Mental Health Day. The World Health Organization said the day provides a chance to “raise awareness of mental health issues around the world and to mobilize efforts in support of mental health.”  The organization’s theme for this year, “Make mental health & well-being for…\n', NULL, NULL, 6),
('ed5bf44d-61ed-11f1-98fa-60cf847a2597', 'podcast', 'Global Media News for You!', 'global-media-news-for-you', NULL, '<figure class=\"wp-block-post-featured-image\"><a href=\"https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/7194/news/global-media-news-for-you/\" title=\"Global Media News for You!\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"429\" height=\"429\" src=\"uploads/NMB-2-Hands-Square-NMB.jpg\" class=\"attachment-post-thumbnail size-post-thumbnail wp-post-image\" alt=\"\" style=\"object-fit:cover;\" srcset=\"uploads/NMB-2-Hands-Square-NMB.jpg 429w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/NMB-2-Hands-Square-NMB-70x70.jpg 70w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/NMB-2-Hands-Square-NMB-300x300.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 429px) 100vw, 429px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-audio\"><audio controls src=\"https://www.oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/NMB-2-Podcaast-2022-10-13.mp3\"></audio></figure>\n\n\n<p><strong>This Week on New Media Beat:</strong></p>\n<p><!-- /wp:post-content --><!-- wp:list --></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Nigeria: Why Did President Buhari Lift the Twitter Ban in January?</li>\n<li>Impact:&nbsp; Why Is South Africa Enforcing its Amended Internet Rules?</li>\n<li>Hong Kong: Is Social to Blame for COVID Delinquents?</li>\n<li>Why Did China Ban Foreign Social in 2009?</li>\n<li>What Is &#8220;Misinformation&#8221; in China?</li>\n<li>Nicaragua: What Has President Ortega Done to <em>La Prensa</em>?</li>\n<li>Mexican Journalists: The Killings Continue.&nbsp;</li>\n</ul>\n<p><!-- /wp:list --></p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --></p>\n<p><!-- /wp:paragraph --></p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.newmediabeat.org/\"><strong>New Media Beat</strong></a> covers media news from around the world. NMB is a production of&nbsp; Media Studies students from the <a href=\"https://www.oldwestbury.edu/\" target=\"_self\" rel=\"noopener\">SUNY College @ Old Westbury.</a>&nbsp;&nbsp; We scour the web for news about about the world of media, journalism and technology.</p>\n<p><!-- /wp:paragraph --></p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --></p>\n<p>Follow<strong> <a href=\"https://twitter.com/OWWRGMN\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">@OWWRGMN</a></strong> for a curated feed of the latest new media news for aspiring media professionals.</p>\n<p><!-- /wp:paragraph --></p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --></p>\n<p>The NMB Podcast streams live on <a href=\"http://www.owwrny.org/\">Old Westbury Web Radio</a> every Thursday from 10:00-11:00 AM EST.&nbsp; Can&#8217;t listen live? Our podcast will be <a href=\"https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/?cat=17\">posted</a> for your listening pleasure every Friday afternoon</p>\n<p><!-- /wp:paragraph --></p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --></p>\n<p><!-- /wp:paragraph --></p>\n<p><!-- wp:post-featured-image /--></p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --></p>\n<p><!-- /wp:paragraph --></p>', NULL, 'APPROVED', 'TC527', NULL, '2022-10-14 16:56:26', 0, 'This Week on New Media Beat: Nigeria: Why Did President Buhari Lift the Twitter Ban in January? Impact:  Why Is South Africa Enforcing its Amended Internet Rules? Hong Kong: Is Social to Blame for COVID Delinquents? Why Did China Ban Foreign Social in 2009? What Is “Misinformation” in China? Nicaragua: What Has President Ortega Done…\n', NULL, NULL, 1),
('ed5c3d45-61ed-11f1-98fa-60cf847a2597', 'article', 'The ICC Men’s T20 World Cup Guide', 'the-icc-mens-t20-world-cup-guide', NULL, '<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" src=\"uploads/image-66.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-7206\" width=\"567\" height=\"319\" srcset=\"https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/image-66.png 845w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/image-66-600x337.png 600w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/image-66-768x432.png 768w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/image-66-300x169.png 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 567px) 100vw, 567px\" /><figcaption>Photo credit: icc-cricket.com</figcaption></figure>\n</div>\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Here is a detailed guide with all that you need to know about this year’s cricket championship!</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\"><strong>What is The ICC Cricket Men’s T20 World Cup?</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">The Cricket World Cup is the international championship of cricket. This competition occurs every four years and is watched almost everywhere around the world.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\"><strong>How did the ICC Cricket Men’s T20 World Cup start?</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">The Cricket World Cup started in England in 1975. It was a one day match with 60 overs per side. Then, in 1987, the tournament was held in India and Pakistan.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\"><strong>When is the tournament going to happen this year?&nbsp;</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">The Cricket World Cup will happen from October 16 to November 13, 2022.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\"><strong>Who is going to host this year’s T20 World Cup?&nbsp;</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Australia will host the tournament in less than 100 days.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\"><strong>What are the tournament’s teams?</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">There are 32 teams that play in three different leagues. The first league is the Super League, in which 13 teams play. The second league is League 2, in which seven teams play. The third league is the Challenge League, in which 12 teams play. Based on the results of the leagues, some teams go straight forward to the World Cup, while other teams are eliminated and can’t play in the World Cup. Some teams advance to supplementary qualifying tournaments. A few of those teams are selected to play in the World Cup based on the results of the supplementary tournaments.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">According to an article from Sports Ganga, “India, Pakistan, Afghanistan, South Africa, West Indies, New Zealand, England &amp; hosts Australia, will be the participants. These 8 teams will go straight to super 12s. Namibia, Scotland, Sri Lanka, Bangladesh, UAE, Ireland, Netherlands &amp; Zimbabwe have secured their birth because they qualify for super 12s.”&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">The groups and their teams are:</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-table\"><table><tbody><tr><td><strong>Group A</strong></td><td><strong>Group B</strong></td><td><strong>Group 1</strong></td><td><strong>Group 2</strong></td></tr><tr><td>Namibia</td><td>Ireland</td><td>Afghanistan</td><td>Bangladesh</td></tr><tr><td>Netherlands</td><td>Scotland</td><td>Australia</td><td>India</td></tr><tr><td>Sri Lanka</td><td>West Indies</td><td>England</td><td>Pakistan</td></tr><tr><td>United Arab Emirates</td><td>Zimbabwe</td><td>New Zealand</td><td>South Africa</td></tr><tr><td></td><td></td><td>Group A Winner</td><td>Group A Runner-Up&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td></td><td></td><td>Group B Runner-Up&nbsp;</td><td>Group B Winner&nbsp;</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\"><strong>What is the cost of attending the ICC Cricket Men’s T20 World Cup</strong>?</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">According to SportsKeeda, the ticket prices for the ICC T20 World Cup range from $20.40 to $4,083.74. The general saver seat in the Stadium costs about $20.40 to $40.84, while a Premium Seat in the Stadium costs $61.26 to $217.80. The most expensive seat in the stadium is priced from $789.52 to $4,083.74.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\"><strong>What Stadiums will be available for the Tournament?</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">The T20 World Cup will be hosted in seven different stadiums. The stadiums are located across Australia. The stadiums are the Adelaide Oval, the Gabba, Kardinia Park, Bellerive Oval, Melbourne Cricket Ground, Perth Stadium, and Sydney Cricket Ground. Those stadiums have beautiful designs, architecture, and special features.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\"><strong>How much will the winners earn?</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">According to a report from ICC-Cricket website, the winners of the ICC Men&#8217;s T20 World Cup 2022 in Melbourne on November 13 will receive prize money of $1.6 million, with the runner-ups guaranteed half the amount. At the end of the nearly month-long 16-team tournament, the losing semi-finalists will each get $400,000 from the $5.6 million total prize pool. The eight teams who exit at the Super 12 stage will receive $70,000 each. Like last year at the ICC Men&#8217;s T20 World Cup 2021, a win in each of the 30 games in the Super 12 phase will be worth $40,000.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\"><strong>How to watch and listen to the Tournament?</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">The tournament will be televised on Willow TV and ESPN+ and will be live streamed through Hot Star in the USA.</p>\n', NULL, 'APPROVED', 'LG167', NULL, '2022-10-17 19:13:18', 0, 'Here is a detailed guide with all that you need to know about this year’s cricket championship! What is The ICC Cricket Men’s T20 World Cup? The Cricket World Cup is the international championship of cricket. This competition occurs every four years and is watched almost everywhere around the world.  How did the ICC Cricket…\n', NULL, NULL, 3),
('ed5c86a4-61ed-11f1-98fa-60cf847a2597', 'podcast', 'The Beat Goes On!', 'the-beat-goes-on', NULL, '\n<figure class=\"wp-block-video\"><video controls src=\"https://www.oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/NMB-3-Leaves-NMB-15s.mov\"></video><figcaption>Fall for New Media Beat!</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n<audio class=\"wp-audio-shortcode\" id=\"audio-7208-1\" preload=\"none\" style=\"width: 100%;\" controls=\"controls\"><source type=\"audio/mpeg\" src=\"https://www.oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/NMB-3-Podcast-2022-10-20.mp3?_=1\" /><a href=\"https://www.oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/NMB-3-Podcast-2022-10-20.mp3\">https://www.oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/NMB-3-Podcast-2022-10-20.mp3</a></audio>\n<p><strong>This Week on New Media Beat!</strong></p>\n<p><!-- /wp:post-content --><!-- wp:list --></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>China:</strong> Genshin Impact &#8211; miHoYo’s global mobile gaming sensation just keeps growing!</li>\n<li><strong>Indonesia:</strong> OTT Wars! Can <a href=\"https://www.vidio.com/categories/52-home-page\">Vidio</a> defeat Netflix and Disney+? </li>\n<li><strong>Iran:</strong> Filmmaker arrested for opposing the regime. Who is <span class=\"TextRun SCXW238748513 BCX0\" lang=\"EN-US\" xml:lang=\"EN-US\" data-contrast=\"auto\"><span class=\"NormalTextRun SCXW238748513 BCX0\">Jafar Panahi?</span></span></li>\n<li><strong>Pakistan:</strong> What can you share on social?</li>\n<li><strong>North Korea:</strong> No free media. Still. Why?</li>\n</ul>\n<p><!-- /wp:list --></p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.newmediabeat.org/\"><strong>New Media Beat</strong></a> covers media news from around the world. NMB is a production of  Media Studies students from the <a href=\"https://www.oldwestbury.edu/\" target=\"_self\" rel=\"noopener\">SUNY College @ Old Westbury.</a>   We scour the web for news about about the world of media, journalism and technology.</p>\n<p>Our producer is Michael Green. The podcast is engineered by Tania Fils-Aim<span style=\"color: initial; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \'Segoe UI\', Roboto, Oxygen-Sans, Ubuntu, Cantarell, \'Helvetica Neue\', sans-serif;\">é </span>and hosted by Jacob Friedenburg and Alex Hajko.</p>\n<p><!-- /wp:paragraph --></p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --></p>\n<p>Follow<strong> <a href=\"https://twitter.com/OWWRGMN\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">@OWWRGMN</a></strong> for a curated feed of the latest new media news for aspiring media professionals.</p>\n<p><!-- /wp:paragraph --></p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --></p>\n<p>The NMB Podcast streams live on <a href=\"http://www.owwrny.org/\">Old Westbury Web Radio</a> every Thursday from 10:00-11:00 AM EST.  Can&#8217;t listen live? Our podcast will be <a href=\"https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/?cat=17\">posted</a> for your listening pleasure every Friday afternoon</p>\n<p><!-- /wp:paragraph --></p>\n<p><!-- wp:post-featured-image /--></p>', NULL, 'APPROVED', 'TC527', NULL, '2022-10-21 15:58:02', 0, 'This Week on New Media Beat! China: Genshin Impact – miHoYo’s global mobile gaming sensation just keeps growing! Indonesia: OTT Wars! Can Vidio defeat Netflix and Disney+?  Iran: Filmmaker arrested for opposing the regime. Who is Jafar Panahi? Pakistan: What can you share on social? North Korea: No free media. Still. Why? New Media Beat…\n', NULL, NULL, 1),
('ed5cdaac-61ed-11f1-98fa-60cf847a2597', 'article', '“Terror on Totten:” Terrifying or Boring?', 'terror-on-totten-terrifying-or-boring', NULL, '<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter size-large is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" src=\"uploads/image-67-768x1024.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-7222\" width=\"357\" height=\"476\" srcset=\"https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/image-67-768x1024.png 768w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/image-67-450x600.png 450w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/image-67-900x1200.png 900w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/image-67-1152x1536.png 1152w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/image-67-225x300.png 225w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/image-67.png 1200w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 357px) 100vw, 357px\" /><figcaption>Photo Credit: Joanna Vissichelli</figcaption></figure>\n</div>\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-left wp-block-paragraph\">Warning: The following contains spoilers about an event and may include scary themes.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">The NYPD is hosting a thrilling event just in time for Halloween: <a href=\"https://nam12.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.terrorontotten.com%2F&amp;data=05%7C01%7Cjbecchin%40oldwestbury.edu%7C3c0153cb39694c0170a808dab1e4dbe4%7Cf5089034f2334f12a71638b7f4904370%7C0%7C0%7C638017893785050268%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&amp;sdata=sazgeVq9ER2%2BvS9PoXcj4S2cz8kLRYUvNx%2Fp7BDFWwk%3D&amp;reserved=0\">“Terror on Totten.”</a> This Haunted House consists of spooky fog, loud noises, and of course creepy characters!</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">The Haunted House took place in a tall brick building, decorated with a large skeleton with a pumpkin head. The hosts at the front door inform visitors that NYPD members volunteered to play the characters in the house. They also inform visitors that all noises played are fake and that any contact with the actors is completely unintentional.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">A volunteer then takes the visitors through a hallway to experience some potential sensations in the house: mist, noises, and scary visuals. The visitors proceed to enter through a tunnel… a very disorienting tunnel. As they cross a bridge, they pass through a tunnel of spinning lights that creates a wobbly sensation. When the visitors try to cross the bridge, an unexpected creature chases the group, as they all push each other to the finish.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Finally, at the end of the tunnel, the Haunted House begins. In groups of one to three, visitors walk up the stairs to the second level of the building. The host at the door yells, “fresh meat!” into the house as the visitors pass through the door. Enormous fog encapsulates the first room, as well as the rooms after.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">What seems like an empty room soon becomes a series of seemingly empty rooms. Creepy characters hide and disguise themselves with their surroundings. They perfectly time their “pop-outs” with chainsaw noises, banging, and silent crawling.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">At times, visitors have to do a double-take to try to figure out if a prop or a person stands ahead of them… and when it’s a person, a shriek usually follows the discovery. Human dolls, human pigs, and the Plague Doctor all made a frightening appearance.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">The spookiest part of the whole experience: the sensation of the unknown. Visitors, cornered by two creatures with scary noises and props, must pass to the next room through two inflatables pushing on each other. As visitors walk through the channel, they cannot see in front or behind them, and never know when this seemingly endless route will end. Without giving too much away, they will find the ending with a scary surprise!</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Going through the Haunted House for the first time felt like a dream (perhaps a nightmare), specifically for me. As someone with a low tolerance for fright, I found this Haunted House as a scary experience. Even after going through the house four times, I screamed in each room and found myself clinging to a different family member. Even though others may scare less easily than myself, I still recommend visiting “Terror on Totten” if you’re looking for a fun Halloween thrill.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\"><strong>The event will continue through October on Fridays, Saturdays, and Sundays from 4 p.m. to 11 p.m. Visitors can attend for free! The Haunted House is located on 604 Little Bay Road, Building 604, Bayside, NY 11359, and is recommended for people ages 12 and up.</strong></p>\n', NULL, 'APPROVED', 'JV368', NULL, '2022-10-20 16:49:00', 0, 'Warning: The following contains spoilers about an event and may include scary themes. The NYPD is hosting a thrilling event just in time for Halloween: “Terror on Totten.” This Haunted House consists of spooky fog, loud noises, and of course creepy characters! The Haunted House took place in a tall brick building, decorated with a…\n', NULL, NULL, 1),
('ed5d28d3-61ed-11f1-98fa-60cf847a2597', 'article', 'Popular L.I. Concert Venue to Receive an Upgrade', 'popular-l-i-concert-venue-to-receive-an-upgrade', NULL, '<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1200\" height=\"798\" src=\"uploads/image-68-1200x798.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-7226\" srcset=\"https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/image-68-1200x798.png 1200w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/image-68-600x399.png 600w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/image-68-768x511.png 768w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/image-68-1536x1021.png 1536w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/image-68-300x200.png 300w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/image-68.png 1600w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" /><figcaption><strong>Photo Credit:<a href=\"https://nam12.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fgreaterlongisland.com%2Fjones-beach-theater-set-to-get-a-major-makeover%2F&amp;data=05%7C01%7Cjbecchin%40oldwestbury.edu%7C66f68c207c7e463e823f08dab76250b5%7Cf5089034f2334f12a71638b7f4904370%7C0%7C0%7C638023930156223431%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&amp;sdata=Et15m3%2Be1yAa%2FOaOR91sSmvU1okVTX6LHFkKJwNSy3U%3D&amp;reserved=0\"><em>Greater Long Island</em></a></strong></figcaption></figure>\n</div>\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\"><strong>(Photo: Renovation plans for the Northwell Health at Jones Beach Theater</strong>)</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">If you live in Nassau County and have attended a summer concert, you’ve likely been to the Northwell Health at Jones Beach Theater in Wantagh, NY. This popular concert venue will receive upgrades as part of a five-year renovation plan!</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">According to the <a href=\"https://nam12.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fdailyvoice.com%2Fnew-york%2Fnassau%2Fbusiness%2Fan-even-better-experience-jones-beach-theater-to-get-multimillion-dollar-upgrade-photos%2F847048%2F&amp;data=05%7C01%7Cjbecchin%40oldwestbury.edu%7C66f68c207c7e463e823f08dab76250b5%7Cf5089034f2334f12a71638b7f4904370%7C0%7C0%7C638023930156223431%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&amp;sdata=zIQt81QwXGNoil4AdCdUv6U0mhKVvA9TwKPIuYLDans%3D&amp;reserved=0\"><em>Daily Voice</em></a>, Live Nation Entertainment will invest millions of dollars into the renovation project. The company has not disclosed the exact investment cost to the public. Fans can expect a “seamless” entryway and new and increased dining. <a href=\"https://nam12.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fgreaterlongisland.com%2Fjones-beach-theater-set-to-get-a-major-makeover%2F&amp;data=05%7C01%7Cjbecchin%40oldwestbury.edu%7C66f68c207c7e463e823f08dab76250b5%7Cf5089034f2334f12a71638b7f4904370%7C0%7C0%7C638023930156223431%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&amp;sdata=Et15m3%2Be1yAa%2FOaOR91sSmvU1okVTX6LHFkKJwNSy3U%3D&amp;reserved=0\"><em>Greater Long Island</em></a> reported that visitors can anticipate a food and beverage section dedicated to local concession options. </p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">One of the biggest additions to the amphitheater is a twenty percent increase in the number of bathroom facilities. The venue currently accommodates 14,500 people, so this will certainly benefit concertgoers. The renovation will also consist of replacing many seats in the upper section of the venue.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\"><a href=\"https://nam12.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fabc7ny.com%2Fgov-kathy-hochul-jones-beach-live-nation-new-investments%2F12361231%2F&amp;data=05%7C01%7Cjbecchin%40oldwestbury.edu%7C66f68c207c7e463e823f08dab76250b5%7Cf5089034f2334f12a71638b7f4904370%7C0%7C0%7C638023930156223431%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&amp;sdata=aOI0b59pgseTH9FiiMKXlXPtyx3LhVIzxsSgwzmICDw%3D&amp;reserved=0\"><em>ABC7NY</em></a> said that “resilience and sustainability will be improved with new seawalls to protect from high tides, new energy-efficient LED lighting, and solar-powered street lighting.” The Northwell Health at Jones Beach Theater has already received digital boards and increased concession areas as part of a previous Live Nation renovation.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\"><a href=\"https://nam12.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fgreaterlongisland.com%2Fjones-beach-theater-set-to-get-a-major-makeover%2F&amp;data=05%7C01%7Cjbecchin%40oldwestbury.edu%7C66f68c207c7e463e823f08dab76250b5%7Cf5089034f2334f12a71638b7f4904370%7C0%7C0%7C638023930156223431%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&amp;sdata=Et15m3%2Be1yAa%2FOaOR91sSmvU1okVTX6LHFkKJwNSy3U%3D&amp;reserved=0\"><em>Greater Long Island</em></a> explained that the Northwell Health at Jones Beach Theater will still have a 2023 summer concert season. Tom See, the chief operating officer for Live Nation’s Venue Nation, said, “We look forward to sharing the first phase of improvements with our fans next summer, and will continue to create an impact for years to come.” The Northwell Health at Jones Beach Theater has not revealed a start date for construction.<strong>  </strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">The 70-year-old concert venue has hosted many big artists from OneRepublic, to the Backstreet Boys, to Pitbull! According to <a href=\"https://nam12.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cbsnews.com%2Fnewyork%2Fnews%2Fjones-beach-theater-renovations%2F&amp;data=05%7C01%7Cjbecchin%40oldwestbury.edu%7C66f68c207c7e463e823f08dab76250b5%7Cf5089034f2334f12a71638b7f4904370%7C0%7C0%7C638023930156223431%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&amp;sdata=LL9MiI9k9i6QMMA26o3iN7LGHkAi5NAXjhqrTIZ5%2B1M%3D&amp;reserved=0\"><em>CBSNews</em></a>, the regional president at Live Nation Entertainment, Geoff Gordon, said &#8220;It&#8217;s a world-class venue, and these reimagining aspects that we&#8217;re going to add today and unveil today, will only make it that much better, and it will be the best venue on the East Coast.”</p>\n', NULL, 'APPROVED', 'JV368', NULL, '2022-10-26 11:37:37', 0, '(Photo: Renovation plans for the Northwell Health at Jones Beach Theater) If you live in Nassau County and have attended a summer concert, you’ve likely been to the Northwell Health at Jones Beach Theater in Wantagh, NY. This popular concert venue will receive upgrades as part of a five-year renovation plan! According to the Daily…\n', NULL, NULL, 1),
('ed5d77cc-61ed-11f1-98fa-60cf847a2597', 'article', 'Kenny Feldsott: Artist of Howls that Wake Us in the Night', 'kenny-feldsott-artist-of-howls-that-wake-us-in-the-night', NULL, '\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns is-layout-flex wp-container-core-columns-is-layout-8f761849 wp-block-columns-is-layout-flex\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:100%\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-group is-nowrap is-layout-flex wp-container-core-group-is-layout-8f761849 wp-block-group-is-layout-flex\">\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" src=\"uploads/image1-9.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-7248\" width=\"167\" height=\"318\" srcset=\"https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/image1-9.png 198w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/image1-9-157x300.png 157w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 167px) 100vw, 167px\" /><figcaption>Photo Credit: Luisa Garcia</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"232\" height=\"377\" src=\"uploads/image2-3.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-7249\" srcset=\"https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/image2-3.png 232w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/image2-3-185x300.png 185w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 232px) 100vw, 232px\" /></figure>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">The Amelie A. Wallace Gallery at SUNY College at Old Westbury hosted an art exhibition titled <em>Howls that Wake Us in the Night,</em> featuring artist Kenny Feldsott&#8217;s paintings.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">The exhibition had nearly forty paintings and works created by Feldsott. The paintings reflected topics of postcolonial traumas, violence, and human redemption.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Emerald Arguelles, an independent publisher of contemporary art, interviewed the artist and posted an article on her website, <a href=\"https://nam12.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aint-bad.com%2Farticle%2F2022%2F06%2F18%2Fin-conversation-with-feldsott%2F&amp;data=05%7C01%7Cjbecchin%40oldwestbury.edu%7C073987b4febc467fd1cb08dab7627510%7Cf5089034f2334f12a71638b7f4904370%7C0%7C0%7C638023930733837416%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&amp;sdata=Qk0y8SHzdbDTvO2f%2BwtTe69d%2F%2BeTrUl2o%2Ftf2aax1v0%3D&amp;reserved=0\"><em>aint-bad.com</em></a><em>.</em></p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">One of Arguelles&#8217; questions was “How has traditional medicine influenced your work?” Feldsott said, “For me, art acts as a medium or translation between the visible and the invisible world. It’s a conduit for all kinds of experiences to translate and become embodied somehow, whether that’s music or spoken word or dance or visual arts or conceptual art-whatever it is, there’s a translation of what is almost untouchable. Art triggers in us a kind of knowledge or understanding. Art, in its best ways, inspires us and cleans away the cobwebs that dull us and challenge us.”</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Feldsott, in full Yisrael K. Feldsott, is a California painter, sculptor, and shaman who has been creating art for almost fifty years. At the age of 17, he enrolled in the California College of the Arts (CCA). Then, without holding an undergraduate degree, he received an MFA.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">He worked on ecological restoration and cultural preservation initiatives in Central and South America, where he became a shaman and studied traditional medicine with local Indigenous populations.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Feldsott said during an interview at the 16th Annual LA Art Show that his artistic inspiration comes from “many artists from all over the world [that] have inspired [him] in places where [he has] been or seen out on the streets… and everything from Picasso to people’s names you wouldn’t even know.”&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">The artist combines elements of street art and modern art to produce a distinctive style and offer a sense of morality in the middle of an unending crisis.</p>\n', NULL, 'APPROVED', 'LG167', NULL, '2022-10-26 12:13:51', 0, 'The Amelie A. Wallace Gallery at SUNY College at Old Westbury hosted an art exhibition titled Howls that Wake Us in the Night, featuring artist Kenny Feldsott’s paintings. The exhibition had nearly forty paintings and works created by Feldsott. The paintings reflected topics of postcolonial traumas, violence, and human redemption.  Emerald Arguelles, an independent publisher…\n', NULL, NULL, 1),
('ed5dbbf9-61ed-11f1-98fa-60cf847a2597', 'article', 'A Soccer Experience', 'a-soccer-experience', NULL, '<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" src=\"uploads/image-74.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-7257\" width=\"478\" height=\"318\" srcset=\"https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/image-74.png 799w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/image-74-600x399.png 600w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/image-74-768x511.png 768w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/image-74-300x200.png 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 478px) 100vw, 478px\" /><figcaption>Photo Credit: Jessi Vasquez</figcaption></figure>\n</div>\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Jessi Vasquez has been playing soccer since he was 6 years old and has been his passion ever since. He is a  left winger for the Old Westbury Panthers, and he is so passionate about soccer because it’s an escape for him. When he plays soccer, everything else is irrelevant to him.“Even at such a young age I found myself to be passionate while watching soccer, that I eventually took up the sport and was even passionate about that,” he said. “Soccer provided me the escape that I needed and wanted from actual reality.”</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Growing up he kept up his love of the sport because of his friends. He continued to take the game more seriously as he grew older and it became one of his favorite pastimes.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Jessi attended Lawrence High School before attending OW and it was a whole different experience for him. He was on a team with all of his friends which motivated him more and made it extremely fun for all of them. He got to experience something he never experienced before in his life at the time, and it was extraordinary.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Much to his surprise, he made the varsity team freshman year of high school. That was when he knew he had to take it more seriously since he was now a full fledged player. “Making varsity was an experience that I never thought could happen. I knew I was good at soccer but to be good enough to represent the school playing this sport was a big accomplishment at the time,” he said.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">&nbsp;At that moment he knew he had to push himself to limits that he didn’t even know he could go. “I kept playing soccer because of how fun it is and how much passion I have for this sport. Soccer will always be a part of my life. No matter where I am in the world, I will never stop playing soccer,” Jessi stated.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">It is clear to see where Jessi’s love for soccer came from and how it has affected his life, both on and off the field. A lesson to take away from Jess is that to find something that we are passionate about and stick with it.</p>\n', NULL, 'APPROVED', 'DS861', NULL, '2022-10-28 13:56:44', 0, 'Jessi Vasquez has been playing soccer since he was 6 years old and has been his passion ever since. He is a  left winger for the Old Westbury Panthers, and he is so passionate about soccer because it’s an escape for him. When he plays soccer, everything else is irrelevant to him.“Even at such a…\n', NULL, NULL, 1),
('ed5e06d0-61ed-11f1-98fa-60cf847a2597', 'podcast', 'Listen: New Media Beat!', 'listen-new-media-beat', NULL, '\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://www.oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/NMB-4-Fall-Oak-1-1-1024x768.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-7271\"/><figcaption>Fall for New Media Beat!</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n<p><strong>This Week on New Media Beat:</strong> &nbsp;</p>\n<audio class=\"wp-audio-shortcode\" id=\"audio-7266-1\" preload=\"none\" style=\"width: 100%;\" controls=\"controls\"><source type=\"audio/mpeg\" src=\"uploads/NMB-4-Podcast-2022-10-27.mp3?_=1\" /><a href=\"uploads/NMB-4-Podcast-2022-10-27.mp3\">uploads/NMB-4-Podcast-2022-10-27.mp3</a></audio>\n<p></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>China: </strong>Targeting U.S. Elections with Social Media</li>\n<li><strong>Ethiopia &amp; Eritrea:&nbsp;</strong>Wartime Media Restrictions</li>\n<li><strong>North Korea:&nbsp;</strong>Government Phones and Internet Access</li>\n<li><strong>China:&nbsp;</strong>Government Swiping Left on Dating Apps</li>\n<li><strong>Iran: </strong>Protest Media Crackdown!</li>\n<li><strong>Kenya: </strong>Slamming&nbsp;the Closet Door on LGBTQ+ Media</li>\n<li><strong>Mexico: </strong>Drag Media Cultures: From <em>La Más</em><em> Draga&nbsp;</em>to RuPaul&#8217;s Drag Race Mexico!</li>\n<li><strong>Nicaragua:&nbsp;</strong>Why Is Ortega Turning Off the Radio?</li>\n</ul>\n<p><!-- /wp:post-content --></p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --></p>\n<p>The NMB Podcast streams live on <a href=\"http://www.owwrny.org/\">Old Westbury Web Radio</a> Thursdays from 10:00-11:00 AM EST.&nbsp; Can&#8217;t listen live? Our podcast will be <a href=\"https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/?cat=17\">posted</a> for your listening pleasure every Friday afternoon. &nbsp;</p>\n<p><!-- /wp:paragraph --></p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --></p>\n<p>NMB is produced by Michael Green. Our engineer is Jacob Friedenburg. Our hosts are Stephany Okenwa &amp; Kayla Sedotto!</p>\n<p><!-- /wp:paragraph --></p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.newmediabeat.org/\"><strong>New Media Beat</strong></a> covers new media news from around the world.&nbsp;NMB&nbsp;is a production of&nbsp; Media Studies students from the <a href=\"https://www.oldwestbury.edu/\" target=\"_self\" rel=\"noopener\">SUNY College @ Old Westbury.</a>&nbsp;&nbsp; We scour the web for news about about the world of media, journalism and technology.</p>\n<p><!-- /wp:paragraph --></p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --></p>\n<p>Follow<strong> <a href=\"https://twitter.com/OWWRGMN\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">@OWWRGMN</a></strong> for a curated feed of the latest new media news for aspiring media professionals. &nbsp;</p>\n<p><!-- /wp:paragraph --></p>', NULL, 'APPROVED', 'TC527', NULL, '2022-10-28 16:41:27', 0, 'This Week on New Media Beat:   China: Targeting U.S. Elections with Social Media Ethiopia & Eritrea: Wartime Media Restrictions North Korea: Government Phones and Internet Access China: Government Swiping Left on Dating Apps Iran: Protest Media Crackdown! Kenya: Slamming the Closet Door on LGBTQ+ Media Mexico: Drag Media Cultures: From La Más Draga to RuPaul’s Drag Race Mexico! Nicaragua: Why…\n', NULL, NULL, 1);
INSERT INTO `content` (`id`, `type`, `title`, `slug`, `description`, `content`, `url`, `approval_status`, `author_id`, `editor_id`, `created_at`, `is_featured`, `excerpt`, `video_url`, `featured_image`, `category_id`) VALUES
('ed5e5447-61ed-11f1-98fa-60cf847a2597', 'article', 'The New Center of Excellence for Veteran Student Success', 'the-new-center-of-excellence-for-veteran-student-success', NULL, '\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"300\" height=\"158\" src=\"uploads/image-76-300x158.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-7275\" srcset=\"https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/image-76-300x158.png 300w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/image-76-600x315.png 600w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/image-76-768x403.png 768w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/image-76.png 1200w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" /><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Photo Credit: OldWestbury.edu</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">SUNY College at Old Westbury has received a federal grant allowing for the creation of the Center of Excellence for Veteran Student Success (CEVSS).&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">The U.S. Department of Education granted SUNY Old Westbury over $538,000 for the Center. As the first New York State campus to ever receive funding from this grant, SUNY Old Westbury hopes to provide a college path for veterans.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">The <a href=\"https://nam12.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww2.ed.gov%2Fprograms%2Fcevss%2Findex.html&amp;data=05%7C01%7Cjbecchin%40oldwestbury.edu%7C7ad5c9b52f354b3aea7d08dabc4de1b1%7Cf5089034f2334f12a71638b7f4904370%7C0%7C0%7C638029339925751094%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&amp;sdata=90PaRMh%2BLVuQanZ%2FB1%2Bf2m3mWBvGbNeqivViMygIHRg%3D&amp;reserved=0\">United States Department of Education</a> hopes to “[encourage] model programs to support veteran student success in postsecondary education by coordinating services to address the academic, financial, physical, and social needs of veteran students.” The grant will cover many costs, including a support team, a coordinator, and the development of a sustainable plan.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">SUNY OW will also hire staff to support the Center. One member will focus on coordinating services and community outreach. The other will act as the “Veteran Student Success Coach,” concentrating on advising, financial counseling, etc. SUNY OW has not yet announced the new hires.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">According to a SUNY OW <a href=\"https://nam12.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.oldwestbury.edu%2Fnews-events%2Fsuny-old-westbury-create-center-excellence-veteran-student-success&amp;data=05%7C01%7Cjbecchin%40oldwestbury.edu%7C7ad5c9b52f354b3aea7d08dabc4de1b1%7Cf5089034f2334f12a71638b7f4904370%7C0%7C0%7C638029339925907325%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&amp;sdata=qoS7sRYTA12j1%2BEqXsRAbNNCHaxqWQwOf0JlgO%2FmGoE%3D&amp;reserved=0\">news announcement</a>, “Through the CEVSS, the College will seek to partner with veteran organizations to form a network of support while offering these organizations guidance and resources to promote access to higher education for veterans.” These organizations have yet to be confirmed.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Dr. Cristina Notaro, Assistant Provost for Student Success and Administration and the principal investigator for the grant, said currently, “We have about 50 veterans and our goal is to grow to 200 in the next few years.” She also emphasized that the College hopes the Center will provide proactive academic support and planning for veteran students.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">While not required, recipients of the grant may choose to provide tutoring services and housing support. The <a href=\"https://nam12.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww2.ed.gov%2Fprograms%2Fcevss%2Findex.html&amp;data=05%7C01%7Cjbecchin%40oldwestbury.edu%7C7ad5c9b52f354b3aea7d08dabc4de1b1%7Cf5089034f2334f12a71638b7f4904370%7C0%7C0%7C638029339925907325%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&amp;sdata=sq2VHAP4y3ciJX7BFUk8HRFfureC0nT993C4hffX2GE%3D&amp;reserved=0\">United States Department of Education</a> also said recipients may choose to coordinate “academic advising and admissions counseling with military bases and national guard units in the area.”<br>Some veteran-related opportunities that already exist at SUNY Old Westbury include the <a href=\"https://nam12.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.oldwestbury.edu%2Fdivision%2Foffice-academic-affairs%2Fveterans-benefits-and-resources%2Fnew-york-state-benefits-available&amp;data=05%7C01%7Cjbecchin%40oldwestbury.edu%7C7ad5c9b52f354b3aea7d08dabc4de1b1%7Cf5089034f2334f12a71638b7f4904370%7C0%7C0%7C638029339925907325%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&amp;sdata=EklX5snO%2F2TEYznh8CluxkxWeiUtz47lCuoJMU7AnLs%3D&amp;reserved=0\">NYS Veterans Tuition Award</a>, <a href=\"https://nam12.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.oldwestbury.edu%2Fdivision%2Foffice-academic-affairs%2Fveterans-benefits-and-resources%2Ffederal-benefits-available&amp;data=05%7C01%7Cjbecchin%40oldwestbury.edu%7C7ad5c9b52f354b3aea7d08dabc4de1b1%7Cf5089034f2334f12a71638b7f4904370%7C0%7C0%7C638029339925907325%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&amp;sdata=aJTtR3bSF%2FThw3P9mR7xtlzlrVEGZtCcMY7KLmdVw%2Bs%3D&amp;reserved=0\">federal benefits</a>, and other <a href=\"https://nam12.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.oldwestbury.edu%2Fdivision%2Foffice-academic-affairs%2Fveterans-benefits-and-resources%2Fsuny-old-westbury-benefits&amp;data=05%7C01%7Cjbecchin%40oldwestbury.edu%7C7ad5c9b52f354b3aea7d08dabc4de1b1%7Cf5089034f2334f12a71638b7f4904370%7C0%7C0%7C638029339925907325%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&amp;sdata=AIV65H%2FaV7xQPSMsoRNZ65hWEh2FA98xe4brVIMlEKs%3D&amp;reserved=0\">on-campus benefits</a>.</p>\n', NULL, 'APPROVED', 'JV368', NULL, '2022-11-01 17:17:17', 0, 'SUNY College at Old Westbury has received a federal grant allowing for the creation of the Center of Excellence for Veteran Student Success (CEVSS).  The U.S. Department of Education granted SUNY Old Westbury over $538,000 for the Center. As the first New York State campus to ever receive funding from this grant, SUNY Old Westbury…\n', NULL, NULL, 1),
('ed5ec690-61ed-11f1-98fa-60cf847a2597', 'podcast', 'Media News Blast!', 'media-news-blast', NULL, '<p><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter wp-image-7292 size-full\" src=\"uploads/NMB-6-Leaves-Banner-Top-Cat-scaled-1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"2560\" height=\"775\" srcset=\"https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/NMB-6-Leaves-Banner-Top-Cat-scaled-1.jpg 2560w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/NMB-6-Leaves-Banner-Top-Cat-scaled-1-600x182.jpg 600w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/NMB-6-Leaves-Banner-Top-Cat-scaled-1-1200x363.jpg 1200w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/NMB-6-Leaves-Banner-Top-Cat-scaled-1-768x233.jpg 768w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/NMB-6-Leaves-Banner-Top-Cat-scaled-1-1536x465.jpg 1536w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/NMB-6-Leaves-Banner-Top-Cat-scaled-1-2048x620.jpg 2048w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/NMB-6-Leaves-Banner-Top-Cat-scaled-1-300x91.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 2560px) 100vw, 2560px\" /></p>\n<p><strong>This Week on New Media Beat:</strong></p>\n<audio class=\"wp-audio-shortcode\" id=\"audio-7289-1\" preload=\"none\" style=\"width: 100%;\" controls=\"controls\"><source type=\"audio/mpeg\" src=\"uploads/NMB-6-Podcast-2022-11-10.mp3?_=1\" /><a href=\"uploads/NMB-6-Podcast-2022-11-10.mp3\">uploads/NMB-6-Podcast-2022-11-10.mp3</a></audio>\n<p></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>China:</strong> Bridge Man Censored!</li>\n<li><strong>Tunisia:&nbsp;</strong>Press Freedom Friction?</li>\n<li><strong>Nicaragua:&nbsp;</strong>Television Rules News!</li>\n<li><strong>Indonesia: </strong>Restricting Social Media.</li>\n<li><strong>Russia: </strong>Putin&#8217;s Music Censorship.</li>\n<li><strong>Barbados:</strong> Island Media Intro!</li>\n<li><strong>China:</strong> More Media Censorhip?</li>\n<li><strong>Singapore: </strong>LGBTQ+ Content Ban?</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">The NMB Podcast streams live on <a href=\"http://www.owwrny.org/\">Old Westbury Web Radio</a> Thursdays from 10:00-11:00 AM EST.&nbsp; Can&#8217;t listen live? Our podcast will be <a href=\"https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/?cat=17\">posted</a> for your listening pleasure every Friday afternoon.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">NMB is produced by Michael Green. Our engineer is Jacob Friedenburg.&nbsp; Our hosts are Anthony Moyett &amp; Joanna Vissichelli.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\"><a href=\"https://www.newmediabeat.org/\"><strong>New Media Beat</strong></a> covers new media news from around the world.&nbsp;NMB&nbsp;is a production of&nbsp; Media Studies students from the <a href=\"https://www.oldwestbury.edu/\" target=\"_self\" rel=\"noopener\">SUNY College @ Old Westbury.</a>&nbsp;&nbsp; We scour the web for news about about the world of media, journalism and technology.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Follow<strong> <a href=\"https://twitter.com/OWWRGMN\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">@OWWRGMN</a></strong> for a curated feed of the latest new media news for aspiring media professionals.</p>\n\n\n<p><a href=\"uploads/NMB-6-Leaves-Nations-Square-scaled-1-1200x1200.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-5607\" src=\"uploads/NMB-6-Leaves-Nations-Square-scaled-1-1200x1200.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"2560\" height=\"734\"></a></p>', NULL, 'APPROVED', 'TC527', NULL, '2022-11-11 13:43:47', 0, 'This Week on New Media Beat: China: Bridge Man Censored! Tunisia: Press Freedom Friction? Nicaragua: Television Rules News! Indonesia: Restricting Social Media. Russia: Putin’s Music Censorship. Barbados: Island Media Intro! China: More Media Censorhip? Singapore: LGBTQ+ Content Ban? The NMB Podcast streams live on Old Westbury Web Radio Thursdays from 10:00-11:00 AM EST.  Can’t listen live? Our…\n', NULL, NULL, 1),
('ed5f15a7-61ed-11f1-98fa-60cf847a2597', 'article', ' COVID-19 Coverage for Fall 2022 and Spring 2023  ', 'covid-19-coverage-for-fall-2022-and-spring-2023', NULL, '<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" src=\"uploads/image-79.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-7305\" width=\"514\" height=\"289\" srcset=\"https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/image-79.png 850w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/image-79-600x337.png 600w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/image-79-768x432.png 768w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/image-79-300x169.png 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 514px) 100vw, 514px\" /><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Photo Credit: <a href=\"https://nam12.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Flabblog.uofmhealth.org%2F&amp;data=05%7C01%7Cjbecchin%40oldwestbury.edu%7C6d4a1e40e10d43a219bb08dac5ba8492%7Cf5089034f2334f12a71638b7f4904370%7C0%7C0%7C638039702144463279%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&amp;sdata=h%2B9Q%2BCajLx7kGWVjffWkw53pFVVwkfbR1IAw1bmLiqY%3D&amp;reserved=0\">labblog.uofmhealth.org</a>&nbsp;</figcaption></figure>\n</div>\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">For the Fall 2022 and Spring 2023 semesters, SUNY College at Old Westbury will continuously follow all public health and state guidelines for COVID-19 to provide a safe and healthy environment for students, faculty, staff, and visitors.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">The Student Health Center announced that any changes or implementations of COVID-19 guidance would be provided via email to our campus community. The website guidance would also be updated.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Here is the updated COVID-19 guidance for this semester, Fall 2022, and next semester, Spring 2023, to protect our community on campus.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\"><strong>Vaccination and Boosters</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">SUNY Old Westbury requires students that are planning to be on campus to submit their CDC vaccination card to the Student Health Center by emailing <a href=\"mailto:studenthealth@oldwestbury.edu\">studenthealth@oldwestbury.edu</a>.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Remote classes are not an option for students who are not vaccinated. These students cannot request changes in the course modality if they do not get the vaccine.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Students who are not vaccinated and fail to complete a religious or medical exemption will be disenrolled from all of their in-person classes. They will not be allowed on campus.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Students who wish to receive their COVID-19 booster can update their CDC vaccination card by sending it to the Student Health Center by emailing <a href=\"mailto:studenthealth@oldwestbury.edu\">studenthealth@oldwestbury.edu</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Faculty and staff who are already vaccinated can submit their CDC Vaccination Card to the Office of Human Resources via email to <a href=\"mailto:HR@oldwestbury.edu\">HR@oldwestbury.edu</a>. If they do not get vaccinated, they cannot return to campus until they provide proof that they are vaccinated.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Faculty and staff that are vaccinated and send proof will not be mandated to have weekly testing for COVID-19.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\"><strong>Available Exemptions</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">The school provides the option of medical and religious exemptions that should be requested for students who qualify.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">All exemption requests for the Fall 2022 semester have already been reviewed. The deadline to submit a request was August 15, 2022. The deadline for the Spring 2023 semester will be announced closer to the beginning of that semester.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Students who are exempt and receive remote, hybrid, or in-person classes must be tested for COVID-19 weekly. The failure to provide a weekly test for COVID-19 will result in a conduct proceeding and suspension.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">The school also provides an affidavit of affirmation form for those seeking a remote exemption from required COVID-19 vaccination for Fall 2022 and Spring 2023. Those students will not be allowed to enroll in face-to-face classes or attend any meetings and activities for clubs.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">If you have questions, please email them to <a href=\"mailto:covid19-remote@oldwestbury.edu\">covid19-remote@oldwestbury.edu</a> and someone will answer as soon as possible.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\"><strong>Masking</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">The masking policy is subject to change at any time, and students, faculty, and staff are required to always follow the masking guidelines.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Students should wear a mask in class if the instructor requires them to wear one.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">In settings like the Student Health Center, Office of Counseling and Psychological Wellness, COVID-19 testing site, and other health centers, students, visitors, faculty, and staff are required to always wear a mask.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">When you are feeling COVID-19 symptoms, you must wear a mask, get tested for COVID-19, and quarantine. After the quarantine period, students should wear a mask for five more days.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\"><strong>Isolation and Quarantine</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Employees that are not feeling well should not go to work and they must call Human Resources for more directions on what to do.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">When employees test positive for COVID-19, they should submit the result via email to Human Resources and quarantine for five days.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Students who are not feeling well should not go to class or any campus activities. They must call and inform the Student Health Center.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">When students test positive for COVID-19, they should submit the results via email to the Student Health Center and quarantine for five days.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\"><strong>Distancing&nbsp;</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Requirements for physical distance are no longer applicable for students, visitors, faculty, and staff.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\"><strong>Mental Health&nbsp;</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">The Office of Counseling and Psychological Wellness Services are available for all students to seek help if they are struggling to handle the challenges that arrived with the pandemic.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\"><strong>Visitors’ Guidelines</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">All visitors should have completed their initial COVID-19 vaccination series. If they are not feeling well, they should not visit campus until they are completely sure that they are testing negative for COVID-19.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Right now, masks are optional and frequent hand washing is encouraged.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\"><strong>Campus Transportation</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">The use of masks while riding the shuttle bus is optional for both the drivers and the passengers.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">If you would like to know more about COVID-19 guidance, you can visit the school website at <a href=\"https://nam12.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.oldwestbury.edu%2F&amp;data=05%7C01%7Cjbecchin%40oldwestbury.edu%7C044dd3bd4b7f494425e908dac711e271%7Cf5089034f2334f12a71638b7f4904370%7C0%7C0%7C638041176895557238%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&amp;sdata=lY81J%2BC5NbGCjm%2BBV1%2B0ohTK6%2B2PyFXLpS2nazslmxU%3D&amp;reserved=0\">https://www.oldwestbury.edu</a>. You can also email the Student Health Center at <a href=\"mailto:studenthealth@oldwestbury.edu\">studenthealth@oldwestbury.edu</a> or call (516) 876-3250 if you have any additional questions.</p>\n', NULL, 'APPROVED', 'LG167', NULL, '2022-11-14 11:33:19', 0, 'For the Fall 2022 and Spring 2023 semesters, SUNY College at Old Westbury will continuously follow all public health and state guidelines for COVID-19 to provide a safe and healthy environment for students, faculty, staff, and visitors. The Student Health Center announced that any changes or implementations of COVID-19 guidance would be provided via email…\n', NULL, NULL, 1),
('ed5f6896-61ed-11f1-98fa-60cf847a2597', 'article', 'Review:  On the Street; The Extraordinary Vision of Sook Jin Jo at the Amelia A. Wallace Gallery', 'review-on-the-street-the-extraordinary-vision-of-sook-jin-jo-at-the-amelia-a-wallace-gallery', NULL, '<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" src=\"uploads/image-80.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-7317\" width=\"428\" height=\"389\" srcset=\"https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/image-80.png 775w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/image-80-600x546.png 600w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/image-80-768x699.png 768w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/image-80-300x273.png 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 428px) 100vw, 428px\" /><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Photo Credit: <a href=\"https://nam12.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fsoutheastmuseumofphotography.org%2F&amp;data=05%7C01%7Cjbecchin%40oldwestbury.edu%7C3b56b55e5223413143aa08dac7f9e829%7Cf5089034f2334f12a71638b7f4904370%7C0%7C0%7C638042173416682372%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&amp;sdata=JH4cuNgulvBVDN51rln7Lo0KrUDP8PJJ1ZKKs2D4XH8%3D&amp;reserved=0\">https://southeastmuseumofphotography.org</a></figcaption></figure>\n</div>\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\"><strong>October 28-December 1</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">The Amelia A. Wallace Gallery at the State University of New York at Old Westbury is hosting an art exhibition titled: &#8220;<em>On the Street. The Extraordinary Vision of Sook Jin Jo,&#8221;</em> curated by Amelia A. Wallace Gallery Director Hyewon Yi.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Sook Jin Jo is a multidisciplinary artist living in New York and of Korean descent. Since 1985, she has created art that inspires and creates awareness.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Her art includes diverse forms of art, such as drawings and sculptures. Jo also does performances, photographs, videos, installations, public artworks, and architecture with the approach of restoring humanity and reclaiming empathy and truth.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">She had been the subject of thirty-five solo exhibitions. Some of her exhibitions are &#8220;<em>Walter Gropius Mater Artist Series,&#8221;</em> a collaboration with immigrants from Latin America that was exhibited in Virginia; &#8220;<em>SeMA Gold 2014: Nobody</em>&#8220;; and the contemporary art exhibition &#8220;<em>Art Jeoji 2022,&#8221;</em> exhibited in Korea.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">The solo exhibition highlights recent photographic works, sculptures, and video documentation of her public projects and architectural work focusing on the circle of life and destruction.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">The photos portray one hundred homeless people, representing the crude reality that some people experience on the streets of New York City.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">The art exhibition also presents massive wooden assemblage sculptures. Those sculptures reflect the spiritual significance of discarded objects and fading ecosystems.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">According to and article of <em>The Korean Art Museum Association Museum website,</em> Donald Kuspit, an American art critic and poet known for his practice of psychoanalytic art criticism, said, &#8220;Sook Jin Jo&#8217;s work is not &#8220;junk sculpture&#8221; in the ordinary sense,&#8221; and &#8220;there is nothing arbitrary and vulgar about Jo’s abstract compositions, as there is about the crude material found on the street&#8230; Jo has taken profane materials and created a sacred art.&#8221;</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">During the art exhibition, I felt extremely connected with the photographic work displayed because it reflected the inequality that is experienced in different cities around the world, especially in New York City, the capital of the world.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">The colors and the paper used for the photographs were excellent. Sook Jin Jo impressed me with the quality of her photographs.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Her sculptures had many surfaces of carelessly painted dark colors on wooden supports. These flat surfaces combine to create abstract relief sculptures without a figurative content..</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Sook Jin Jo’s art exhibit on the OW campus shows a diverse art style that will promote and inspire all visitors to the gallery to form their own opinions and interpretations of Jo’s body of work.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\"></p>\n', NULL, 'APPROVED', 'LG167', NULL, '2022-11-16 12:50:14', 0, 'October 28-December 1 The Amelia A. Wallace Gallery at the State University of New York at Old Westbury is hosting an art exhibition titled: “On the Street. The Extraordinary Vision of Sook Jin Jo,” curated by Amelia A. Wallace Gallery Director Hyewon Yi. Sook Jin Jo is a multidisciplinary artist living in New York and…\n', NULL, NULL, 6),
('ed5fb5c7-61ed-11f1-98fa-60cf847a2597', 'podcast', 'EU, Germany, South Korea, Japan, Israel, Palestine, Iran, & Russia!', 'eu-germany-south-korea-japan-israel-palestine-iran-russia', NULL, '\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://www.oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/NMB-7-Night-Oak-Flash-Countries-Web-1024x377.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-7322\"/></figure>\n\n\n<p><strong>This Week on New Media Beat:</strong></p>\n<audio class=\"wp-audio-shortcode\" id=\"audio-7320-1\" preload=\"none\" style=\"width: 100%;\" controls=\"controls\"><source type=\"audio/mpeg\" src=\"uploads/NMB-7-Podcast-2022-11-17.mp3?_=1\" /><a href=\"uploads/NMB-7-Podcast-2022-11-17.mp3\">uploads/NMB-7-Podcast-2022-11-17.mp3</a></audio>\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\"></p>\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>European Union:</strong> What is the Digital Services Act?</li>\n<li><strong>South Korea: </strong>The Other Side of K-Pop?</li>\n<li><strong>Japan: </strong>VTubers!</li>\n<li><strong>Qatar: </strong>Strings Attached &#8211; Free Trip to World Cup?</li>\n<li><strong>Israel: </strong>Why Did TikTok Deplatform the Lions Den?</li>\n<li><strong>Iran:</strong> Digital Activists Take on the Government!</li>\n<li><strong>Russia: </strong>LGBTQ+ &#8220;Propaganda&#8221; Law Under Fire.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><!-- /wp:post-content --></p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --></p>\n<p>The NMB Podcast streams live on <a href=\"http://www.owwrny.org/\">Old Westbury Web Radio</a> Thursdays from 10:00-11:00 AM EST.&nbsp; Can&#8217;t listen live? Our podcast will be <a href=\"https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/?cat=17\">posted</a> for your listening pleasure every Friday afternoon.</p>\n<p><!-- /wp:paragraph --></p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --></p>\n<p>NMB is produced by Michael Green. Our engineer is Tania Fils-Aimé.&nbsp; Our hosts are Jacob Friedenburg &amp; Alex Hajko.</p>\n<p><!-- /wp:paragraph --></p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.newmediabeat.org/\"><strong>New Media Beat</strong></a> covers new media news from around the world.&nbsp;NMB&nbsp;is a production of&nbsp; Media Studies students from the <a href=\"https://www.oldwestbury.edu/\" target=\"_self\" rel=\"noopener\">SUNY College @ Old Westbury.</a>&nbsp;&nbsp; We scour the web for news about about the world of media, journalism and technology.</p>\n<p><!-- /wp:paragraph --></p>\n<p>Follow<strong> <a href=\"https://twitter.com/OWWRGMN\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">@OWWRGMN</a></strong> for a curated feed of the latest new media news for aspiring media professionals.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p><!-- wp:image {\"id\":7329,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} --></p>\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://www.oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/NMB-7-Green-NMB-Night-Oak-Flash-Banner-Web-1024x256.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-7329\"></figure>\n<p><!-- /wp:image --></p>\n<p><!-- wp:post-featured-image /--></p>', NULL, 'APPROVED', 'TC527', NULL, '2022-11-18 15:37:17', 0, 'This Week on New Media Beat: European Union: What is the Digital Services Act? South Korea: The Other Side of K-Pop? Japan: VTubers! Qatar: Strings Attached – Free Trip to World Cup? Israel: Why Did TikTok Deplatform the Lions Den? Iran: Digital Activists Take on the Government! Russia: LGBTQ+ “Propaganda” Law Under Fire. The NMB…\n', NULL, NULL, 1),
('ed600c97-61ed-11f1-98fa-60cf847a2597', 'video', 'Your Global Media News Update!', 'your-global-media-news-update-2', NULL, '<p><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter wp-image-7347 size-medium\" src=\"uploads/NMB-8-Stump-NMB-Green-Square-e1670106640203-1200x855.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"500\" height=\"356\" srcset=\"https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/NMB-8-Stump-NMB-Green-Square-e1670106640203-1200x855.jpg 1200w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/NMB-8-Stump-NMB-Green-Square-e1670106640203-600x427.jpg 600w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/NMB-8-Stump-NMB-Green-Square-e1670106640203-768x547.jpg 768w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/NMB-8-Stump-NMB-Green-Square-e1670106640203-300x214.jpg 300w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/NMB-8-Stump-NMB-Green-Square-e1670106640203.jpg 1513w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px\" /></p>\n<p><strong>This Week on New Media Beat:</strong></p>\n<audio class=\"wp-audio-shortcode\" id=\"audio-7343-1\" preload=\"none\" style=\"width: 100%;\" controls=\"controls\"><source type=\"audio/mpeg\" src=\"uploads/NMB-8-Podcast-2022-12-01.mp3?_=1\" /><a href=\"uploads/NMB-8-Podcast-2022-12-01.mp3\">uploads/NMB-8-Podcast-2022-12-01.mp3</a></audio>\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\"></p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\"></p>\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Tibet:&nbsp;</strong>Lockdown Video Protests!</li>\n<li><strong>China:&nbsp;</strong>Online Comments Censored!</li>\n<li><strong>Nicaragua:&nbsp;</strong>Internet Under Ortega.</li>\n<li><strong>Turkey: </strong>Pressure on Journalists?</li>\n<li><strong>China:&nbsp;</strong>Ethnic Minority Influencers?</li>\n<li><strong>Internet:</strong>&nbsp; The ITU Explained!</li>\n<li><strong>Asia:&nbsp;</strong>Disney+ Creator Hunt!</li>\n<li><strong>Canada:&nbsp;</strong>What&#8217;s on TV?</li>\n</ul>\n<p><!-- /wp:post-content --></p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --></p>\n<p>The NMB Podcast streams live on <a href=\"http://www.owwrny.org/\">Old Westbury Web Radio</a> Thursdays from 10:00-11:00 AM EST.&nbsp; Can&#8217;t listen live? Our podcast will be <a href=\"https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/?cat=17\">posted</a> for your listening pleasure every Friday afternoon.</p>\n<p><!-- /wp:paragraph --></p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --></p>\n<p>NMB is produced by Michael Green. Our engineer is Jacob Friedenburg.&nbsp; Our hosts are Kayla Sedotto &amp; Anthony Moyett.</p>\n<p><!-- /wp:paragraph --></p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.newmediabeat.org/\"><strong>New Media Beat</strong></a> covers new media news from around the world.&nbsp;NMB&nbsp;is a production of&nbsp; Media Studies students from the <a href=\"https://www.oldwestbury.edu/\" target=\"_self\" rel=\"noopener\">SUNY College @ Old Westbury.</a>&nbsp;&nbsp; We scour the web for news about about the world of media, journalism and technology.</p>\n<p><!-- /wp:paragraph --></p>\n<p>Follow<strong> <a href=\"https://twitter.com/OWWRGMN\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">@OWWRGMN</a></strong> for a curated feed of the latest new media news for aspiring media professionals.</p>\n<p>&nbsp; <img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter wp-image-7345 size-full\" src=\"uploads/NMB-8-Cat-Bark-Banner-scaled-1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"2560\" height=\"705\" srcset=\"https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/NMB-8-Cat-Bark-Banner-scaled-1.jpg 2560w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/NMB-8-Cat-Bark-Banner-scaled-1-600x165.jpg 600w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/NMB-8-Cat-Bark-Banner-scaled-1-1200x330.jpg 1200w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/NMB-8-Cat-Bark-Banner-scaled-1-768x212.jpg 768w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/NMB-8-Cat-Bark-Banner-scaled-1-1536x423.jpg 1536w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/NMB-8-Cat-Bark-Banner-scaled-1-2048x564.jpg 2048w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/NMB-8-Cat-Bark-Banner-scaled-1-300x83.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 2560px) 100vw, 2560px\" /></p>', NULL, 'APPROVED', 'TC527', NULL, '2022-12-03 17:22:02', 0, 'This Week on New Media Beat: Tibet: Lockdown Video Protests! China: Online Comments Censored! Nicaragua: Internet Under Ortega. Turkey: Pressure on Journalists? China: Ethnic Minority Influencers? Internet:  The ITU Explained! Asia: Disney+ Creator Hunt! Canada: What’s on TV? The NMB Podcast streams live on Old Westbury Web Radio Thursdays from 10:00-11:00 AM EST.  Can’t listen live? Our podcast will be posted…\n', NULL, NULL, 15),
('ed605991-61ed-11f1-98fa-60cf847a2597', 'article', 'Campus Upgrades', 'campus-upgrades', NULL, '<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter size-large is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" src=\"uploads/image-86-300x200.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-7370\" width=\"641\" height=\"427\" srcset=\"https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/image-86-300x200.png 300w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/image-86-600x400.png 600w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/image-86-768x512.png 768w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/image-86.png 1140w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 641px) 100vw, 641px\" /><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Photo Credit: oldwestbury.edu</figcaption></figure>\n</div>\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">After delays caused by Covid, problems with supply chains, and even the weather, significant campus renovations are expected to be completed by the late spring.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Major renovations include the Media Innovation Center, the Duane L. Jones Recital Hall, and the Clark Athletic Fields and Gym.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">The original proposal for the Media Innovation Center (MIC) “was submitted as far back as 2016,” said Professor Ozgur Akgun, MIC manager and assistant professor American Studies/Media and Communications. “Because of COVID, for instance, we lost almost two years working on this project.”&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">“There have many complications,” said Samara Smith, MIC co-director and associate professor American Studies/Media and Communications. “Finding the right vendors and suppliers and dealing with state rules around how awards are allocated can take time.”&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">With a grant of $1.125 million from the Dormitory Authority of New York State, MIC’s G wing renovation will have a classroom-sized control room and new TV studio equipment and lighting to compare to a professional TV or film studio. As a hub for media and communications learning, the center will have an on-site reception area with a help desk, an equipment check out window, lounge, teaching and meeting spaces. There will also be “a small studio with a flexible teaching lab where students can learn virtual reality and other emerging media, which can also accommodate talks and small screenings,” Smith said.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">The renovation “will showcase and promote advancement in media communication arts and fully prepare students for professions in TV&nbsp;and media arts,” said Ray Maggiore, assistant vice president for capital planning, whose dedicated supervision along with Philip Joseph, site representative for capital planning, was essential to the renovation.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">“I am excited, it looks really good!” said Smith, who was part of the renovation team with Akgun and professors Laura Chipley and Lisa Payton. “I think it’s going to be such a lovely space for students to gather and there is going to be a hallway where we can showcase Old Westbury alumni and student work.”&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">In addition, as part of the library’s renovation, a podcasting facility was recently completed with the help of Akgun and Joe Manfredi, station&nbsp;manager, Old Westbury Web Radio and lecturer in the American Studies/Media and Communications Department. It was a part of the last phase of the library’s capital project.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">“The Duane L. Jones Recital Hall was reimagined as a state of the art multi-purpose venue that can accommodate speakers, dance, music performances, a catwalk, control booth, with professional visual equipment and acoustics,” Maggiore said. “When finished it will host open houses, events, and showcase opportunities for education in the arts. It will provide a lasting impression for years to come.”&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">The Maguire Theatre received new seating and carpeting over the&nbsp;past year.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">“The Clark athletic fields are&nbsp;being improved from the conditions they were in before the site was used” as a temporary healthcare facility by New York State to combat Covid 19, Maggiore said. “The baseball and softball fields will have all new lighting and scoreboards&#8230;The upper and lower soccer fields were regraded for better drainage and are newly sod with an automated sprinkler system.”</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">The gymnasium and Clark building are being restored to their condition before they were converted for vaccination use.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Additional on-going campus renovations include Atrium renovations to comply with the Americans with&nbsp;Disabilities Act whereby six bathroom modifications as well a replacements of all railing on the balconies and stairs are expected to be completed by the late spring; the replacement of the campus main power supply room in the Campus Center, which will be ongoing past the spring of 2023; replacement of the Gate B Roadway, tentatively scheduled for completion by the end of ‘23; and renovation of the Natural Science Building, tentatively scheduled to start in the summer of 2023.&nbsp;</p>\n', NULL, 'APPROVED', 'TC527', NULL, '2022-12-05 16:03:47', 0, 'After delays caused by Covid, problems with supply chains, and even the weather, significant campus renovations are expected to be completed by the late spring.  Major renovations include the Media Innovation Center, the Duane L. Jones Recital Hall, and the Clark Athletic Fields and Gym.  The original proposal for the Media Innovation Center (MIC) “was…\n', NULL, NULL, 1),
('ed60a548-61ed-11f1-98fa-60cf847a2597', 'article', 'Library Acts to Preserve College’s History', 'library-acts-to-preserve-colleges-history', NULL, '<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" src=\"uploads/image-85.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-7365\" width=\"359\" height=\"479\" srcset=\"https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/image-85.png 600w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/image-85-450x600.png 450w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/image-85-225x300.png 225w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 359px) 100vw, 359px\" /><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Photo Credit: Christina DeVirgilio</figcaption></figure>\n</div>\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">“We have a unique, interesting history that has been neglected,” said Antonia DiGregorio, SUNY OW’s director of library services. “But little has been done to preserve it.” This will soon change.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Christa DeVirgilio, digital initiative and archives librarian, said she expects to receive a grant early next year of about $4,000 from the Long Island Library Resource Council to digitize nearly all the paper copies of&nbsp;<em>The Catalyst&nbsp;</em>newspaper.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Prior to 1974, there were mimeographed copies called&nbsp;<em>The Gadfly&nbsp;</em>and&nbsp;<em>Abraxas</em>. The digitization will begin from 1974 when the newspaper was officially approved by the faculty senate until 2010 when the use of color started to be used, which requires more costly scans, and&nbsp;when some Internet versions began to be available.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">The library may apply for an additional grant to preserve copies of the&nbsp;paper edition from 2010 and beyond. The grant stipulates that the collection has to be accessible and available to the public in one of the digital platforms managed by the various NY library councils.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Digital collections created with these&nbsp;funds will be accessible online without charge to students, teachers, scholars, and citizens of New York State. All digitized assets must be contributed to New York heritage or New York historic news- papers.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">They will also be available on the library website. The benefits of having this collection on these platforms is that they will be discoverable and searchable from any search engine by any person on any continent. An estimated 8,000&nbsp;images have to be digitized. All words will be searchable. The collection should be available to the public by the end of 2023.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Future projects will include material from the files of the late president Dr. Calvin O. Butts III as well as yearbooks, faculty and staff newsletters, college cat- alogues, brochures from the art gallery, the Recital Hall, and the Maguire Theatre as well as material from the Office of Communications and College Relations, which maintains its own archive.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">“I am excited to get this project going as I recently found evidence of a similar project that was never funded and inevitably abandoned by a previous librarian around the year 2000, “ said DeVirgilio.&nbsp;</p>\n', NULL, 'APPROVED', 'TC527', NULL, '2022-12-05 15:54:44', 0, '“We have a unique, interesting history that has been neglected,” said Antonia DiGregorio, SUNY OW’s director of library services. “But little has been done to preserve it.” This will soon change. Christa DeVirgilio, digital initiative and archives librarian, said she expects to receive a grant early next year of about $4,000 from the Long Island…\n', NULL, NULL, 1),
('ed60ed3e-61ed-11f1-98fa-60cf847a2597', 'article', 'The Student Health Center at SUNY Old Westbury', 'the-student-health-center-at-suny-old-westbury', NULL, '<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" src=\"uploads/image-87.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-7373\" width=\"419\" height=\"210\" srcset=\"https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/image-87.png 318w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/image-87-300x150.png 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 419px) 100vw, 419px\" /><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Photo Credit:Adele Gutierrez</figcaption></figure>\n</div>\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Photograph from left to right: Marianne Spencer, Cristine Tesoriero, Dr. Margaret Sikhism, Faylon Robinson, Adele Gutierrez, Dr. Ellen Feit, Anna Sbano, and Kristen Mantikas. </p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">SUNY Old Westbury’s Student Health Center is a resource available to all registered students. It promotes wellness by providing knowledge about disease prevention, treatment, and maintenance of healthy lifestyle habits. The Center is located in the I-Wing of the Campus Center.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">According to Adele Gutierrez, the nurse coordinator, “The mission of the Student Health Center is ensuring the accessibility and delivery of high-quality clinical services in an inclusive and respectful environment, [promoting] wellness through education, disease prevention, treatment, and maintenance of healthy lifestyle practices.”</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">The Student Health Center is adding great value to the Old Westbury community. It allows students to experience comfort in knowing that a safety net for basic healthcare exists for them.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Gutierrez said that students frequently visit the Student Health Center because they are “not feeling well, [they need assistance with] sexual &amp; reproductive health, [they have] cold symptoms, and ear infections.”</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">The Student Health Center provides clinical and special services such as triages and consultations, physical examinations, and limited laboratory testing. The center also provides STI screening, testing, and treatment, as well as HIV testing and counseling. The Northeast College of Health Sciences provides the Old Westbury community with chiropractic care.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">All students also have access to gynecological, sexual, and reproductive health services. Those services included history and medical evaluations, birth control prescriptions, sexual and reproductive physicals for all genders, PAP smears, health education and counseling, and hemoglobin and routine urinalysis. There is a fee of $25 for PAP smears for people over the age of 21. The Center charges $5 for each pregnancy test and $15 for the emergency care on site. The Student Health Center provides over the counter medication and the plan B pill for students.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">The flu shots and the COVID-19 vaccines are offered, as well, for all students.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Students are encouraged to always bring their insurance information to campus. They are also encouraged to keep track of any medication they are taking and have their vaccines up to date.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">The facility has one Nurse, Faylon Robinson; one Nurse Coordinator, Adele Gutierrez; one Nurse Practitioner, Margaret Sukhram; one Senior Medical Advisor, Ellen Feit; two Physicians, Jane Swedler and Greta Rainsford; one Secretary, Marianne Spencer; one Office Assistant, Kristen Mantikas; and one Director, Cristine Tesoriero.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">During the fall and spring semesters, students can visit the Student Health Center on Mondays and Tuesdays between 8:00 a.m. and 7:00 p.m., and Wednesdays, Thursdays, and Fridays between 8:00 a.m. and 5:00 p.m..</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">To make an appointment with the chiropractor, please call (516) 796-4800. For all sexual exams, a prescreening is required, so you must call (516) 876-3250 to schedule an appointment.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">For more information, please visit <a href=\"http://www.oldwestbury.edu/\">www.oldwestbury.edu</a>. You can also contact the Student Health Center via email at <a>studenthealth@oldwestbury.edu</a> or call (516) 876-3250.</p>\n', NULL, 'APPROVED', 'LG167', NULL, '2022-12-05 16:11:28', 0, 'Photograph from left to right: Marianne Spencer, Cristine Tesoriero, Dr. Margaret Sikhism, Faylon Robinson, Adele Gutierrez, Dr. Ellen Feit, Anna Sbano, and Kristen Mantikas.  SUNY Old Westbury’s Student Health Center is a resource available to all registered students. It promotes wellness by providing knowledge about disease prevention, treatment, and maintenance of healthy lifestyle habits. The…\n', NULL, NULL, 1);
