('ed7f0366-61ed-11f1-98fa-60cf847a2597', 'article', 'Bad Bunny’s “Nadie Sabe Lo Que Va Pasar Mañana” ', 'bad-bunnys-nadie-sabe-lo-que-va-pasar-manana', NULL, '\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"640\" height=\"640\" src=\"uploads/image-300.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-8349\" style=\"aspect-ratio:1;width:325px;height:auto\" srcset=\"https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/image-300.png 640w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/image-300-600x600.png 600w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/image-300-70x70.png 70w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/image-300-300x300.png 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" /><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\"><sup>Photo Credit: <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://nam12.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fopen.spotify.com%2Falbum%2F4FftCsAcXXD1nFO9RFUNFO&amp;data=05%7C01%7Clgarci26%40oldwestbury.edu%7C339c802d0c864bd25c0108dbd567fec2%7Cf5089034f2334f12a71638b7f4904370%7C0%7C0%7C638338414863616701%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&amp;sdata=1KanXYfronLHGCk%2BpqQSrceIhR%2BJv7Ur6k5A7sh7epw%3D&amp;reserved=0\" target=\"_blank\">Spotify</a></sup></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">There is no doubt that Bad Bunny is one of the most popular artists in the world right now. In 2022, he captivated the world with his hit album Un Verano Sin Ti, making it the most streamed album of the year and solidifying himself as the biggest artist of the year. According to Spotify, Bad Bunny has been the most streamed artist for three years, from 2020-2022 on their platform, and he’s the only artist to ever do that. He’s also the fourth most listened to artist, with 80 million monthly listeners.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Incredibly, the Puerto Rican singer has surpassed numerous records with albums completely sung in spanish. Before the album, Bad Bunny had big collabs with many artists, such as Tainy, El Groupo Frontera, Travis Scott, The Weeknd and one of the biggest artists of the decade, Drake.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Earlier this year Bad Bunny released his first single of the new album, titled “Where She Goes.” This song caused a lot of controversy amongst Bad Bunny’s fans due to the song title being in English. Many felt that he was selling himself out to fit a more Americanized demographic, to match with his American and rumored girlfriend, Kendall Jenner. Despite that, the song was very successful. A few months later, he released his second single of the album, “Un Preview,” and on October 13, he released his new album, Nadie Sabe Qué Va Pasar Mañana.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">The album starts with the song “Nadie Sabe,” which is a message from Bad Bunny to his fans, the song is filled with disses against people who have criticized him. The songs, “Cybertruck” and “Where She Goes,” are very similar to “Jersey beats,” which I think Bad Bunny has excelled at, making very fun catchy songs.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">The song “Fina” has been loved by fans because it features another very popular Puerto Rican singer, Young Miko. Similarly, “Perro Negro” features Colombian singer, Feid, who is very loved by Latino fans. The whole Album is amazing and any fan of Bad Bunny would enjoy listening to it, I know I haven’t stopped!&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">The album is filled with many songs that are reminiscent of Bad Bunny’s old style of writing trap songs. Fans of the singer took to twitter to discuss the new album, and what he sings about. In the first song Bad Bunny sings, “Tu no eres mi fan real, por eso te tire el cellular,” which addresses the controversy of him throwing a fan’s phone earlier this year. Overall, the album is filled with many great songs, with different styles. My personal favorites are “Cybertruck” and “Monaco.”</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Bad Bunny has announced he’s going on tour in 2024. Fans all over the country have run to Ticketmaster to register for ticket sales. Ticketmaster has predicted that the tour is going to have an influx of people who want to buy a ticket to see the Puerto Rican singer in person.&nbsp;</p>\n', NULL, 'APPROVED', 'FR779', NULL, '2023-10-25 12:18:34', 0, 'There is no doubt that Bad Bunny is one of the most popular artists in the world right now. In 2022, he captivated the world with his hit album Un Verano Sin Ti, making it the most streamed album of the year and solidifying himself as the biggest artist of the year. According to Spotify,…\n', NULL, NULL, 1),
('ed7fbcc1-61ed-11f1-98fa-60cf847a2597', 'article', '“Down With The System”Serj Tankian Announces Memoir', 'down-with-the-systemserj-tankian-announces-memoir', NULL, '\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"300\" height=\"295\" src=\"uploads/image-301-300x295.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-8352\" style=\"aspect-ratio:1.015625;width:316px;height:auto\" srcset=\"https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/image-301-300x295.png 300w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/image-301-600x591.png 600w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/image-301-70x70.png 70w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/image-301-768x756.png 768w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/image-301.png 1170w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" /><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\"><sup>Photo Credit: Instagram @serjtankian.</sup></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">On October 24, the lead singer of the hard rock band “System Of A Down,” Serj Tankian, announced his first ever memoir on Instagram. The title of the memoir will be,&nbsp;<em>Down With the System</em>. The book, according to&nbsp;<a href=\"https://nam12.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.revolvermag.com%2Fculture%2Fsystem-downs-serj-tankian-announces-memoir-down-system&amp;data=05%7C01%7Clgarci26%40oldwestbury.edu%7C3fe601f57d5c4fcbb5ae08dbd567f3aa%7Cf5089034f2334f12a71638b7f4904370%7C0%7C0%7C638338414663302161%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&amp;sdata=mmHSu9Vu6Xvic78WsSjMApAFeiTu2w8cDUID77TodKA%3D&amp;reserved=0\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Revolver Magazine</a>, is set to release in May of 2024.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\"><a href=\"https://nam12.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.revolvermag.com%2Fculture%2Fsystem-downs-serj-tankian-announces-memoir-down-system&amp;data=05%7C01%7Clgarci26%40oldwestbury.edu%7C3fe601f57d5c4fcbb5ae08dbd567f3aa%7Cf5089034f2334f12a71638b7f4904370%7C0%7C0%7C638338414663458498%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&amp;sdata=etlLt4nrp7wbZrc3r0RBt4Adsm6zFk7%2B%2FZDq%2FSAwFOY%3D&amp;reserved=0\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Revolver Magazine</a>&nbsp;reported that the singer wants to delve more into his life outside of his band. Tankian describes the memoir as an “immigrant’s tale,” “an activist awakening,” and a “spiritual journey from darkness towards light.” Before moving to Los Angeles, California at age seven, Tankian was born to Armenian parents in Beirut, Lebanon and grew up hearing bombs dropping outside of his childhood home during the country’s civil war.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Tankian’s band “System Of A Down” was formed in Glendale, California in 1994, according to&nbsp;<a href=\"https://nam12.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.billboard.com%2Fartist%2Fsystem-of-a-down%2F&amp;data=05%7C01%7Clgarci26%40oldwestbury.edu%7C3fe601f57d5c4fcbb5ae08dbd567f3aa%7Cf5089034f2334f12a71638b7f4904370%7C0%7C0%7C638338414663458498%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&amp;sdata=dRHzZIszr01xGuPKlONm6e2Xps3z1h%2F1NgCvYUDBsBo%3D&amp;reserved=0\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\"><em>Billboard</em></a><em>.&nbsp;</em>The band is made up of Serj Tankian (lead singer), Daron Malakian (guitarist), Shavo Odadjian (bass guitarist), and John Dolmayan (drummer). The band members are all of Armenian descent and infuse sounds of their cultural music with heavy rock and socially conscious and politically charged lyrics. The band built a strong following by word of mouth in Los Angeles. In 1998, they released their self titled debut album,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://nam12.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.allmusic.com%2Fartist%2Fsystem-of-a-down-mn0000005501%2Fbiography&amp;data=05%7C01%7Clgarci26%40oldwestbury.edu%7C3fe601f57d5c4fcbb5ae08dbd567f3aa%7Cf5089034f2334f12a71638b7f4904370%7C0%7C0%7C638338414663458498%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&amp;sdata=KNaBG1bSbEgXdaMdZfLE%2BlxsshTq%2BEk9pAMzgpzL34k%3D&amp;reserved=0\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">AllMusic&nbsp;</a>wrote.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Tankian and the band’s eponymous album produced multiple hits with “Sugar,” and “Spiders.” The band eventually went platinum and in September 2001, a week before 9/11, the band released the more ambitious album, “Toxicity.” The album features the lead single “Chop Suey!” which mentions the word suicide. According to&nbsp;<a href=\"https://nam12.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fpitchfork.com%2Freviews%2Falbums%2Fsystem-of-a-down-toxicity%2F&amp;data=05%7C01%7Clgarci26%40oldwestbury.edu%7C3fe601f57d5c4fcbb5ae08dbd567f3aa%7Cf5089034f2334f12a71638b7f4904370%7C0%7C0%7C638338414663458498%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&amp;sdata=KKj9UVlxF%2B%2FDwvN7XBbp4I56RqpTwuQq1grbzc2QQ%2F8%3D&amp;reserved=0\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Pitchfork</a>, this landed the song on a list of songs to avoid playing in the wake of the attacks on the World Trade Center.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Living in California, Tankian immersed himself in the SoCal community of “Little Armenia,” where he learned a lot about the 1915 Armenian genocide that his ancestors faced. The “Toxicity” album features a song titled, “X,” in which they bring awareness to the genocide. In verse two of the song, Tankian sings, “Show your people, show your people how we died.”&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">According to&nbsp;<a href=\"https://nam12.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fgsp.yale.edu%2Fcase-studies%2Farmenian-genocide&amp;data=05%7C01%7Clgarci26%40oldwestbury.edu%7C3fe601f57d5c4fcbb5ae08dbd567f3aa%7Cf5089034f2334f12a71638b7f4904370%7C0%7C0%7C638338414663458498%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&amp;sdata=jMvpzTCxJRBvJekdJmJfOyj1jsOvRz%2F5Ahogr7nqmq0%3D&amp;reserved=0\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Yale University</a>, in 1915, with the outbreak of World War I, the Young Turk government drove Armenians out of their homes. Although the figures are unreliable, it’s reported by many historians that between 800,000 and one million Armenians were killed.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Bringing awareness to social and political issues has been a big part of the singer’s career, according to the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://nam12.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebookseller.com%2Frights%2Fheadline-scoops-system-of-a-down-lead-singer-tankians-memoir&amp;data=05%7C01%7Clgarci26%40oldwestbury.edu%7C3fe601f57d5c4fcbb5ae08dbd567f3aa%7Cf5089034f2334f12a71638b7f4904370%7C0%7C0%7C638338414663458498%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&amp;sdata=1xASglQHRTwhfmUJFl2xwojEzLqHJCUB5EaTWnm%2F7OQ%3D&amp;reserved=0\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">BookSeller</a>. Alongside the guitarist Tom Morello, Tankian co-founded the non-profit organization, Axis of Justice. The point of the organization is to bring together musicians, music fans, and grassroots political organizations for social justice.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">In his memoir, Tankian overall hopes to share other aspects of his life; he has composed scores for film and television series, published poetry, created paintings, and produced documentaries.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Tankian said, “I’ve had a blast working on this accidentally hatched philosophical memoir as it’s given me the unique opportunity to dive deep into my family history, my own motivations from a young age, and lessons I didn’t know I had learned,”&nbsp;<a href=\"https://nam12.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebookseller.com%2Frights%2Fheadline-scoops-system-of-a-down-lead-singer-tankians-memoir&amp;data=05%7C01%7Clgarci26%40oldwestbury.edu%7C3fe601f57d5c4fcbb5ae08dbd567f3aa%7Cf5089034f2334f12a71638b7f4904370%7C0%7C0%7C638338414663458498%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&amp;sdata=1xASglQHRTwhfmUJFl2xwojEzLqHJCUB5EaTWnm%2F7OQ%3D&amp;reserved=0\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">BookSeller</a>&nbsp;reported.</p>\n', NULL, 'APPROVED', 'KJ262', NULL, '2023-10-25 12:21:27', 0, 'On October 24, the lead singer of the hard rock band “System Of A Down,” Serj Tankian, announced his first ever memoir on Instagram. The title of the memoir will be, Down With the System. The book, according to Revolver Magazine, is set to release in May of 2024.  Revolver Magazine reported that the singer wants to delve…\n', NULL, NULL, 1),
('ed830165-61ed-11f1-98fa-60cf847a2597', 'video', 'Listen to New Media Beat!', 'listen-to-new-media-beat', NULL, '<p><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter wp-image-8367 size-large\" src=\"uploads/NMB-4-PIne-NMB-Banner-scaled-e1698524279647-1200x312.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"610\" height=\"158\" srcset=\"https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/NMB-4-PIne-NMB-Banner-scaled-e1698524279647-1200x312.jpg 1200w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/NMB-4-PIne-NMB-Banner-scaled-e1698524279647-600x156.jpg 600w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/NMB-4-PIne-NMB-Banner-scaled-e1698524279647-768x200.jpg 768w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/NMB-4-PIne-NMB-Banner-scaled-e1698524279647-1536x399.jpg 1536w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/NMB-4-PIne-NMB-Banner-scaled-e1698524279647-2048x532.jpg 2048w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/NMB-4-PIne-NMB-Banner-scaled-e1698524279647-300x78.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 610px) 100vw, 610px\" /></p>\n<audio class=\"wp-audio-shortcode\" id=\"audio-8364-1\" preload=\"none\" style=\"width: 100%;\" controls=\"controls\"><source type=\"audio/mpeg\" src=\"uploads/NMB-4-Web-2023-10-26.mp3?_=1\" /><a href=\"uploads/NMB-4-Web-2023-10-26.mp3\">uploads/NMB-4-Web-2023-10-26.mp3</a></audio>\n<h2> </h2>\n<h2><strong>This Week on New Media Beat:</strong></h2>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>South Korea:</strong> Virtual K-Pop!</li>\n<li><strong>Pakistan:</strong> Press Freedom in Jeopardy?</li>\n<li><strong>Italy: </strong>Who Reads the Papers?</li>\n<li><strong>China: </strong>&#8216;Spicy Milk&#8217; on Social Media?</li>\n<li><strong>UK: </strong>Should Celebrities Accused of Abuse Be Demonetized?</li>\n<li><strong>African Football: </strong>Who Controls the Broadcast Rights?</li>\n</ul>\n<p><!-- /wp:post-content --></p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --><br />The NMB Podcast streams live on <a href=\"http://www.owwrny.org/\">Old Westbury Web Radio</a> Thursdays from 10:00-11:00 AM EST.  Can&#8217;t listen live? Our podcast will be <a href=\"https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/?cat=17\">posted</a> for your listening pleasure every Friday afternoon.<!-- /wp:paragraph --><br /><br />NMB is co-produced by Alex Hajko &amp; Demetrick Hylton. Our engineer is Demetrik Hylton.  Our hosts are Anthony Bogorodovsky and Alyssa Rosano.<!-- /wp:paragraph --><br /><br /><a href=\"https://www.newmediabeat.org/\"><strong>New Media Beat</strong></a> covers new media news from around the world. NMB is a production of  Media Studies students from the <a href=\"https://www.oldwestbury.edu/\" target=\"_self\" rel=\"noopener\">SUNY College @ Old Westbury.</a>   We scour the web for news about about the world of media, journalism and technology.<!-- /wp:paragraph --><br /><br />Follow<strong> <a href=\"https://twitter.com/OWWRGMN\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">@OWWRGMN</a></strong> for a curated feed of the latest new media news for aspiring media professionals. <!-- /wp:paragraph --><br /><!-- wp:paragraph --><br /><br /><a href=\"https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/NMB-4-Pine-NMB-Nations-Rectangle-Web.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-6400\" src=\"https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/NMB-4-Pine-NMB-Nations-Rectangle-Web.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1210\" height=\"908\" /></a></p>\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p class=\"\"></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', NULL, 'APPROVED', 'TC527', NULL, '2023-10-28 16:49:52', 0, '  This Week on New Media Beat: South Korea: Virtual K-Pop! Pakistan: Press Freedom in Jeopardy? Italy: Who Reads the Papers? China: ‘Spicy Milk’ on Social Media? UK: Should Celebrities Accused of Abuse Be Demonetized? African Football: Who Controls the Broadcast Rights? The NMB Podcast streams live on Old Westbury Web Radio Thursdays from 10:00-11:00 AM EST.  Can’t…\n', NULL, NULL, 15),
('ed89f210-61ed-11f1-98fa-60cf847a2597', 'article', 'Killers of the Flower Moon Review', 'killers-of-the-flower-moon-review', NULL, '\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1200\" height=\"801\" src=\"uploads/image-305-1200x801.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-8386\" style=\"aspect-ratio:1.4981273408239701;width:485px;height:auto\" srcset=\"https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/image-305-1200x801.png 1200w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/image-305-600x401.png 600w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/image-305-768x513.png 768w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/image-305-1536x1025.png 1536w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/image-305-300x200.png 300w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/image-305.png 1600w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" /><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\"><sup>Left to right; Lily Gladstone, Robert De Niro, Leonardo DiCaprio, in the film.</sup></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\"><em>Killers of the Flower Moon</em>&nbsp;is director Martin Scorsese’s newest feature film, starring long time collaborators Leonardo DiCaprio, Robert DeNiro, and newcomer Lily Gladstone. The film is based on David Grann’s novel of the same name, and follows the systemic murders of the Osage people in Oklahoma during the 1920s. Both the film and the book are a telling of real historical events.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">The Osage are a group of Native Americans that became infamous for their massive wealth as a result of oil that lay beneath their land, as per the film, the book, and Wikipedia. During the early 1900s, Osage started mysteriously dying and their white husbands, wives, and caretakers started getting exponentially richer. This event would come to be called the “Reign of Terror,” and was masterminded by businessman William Hale and his oil baron cronies.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">The film and the book are great companion pieces, and you should not dismiss one just because you have seen or read the other. David Grann’s novel is a harrowing read and is insightful into other atrocities committed against the Osage, and Native Americans as a whole, by American settlers.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">The film premiered at the 76th Cannes Film Festival earlier this year to rave reviews and a&nbsp;<a href=\"https://nam12.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F2023%2Ffilm%2Fnews%2Fkillers-of-the-flower-moon-cannes-standing-ovation-scorsese-dicaprio-1235618650%2F&amp;data=05%7C01%7Clgarci26%40oldwestbury.edu%7Cd971ea50c91944b9d87508dbda60e85d%7Cf5089034f2334f12a71638b7f4904370%7C0%7C0%7C638343881986841953%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&amp;sdata=vB1xl74ah5toieYrIEp66olsDlirL1cnej5KYKQsgA8%3D&amp;reserved=0\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">nine minute standing ovation</a>. From the get-go, Scorsese was very open about how he worked with the Osage people to tell the story as accurately as possible. “This was an amazing experience,” he told&nbsp;<a href=\"https://nam12.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F2023%2Ffilm%2Fnews%2Fkillers-of-the-flower-moon-cannes-standing-ovation-scorsese-dicaprio-1235618650%2F&amp;data=05%7C01%7Clgarci26%40oldwestbury.edu%7Cd971ea50c91944b9d87508dbda60e85d%7Cf5089034f2334f12a71638b7f4904370%7C0%7C0%7C638343881986841953%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&amp;sdata=vB1xl74ah5toieYrIEp66olsDlirL1cnej5KYKQsgA8%3D&amp;reserved=0\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Variety</a>. “We lived in that world.” The film was shot in Osage County, Oklahoma.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">From the first moments of the film you can understand the weight of what you are about to witness. It opens with a small scene depicting a ritual; Osage sat around in a circle, crying goodbye to their children who will not learn their ways but instead, “learn the ways of the white people.” This is immediately juxtaposed by clips of Osage wearing fine clothes, jewels, and driving fancy cars.</p>\n', NULL, 'APPROVED', 'VA153', NULL, '2023-10-31 18:56:59', 0, 'Killers of the Flower Moon is director Martin Scorsese’s newest feature film, starring long time collaborators Leonardo DiCaprio, Robert DeNiro, and newcomer Lily Gladstone. The film is based on David Grann’s novel of the same name, and follows the systemic murders of the Osage people in Oklahoma during the 1920s. Both the film and the book…\n', NULL, NULL, 1),
('ed8ac9f3-61ed-11f1-98fa-60cf847a2597', 'podcast', 'Ear Candy: Media News from New Media Beat!', 'ear-candy-media-news-from-new-media-beat', NULL, '<p><a href=\"https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/NMB-5-Orange-Cone-Rectangle-scaled.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-6459\" src=\"https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/NMB-5-Orange-Cone-Rectangle-scaled.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1991\" /></a></p>\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-audio\"><audio controls src=\"https://www.oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/NMB-5-Web-2023-11-02.mp3\"></audio></figure>\n\n\n<h2><strong>This Week on New Media Beat:</strong></h2>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>UK:</strong> Who Gets the News on Social?</li>\n<li><strong>Australia:</strong> Why Did the eSafety Commissioner Fine X?</li>\n<li><strong>Gaza: </strong>Can Social Be Trusted for War News?</li>\n<li><strong>Russia: </strong>Can Film-Makers Make Independent Movies?</li>\n<li><strong>Venezuela: </strong>Independent News or Censorship?</li>\n<li><strong>Cuba: </strong>Who Controls the Media?</li>\n<li><strong>India: </strong>Are Internet Freedoms Being Restricted?</li>\n<li><strong>Sudan at war: </strong> AI Voice-Clone Impersonates Omar al-Bashir on TikTok?</li>\n</ul>\n<p><!-- /wp:post-content --></p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --></p>\n<p>The NMB Podcast streams live on <a href=\"http://www.owwrny.org/\">Old Westbury Web Radio</a> Thursdays from 10:00-11:00 AM EST.  Can&#8217;t listen live? Our podcast will be <a href=\"https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/?cat=17\">posted</a> for your listening pleasure every Friday afternoon. NMB is co-produced by Alex Hajko &amp; Aidan Bongiorno. Our engineer is Alex Hajko.  Our hosts are Judy Imasogie and Amadi Lee-Kane.</p>\n<p><!-- /wp:paragraph --></p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.newmediabeat.org/\"><strong>New Media Beat</strong></a> covers new media news from around the world. NMB is a production of  Media Studies students from the <a href=\"https://www.oldwestbury.edu/\" target=\"_self\" rel=\"noopener\">SUNY College @ Old Westbury.</a>   We scour the web for news about about the world of media, journalism and technology.</p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --></p>\n<p>Follow<strong> <a href=\"https://twitter.com/OWWRGMN\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">@OWWRGMN</a></strong> for a curated feed of the latest new media news for aspiring media professionals.</p>\n<p><!-- /wp:paragraph --></p>\n\n<!-- wp:post-featured-image /-->', NULL, 'APPROVED', 'TC527', NULL, '2023-11-03 13:07:19', 0, 'This Week on New Media Beat: UK: Who Gets the News on Social? Australia: Why Did the eSafety Commissioner Fine X? Gaza: Can Social Be Trusted for War News? Russia: Can Film-Makers Make Independent Movies? Venezuela: Independent News or Censorship? Cuba: Who Controls the Media? India: Are Internet Freedoms Being Restricted? Sudan at war:  AI Voice-Clone Impersonates Omar al-Bashir on…\n', NULL, NULL, 1),
('ed8bdfd6-61ed-11f1-98fa-60cf847a2597', 'article', 'Repairing the Natural Sciences Building', 'repairingthe-naturalsciencesbuilding', NULL, '\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1200\" height=\"889\" src=\"uploads/Screenshot-2023-11-03-at-5.34.24-PM-1200x889.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-8436\" style=\"aspect-ratio:1.3491620111731844;width:436px;height:auto\" srcset=\"https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Screenshot-2023-11-03-at-5.34.24-PM-1200x889.png 1200w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Screenshot-2023-11-03-at-5.34.24-PM-600x445.png 600w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Screenshot-2023-11-03-at-5.34.24-PM-768x569.png 768w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Screenshot-2023-11-03-at-5.34.24-PM-1536x1138.png 1536w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Screenshot-2023-11-03-at-5.34.24-PM-300x222.png 300w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Screenshot-2023-11-03-at-5.34.24-PM.png 1932w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" /><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\"><sup>The Natural Sciences Building.<br>Photo Credit: Samuel Khaytman</sup></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">The Natural Sciences Building is in disrepair. After several years of delays, a multi-year plan to renovate the Natural Sciences Building (NSB) will finally begin in the summer of 2024. The plan is to expand the building and add upgrades to all the teaching and research spaces.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Plans for the NSB began in 2018 and were completed in 2020. However, the plans weren’t fully funded and slowed due to COVID-19-related expenses.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">The building was constructed in 1985 as a “teaching and research facility for biological sciences, chemistry, physics, and public health programs.”</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">The roof and the ventilation and air-conditioning system (HVAC) needs fixing to minimize condensation and prevent leaks, ceilings and floor tiles are damaged, the building’s exterior needs patching to improve insulation and prevent rodents and insects from entering (in process); regular maintenance is required by an exterminator (also in process); and outdated and broken light fixtures (underway in lab spaces) need to be replaced.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">There are back-up power issues, as well. Sometimes, these interfere with experiments.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"226\" height=\"300\" src=\"uploads/Screenshot-2023-11-03-at-5.34.58-PM-226x300.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-8437\" style=\"aspect-ratio:0.75390625;width:280px;height:auto\" srcset=\"https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Screenshot-2023-11-03-at-5.34.58-PM-226x300.png 226w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Screenshot-2023-11-03-at-5.34.58-PM-452x600.png 452w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Screenshot-2023-11-03-at-5.34.58-PM-905x1200.png 905w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Screenshot-2023-11-03-at-5.34.58-PM-768x1019.png 768w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Screenshot-2023-11-03-at-5.34.58-PM.png 1084w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 226px) 100vw, 226px\" /><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\"><sup>Gaps in the ceiling.<br>Photo Credit: Samuel Khaytman</sup></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Dr. Sarah Smith, an Associate Professor of Public Health, said that the main way her students are affected by the building’s disrepair is by “the heat and the cold.” Students and faculty alike have complained about the building’s unpredictable temperatures. Dr. Smith said that a couple weeks ago that the inside of the building was “really hot.” In fact, it was “too hot to concentrate.”</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Currently, faculty must move their classrooms around. Dr.Smith said sometimes she teaches her classes in the library or the New Academic Building (NAB). The constant changing of classrooms has caused confusion among students.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Dr. Smith added, “We’ve been seeing plans for as long as I’ve been here for eight years. So really, we would just love for those things to actually Happen…we are just sick of waiting.” She said, “Students are always the priority, but we also need to think about the workplace conditions and safety for our faculty, staff, and administration.”</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">On September 21, the NSB Chairs, Eric Doucet (Lab Manager), and Cheryl Wilson (Dean of the School of Arts &amp; Sciences), took part in a meeting that included the president, provost, the chief financial officer, and the heads of the facilities and capital departments on the current state of the NSB. At the meeting, the group discussed how to address the problems.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">During the meeting, the group complained about biology students who may not have an authentic STEM experience. However, in the fall of 2024, all lecture classes will be held at the NAB, Campus Center, or the Library. Laboratory classes will continue to be held in the NSB for 2024-2025. In fall 2025, laboratory classes will be moved into modern, and upgraded modular labs located next to the NSB.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1200\" height=\"675\" src=\"uploads/Screenshot-2023-11-03-at-5.31.49-PM-1200x675.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-8438\" style=\"aspect-ratio:1.7766599597585513;width:376px;height:auto\" srcset=\"https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Screenshot-2023-11-03-at-5.31.49-PM-1200x675.png 1200w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Screenshot-2023-11-03-at-5.31.49-PM-600x338.png 600w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Screenshot-2023-11-03-at-5.31.49-PM-768x432.png 768w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Screenshot-2023-11-03-at-5.31.49-PM-1536x865.png 1536w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Screenshot-2023-11-03-at-5.31.49-PM-300x169.png 300w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Screenshot-2023-11-03-at-5.31.49-PM.png 1766w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" /><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\"><sup>Planned instructional spaces in the NSB.<br>Photo Credit: SUNY OW Capital Planning</sup></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">The NSB was built in 1985. The large,multidisciplinary laboratory fostered collaboration amongst students. However, with the increase in the number of students, several classes have run simultaneously, within this undivided space.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Phase One of construction is set to begin in the summer of 2024, starting with renovations on the first floor labs and support areas. Ray Maggiore, Assistant Vice President of Capital Planning, said, “Summer is always the best way to do it.” Maggiore hopes it will take one to one and a half years to complete.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Due to the construction, half of  the Student Union parking lot will be closed for installation of geothermal wells under the lot. It will be closed until the wells are completed and be ready for parking again. The other half of the lot will be closed for the rest of the construction. The purpose of the geothermal wells is to reduce the existing building’s carbon footprint by over fifty percent.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">During this time, utility preparations (power, sewer, water, gas), an emergency generator for the modular labs, and a vivarium will be built adjacent to the NSBand old basketball courts. </p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">The modular labs will include superpiety areas, and the foundations and utilities of the modular assembly will include a decorative exterior facade, exterior landscaping, stairs, and accessible ramp. There are also talks of creating a temporary greenhouse.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">It’s unclear when Phase Two will begin, but it’ll include 40,000 square feet of new building additions. The plans for Phase Three include renovating the second floor, the ground-floor research and vivarium, classrooms, and the lecture hall. Maggiore said the science building will lose about four classrooms once construction starts.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">OW also plans to create new STEM Community spaces at Woodlands 5. Additions to the STEM center will include makerspace on the ground floor, a 3D modeling lab, and support offices. Students will have opportunities to take part in living-learning communities, work alongside faculty on independent and grant-funded projects, and pursue interdisciplinary research and creative activities.<br></p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\"></p>\n', NULL, 'APPROVED', 'FR779', NULL, '2023-11-03 14:26:39', 0, 'The Natural Sciences Building is in disrepair. After several years of delays, a multi-year plan to renovate the Natural Sciences Building (NSB) will finally begin in the summer of 2024. The plan is to expand the building and add upgrades to all the teaching and research spaces. Plans for the NSB began in 2018 and…\n', NULL, NULL, 1),
('ed8df860-61ed-11f1-98fa-60cf847a2597', 'article', 'Peace be Still', 'peace-be-still', NULL, '\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"246\" height=\"320\" src=\"uploads/image-315.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-8450\" srcset=\"https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/image-315.png 246w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/image-315-231x300.png 231w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 246px) 100vw, 246px\" /><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\"><sup>Artwork by Liselle Power.</sup></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\"><br>Where is my peace?</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Is it by the sea shore, where the waves crash?</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Is it up in the sky that’s blue,</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">with puffy white pillows,</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">that I can lay my head on and dream?</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Do I look for it, or is it hidden?</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">How can I find it if it’s still?</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">But, I will be still.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">As the trees that shades me and comfort me,</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">dances in the wind to speak to me.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">They said my peace is within me.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">That’s how I find it.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">It says nothing to me but just be still.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">But I am not running after it,</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">because it’s always here,</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">&nbsp;right where it belongs.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Just listen.</p>\n', NULL, 'APPROVED', 'LP665', NULL, '2023-11-05 15:16:31', 0, 'Where is my peace? Is it by the sea shore, where the waves crash? Is it up in the sky that’s blue, with puffy white pillows, that I can lay my head on and dream? Do I look for it, or is it hidden? How can I find it if it’s still? But, I will…\n', NULL, NULL, 1),
('ed8f5655-61ed-11f1-98fa-60cf847a2597', 'article', 'Super Mario Bros Wonder Game', 'super-mario-bros-wonder-game', NULL, '\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"408\" height=\"408\" src=\"uploads/image-316.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-8454\" style=\"aspect-ratio:1;width:317px;height:auto\" srcset=\"https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/image-316.png 408w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/image-316-70x70.png 70w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/image-316-300x300.png 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 408px) 100vw, 408px\" /><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\"><sup>Photo credit: IGN.com.</sup></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">This year marked&nbsp;the grand return of Nintendo’s iconic plumber in his most recent side-scrolling adventure, “Super Mario Bros. Wonder.” This game is considered to be the first new 2D Mario game since 2012. Recently released for Nintendo Switch, the game follows Mario and the gang, who visit the flower kingdom, until Bowser shows up and wreaks havoc on their floral world.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">While the story is vaguely similar to past Mario games, this game is a huge step forward for the franchise. The game provides a fresh updated visual style that breathes new life into the Mario Bros franchise. Starting with the character animation, all the playable characters feel more fluid and expressive.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">When Mario enters a pipe he reaches back for his hat and the Goombas have snot bubbles in their nostrils as they nap. When Mario turns into an elephant he squeezes his giant, round body into the warp pipes, and tries to make himself as small as possible, when crouching under a low row of blocks.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">This game also introduces a large roster of characters this time around. With almost 12 characters to choose from; besides Mario and Luigi, you can play as Peach, Daisy, two colored toads, Toadette, four Yoshi’s, and Nabbit from, “New Super Mario Bros U.” Unlike the previous games where it was just Mario, Luigi, blue Toad, and yellow Toad, this game changes the selection of characters up a bit, making it more fun for four player co-op.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">As for the level designs, this time around they&#8217;re more vibrant and atmospheric. Each level has a different unique style as you travel across the 6 main worlds throughout the game. All of the levels have a difficulty rating, ranging from 1 star levels which are the easiest, to 5 star levels which are the hardest.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">The goal of the levels is to collect 2 wonder seeds, while one of them is achieved at the end of each level, there’s another one that’s hidden and must be achieved through the game&#8217;s newest ability, the wonder flower. The wonder effects give off a colorful, trippy vibe that makes the experience more fun and whimsical. Some effects include warp pipes moving like caterpillars, singing piranha plants, and riding a bulrush stampede.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Besides the wonder flower, the game introduces three new power ups. The bubble Mario can blow large bubbles to take out enemies, and drill Mario can turn into a drill to dig under small spaces, and on the ceiling. But, the biggest new power up introduced is the Elephant fruit, which turns Mario into a strong and mighty elephant. With this ability, Mario can use his trunk to launch small enemies into the air, and it also allows him to hold water.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">“Super Mario Bros. Wonder” is truly the comeback of 2D Mario. It feels more colorful, alive, and creative unpredictably. This game shows that Nintendo still has what it takes to deliver a game that brings back a nostalgic sense of joy. It’s another fine masterpiece in the Mario franchise and it’s without a doubt the best Mario game in years. &nbsp;</p>\n', NULL, 'APPROVED', 'AB740', NULL, '2023-11-05 21:26:58', 0, 'This year marked the grand return of Nintendo’s iconic plumber in his most recent side-scrolling adventure, “Super Mario Bros. Wonder.” This game is considered to be the first new 2D Mario game since 2012. Recently released for Nintendo Switch, the game follows Mario and the gang, who visit the flower kingdom, until Bowser shows up and…\n', NULL, NULL, 1);
INSERT INTO `content` (`id`, `type`, `title`, `slug`, `description`, `content`, `url`, `approval_status`, `author_id`, `editor_id`, `created_at`, `is_featured`, `excerpt`, `video_url`, `featured_image`, `category_id`) VALUES
('ed904cff-61ed-11f1-98fa-60cf847a2597', 'article', 'What’s Happening in Sudan: The War and Crisis Explained', 'whats-happening-in-sudan-the-war-and-crisis-explained', NULL, '\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"300\" height=\"136\" src=\"uploads/image-319-300x136.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-8469\" style=\"width:564px;height:auto\" srcset=\"https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/image-319-300x136.png 300w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/image-319-600x272.png 600w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/image-319-768x348.png 768w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/image-319.png 1170w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" /><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\"><sup>Displaced people arriving in South Sudan from Sudan through the Joda border crossing. <br>Photo Credit: UNHCR/Ala Kheir.</sup></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">The events taking place in Israel and Palestine have brought other situations to light, such as what is happening in the&nbsp; Sudan.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">In Khartoum, Sudan, according to&nbsp;<a href=\"https://nam12.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fabcnews.go.com%2FInternational%2Fsudan-conflict-2023-explained%2Fstory%3Fid%3D98897649&amp;data=05%7C01%7Clgarci26%40oldwestbury.edu%7C9473ca9c4f9147bc303508dbe173a005%7Cf5089034f2334f12a71638b7f4904370%7C0%7C0%7C638351658938414600%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&amp;sdata=tuEHd3nbA4rrPMUX8LR81lOHm7fTt%2FlDlSOmjZaNCQc%3D&amp;reserved=0\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">ABCNews</a>, fighting erupted on April 15, 2023 in light of weeks of tension between General Abdel-Fattah Burhan, the commander of the Sudanese Armed Forces (SAF); and General Mohammed Hamdan Dagalo, the head of the Rapid Support Forces (RSF).&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Prior to the conflict between the two generals, in 2019, the authoritarian leader Omar al-Bashir, who ruled from 1993 to 2019, was removed from his position. The removal of al-Bashir sparked hope that Sudan would return to civilian rule. However, Burhan and Dagalo, who used to be allies according to&nbsp;<a href=\"https://nam12.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fabcnews.go.com%2FInternational%2Fsudan-conflict-2023-explained%2Fstory%3Fid%3D98897649&amp;data=05%7C01%7Clgarci26%40oldwestbury.edu%7C9473ca9c4f9147bc303508dbe173a005%7Cf5089034f2334f12a71638b7f4904370%7C0%7C0%7C638351658938414600%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&amp;sdata=tuEHd3nbA4rrPMUX8LR81lOHm7fTt%2FlDlSOmjZaNCQc%3D&amp;reserved=0\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">ABCNews</a>, orchestrated a military coup together in 2021. The military coup resulted in the dissipation of Sudan’s power-sharing government and derailed its short-lived transition to a democracy. After the military coup, Burhan became the ruler of Sudan with Dagalo as his right hand man. Since the military coup, Burhan and Dagalo have fought for control of Sudan.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Before the current crisis, Sudan dealt with violence and displacement due to the 2003 Darfur crisis. By the end of 2022, the amount of internally displaced people surpassed 3.7 million. About 800,000 Sudanese refugees migrated to neighboring countries, including Chad (260,390), South Sudan (178,560), Egypt (255,565), and Ethiopia (26,801).</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">According to the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://nam12.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fdiplomacy.state.gov%2Fteacher-resources%2Fpeacebuilding%2F&amp;data=05%7C01%7Clgarci26%40oldwestbury.edu%7C9473ca9c4f9147bc303508dbe173a005%7Cf5089034f2334f12a71638b7f4904370%7C0%7C0%7C638351658938414600%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&amp;sdata=aSqeJNzdypFnjtKHYZFe3Q%2BMbOgz7PYnkHNsyQ2B6RY%3D&amp;reserved=0\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">National Museum of American Diplomacy</a>, in 2003, a rebellion broke out in Darfur, which is in the western region of Sudan. The rebellion was to protest the Sudanese government’s disregard for the region and its non-Arab population,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://nam12.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.britannica.com%2Fplace%2FSudan%2FConflict-in-Darfur&amp;data=05%7C01%7Clgarci26%40oldwestbury.edu%7C9473ca9c4f9147bc303508dbe173a005%7Cf5089034f2334f12a71638b7f4904370%7C0%7C0%7C638351658938414600%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&amp;sdata=9RBT1QJldIW%2BR4oeMm2oyR9%2F4cQ398D339%2BIvpEsG6I%3D&amp;reserved=0\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Britannica</a>&nbsp;writes. The Sudanese government armed local Arab militias called the “Janjaweed” in an effort to defeat the rebel groups. In 2009, the Janjaweed attacked civilians from ethnic groups associated with the rebels. The United Nations estimated that at least 70,000 people were killed in the conflict.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Today, according to the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://nam12.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Fworld-africa-67356375&amp;data=05%7C01%7Clgarci26%40oldwestbury.edu%7C9473ca9c4f9147bc303508dbe173a005%7Cf5089034f2334f12a71638b7f4904370%7C0%7C0%7C638351658938570826%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&amp;sdata=EgdCD%2BGguBaKxpNznMEpc2ScU%2FUYXMusVjW7%2FP3k%2Fmk%3D&amp;reserved=0\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">BBC</a>, thousands of people are fleeing the Darfur region for fear of ethnic cleansing. The United Nations Refugee Agency&nbsp;<a href=\"https://nam12.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.unrefugees.org%2Fnews%2Fsudan-crisis-explained%2F&amp;data=05%7C01%7Clgarci26%40oldwestbury.edu%7C9473ca9c4f9147bc303508dbe173a005%7Cf5089034f2334f12a71638b7f4904370%7C0%7C0%7C638351658938570826%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&amp;sdata=Dx3Yk075KtkGKMbhuu4s%2BbRiTXAX8aFEAV5IlgC2RUg%3D&amp;reserved=0\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">(UNHCR)</a>&nbsp;says, the most affected groups of the current crisis are women and children. The UN estimated that even before the fighting began, over 3 million Sudanese women and girls were at risk for gender-based violence and intimate-partner violence. Since April 2023, these numbers have increased to an estimated 4.2 million.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Hatim Ali, a local human rights monitor, told&nbsp;<a href=\"https://nam12.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Fworld-africa-67356375&amp;data=05%7C01%7Clgarci26%40oldwestbury.edu%7C9473ca9c4f9147bc303508dbe173a005%7Cf5089034f2334f12a71638b7f4904370%7C0%7C0%7C638351658938570826%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&amp;sdata=EgdCD%2BGguBaKxpNznMEpc2ScU%2FUYXMusVjW7%2FP3k%2Fmk%3D&amp;reserved=0\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">BBC</a><strong>&nbsp;</strong>that he fled to Chad after the RSF and allied militias arrived and besieged Erdamt across the river from El Geneina. Ali said they “killed so many men and raped a lot of women.” Since the capture of El Geneina, the RSF and their allied Arab militias have been accused of murdering, looting the homes of, and raping the women of the Masalit ethnic group.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">The RSF and Arab militia have also, according to&nbsp;<a href=\"https://nam12.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Fworld-africa-67356375&amp;data=05%7C01%7Clgarci26%40oldwestbury.edu%7C9473ca9c4f9147bc303508dbe173a005%7Cf5089034f2334f12a71638b7f4904370%7C0%7C0%7C638351658938570826%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&amp;sdata=EgdCD%2BGguBaKxpNznMEpc2ScU%2FUYXMusVjW7%2FP3k%2Fmk%3D&amp;reserved=0\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">BBC</a><strong>,&nbsp;</strong>attacked a camp for internally displaced people in Erdamta, where about 800 people have reportedly been killed. A man who fled the camp with his family said, “I’m still alive, but I lost a lot.”</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">The&nbsp;<a href=\"https://nam12.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.unrefugees.org%2Fnews%2Fsudan-crisis-explained%2F&amp;data=05%7C01%7Clgarci26%40oldwestbury.edu%7C9473ca9c4f9147bc303508dbe173a005%7Cf5089034f2334f12a71638b7f4904370%7C0%7C0%7C638351658938570826%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&amp;sdata=Dx3Yk075KtkGKMbhuu4s%2BbRiTXAX8aFEAV5IlgC2RUg%3D&amp;reserved=0\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">UNHCR</a>&nbsp;states that in Sudan, the health of the people is also a “particularly alarming,” problem. Over 1,200 children under the age of 5 have died between mid-May and mid-September due to a measles outbreak. This is combined with high levels of malnutrition; at least four children die every week due to the lack of essential medicines, personnel, and supplies.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">According to the World Health Organization and UNFPA, pregnant women have been heavily impacted by the violence. Attacks on healthcare facilities, equipment, and workers have further deprived women of health care. It’s estimated that there are 262,880 pregnant women, more than 90,000 of whom will give birth in the next three months and will need access to proper reproductive health services.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">In addition to being affected by war, the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://nam12.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.unrefugees.org%2Fnews%2Fsudan-crisis-explained%2F&amp;data=05%7C01%7Clgarci26%40oldwestbury.edu%7C9473ca9c4f9147bc303508dbe173a005%7Cf5089034f2334f12a71638b7f4904370%7C0%7C0%7C638351658938570826%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&amp;sdata=Dx3Yk075KtkGKMbhuu4s%2BbRiTXAX8aFEAV5IlgC2RUg%3D&amp;reserved=0\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">UNHCR</a>&nbsp;reports that Sudan has also experienced severe weather disasters that have been linked to climate change, including floods and droughts. As a result, crops and livestock have been destroyed causing food insecurity for hundreds of thousands of people throughout Sudan.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\"><a href=\"https://nam12.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Fworld-africa-67356375&amp;data=05%7C01%7Clgarci26%40oldwestbury.edu%7C9473ca9c4f9147bc303508dbe173a005%7Cf5089034f2334f12a71638b7f4904370%7C0%7C0%7C638351658938570826%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&amp;sdata=EgdCD%2BGguBaKxpNznMEpc2ScU%2FUYXMusVjW7%2FP3k%2Fmk%3D&amp;reserved=0\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">BBC</a> says that peace talks have taken place in Saudi Arabia, but their efforts to secure a ceasefire have failed. A response to the crisis in Sudan was launched earlier this year, the <a href=\"https://nam12.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.unrefugees.org%2Fnews%2Fsudan-crisis-explained%2F&amp;data=05%7C01%7Clgarci26%40oldwestbury.edu%7C9473ca9c4f9147bc303508dbe173a005%7Cf5089034f2334f12a71638b7f4904370%7C0%7C0%7C638351658938570826%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&amp;sdata=Dx3Yk075KtkGKMbhuu4s%2BbRiTXAX8aFEAV5IlgC2RUg%3D&amp;reserved=0\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">UNHCR</a> states. Humanitarians created a $921 million plan, but as the year comes to a close, only 26 percent of the plan has been funded. If you would like to help the people of Sudan, you can send a donation to the <a href=\"https://nam12.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fgive.unrefugees.org%2F230424emer_sdnmain_d_3000%2F%3FSF_onetime%3D7011K000002OOTfQAO%26SF_monthly%3D7011K000002OOTkQAO%26gad_source%3D1%26gclid%3DCjwKCAiA3aeqBhBzEiwAxFiOBoMnephUB9nle-YTBMffgpDvs53jATKFd2Qo-uSnXMOTnr2hH-_EtxoCa6cQAvD_BwE%26gclsrc%3Daw.ds&amp;data=05%7C01%7Clgarci26%40oldwestbury.edu%7C9473ca9c4f9147bc303508dbe173a005%7Cf5089034f2334f12a71638b7f4904370%7C0%7C0%7C638351658938570826%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&amp;sdata=4Ea4mVfcV28IenudwRXYnrQcYalpezgJkCQupjlfWnU%3D&amp;reserved=0\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">UNHCR</a>, which will help provide Sudan with aid such as food, medicine, and clean water. </p>\n', NULL, 'APPROVED', 'KJ262', NULL, '2023-11-10 09:51:50', 0, 'The events taking place in Israel and Palestine have brought other situations to light, such as what is happening in the  Sudan.  In Khartoum, Sudan, according to ABCNews, fighting erupted on April 15, 2023 in light of weeks of tension between General Abdel-Fattah Burhan, the commander of the Sudanese Armed Forces (SAF); and General Mohammed Hamdan…\n', NULL, NULL, 1),
('ed91483a-61ed-11f1-98fa-60cf847a2597', 'article', 'SAG-AFTRA Strike Ends: What This Means for Actors', 'sag-aftra-strike-ends-what-this-means-for-actors', NULL, '\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1200\" height=\"669\" src=\"uploads/image-324-1200x669.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-8493\" style=\"width:467px;height:auto\" srcset=\"https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/image-324-1200x669.png 1200w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/image-324-600x335.png 600w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/image-324-768x428.png 768w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/image-324-300x167.png 300w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/image-324.png 1456w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" /><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\"><sup>Fran Drescher and Duncan Crabtree-Ireland at a press conference. Photo Credit: <a href=\"https://nam12.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F2023%2Fbiz%2Fnews%2Ffran-drescher-sag-aftra-strike-end-1235786973%2F&amp;data=05%7C01%7Clgarci26%40oldwestbury.edu%7C33da018ab96b408cf9a008dbe30bb31e%7Cf5089034f2334f12a71638b7f4904370%7C0%7C0%7C638353411601363407%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&amp;sdata=YB6KxCymYWvgRaN2l0s1LBdvPxIMYRaq%2FBFTVQWrPVI%3D&amp;reserved=0\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Variety</a></sup></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Some social media users may have been confused to see their favorite stars promoting their shows and movies on Friday. Others may have received the message loud and clear through celebratory posts, such as <a href=\"https://nam12.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tiktok.com%2F%40noahschnapp%2Fvideo%2F7299634312050429230%3Fis_from_webapp%3D1%26sender_device%3Dpc%26web_id%3D7171914260934608430&amp;data=05%7C01%7Clgarci26%40oldwestbury.edu%7C33da018ab96b408cf9a008dbe30bb31e%7Cf5089034f2334f12a71638b7f4904370%7C0%7C0%7C638353411601363407%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&amp;sdata=VYHDBv1tXfHoOB8VGKo5DEDGQcvciZmKANDIBwR%2BBug%3D&amp;reserved=0\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Noah Schnapp’s TikTok video</a>: the SAG-AFTRA strike is over.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\"><a href=\"https://nam12.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F2023%2Fbiz%2Fnews%2Ffran-drescher-sag-aftra-strike-end-1235786973%2F&amp;data=05%7C01%7Clgarci26%40oldwestbury.edu%7C33da018ab96b408cf9a008dbe30bb31e%7Cf5089034f2334f12a71638b7f4904370%7C0%7C0%7C638353411601363407%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&amp;sdata=YB6KxCymYWvgRaN2l0s1LBdvPxIMYRaq%2FBFTVQWrPVI%3D&amp;reserved=0\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\"><em>Variety</em></a> reported that at a press conference on Friday, November 9, 2023, <a href=\"https://nam12.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sagaftra.org%2Fsag-aftra-national-board-approves-tentative-agreement-recommends-ratification-2023-tvtheatrical%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%2520SAG-AFTRA%2520National%2520Board%2C)%2520on%2520November%25208%252C%25202023.&amp;data=05%7C01%7Clgarci26%40oldwestbury.edu%7C33da018ab96b408cf9a008dbe30bb31e%7Cf5089034f2334f12a71638b7f4904370%7C0%7C0%7C638353411601363407%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&amp;sdata=lsAnnNfZ5kss4LLhB1dEmvNUJn6UjlJJe7YatVkALDs%3D&amp;reserved=0\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">SAG-AFTRA</a> announced that 86% of the guild has approved a tentative agreement, meaning the 118-day strike has finally concluded. </p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">The deal includes wage increases, an increased contribution cap to support Health and Pension/Retirement funds and benefits, and policies to support actors on streaming services. <a href=\"https://nam12.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sagaftra.org%2Fsag-aftra-national-board-approves-tentative-agreement-recommends-ratification-2023-tvtheatrical%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%2520SAG-AFTRA%2520National%2520Board%2C)%2520on%2520November%25208%252C%25202023.&amp;data=05%7C01%7Clgarci26%40oldwestbury.edu%7C33da018ab96b408cf9a008dbe30bb31e%7Cf5089034f2334f12a71638b7f4904370%7C0%7C0%7C638353411601363407%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&amp;sdata=lsAnnNfZ5kss4LLhB1dEmvNUJn6UjlJJe7YatVkALDs%3D&amp;reserved=0\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">SAG-AFTRA also explained</a> certain protections the contract granted. “Meaningful protections for the casting process have been established, including provisions specifying that breakdowns, sides, and/or scripts shall be provided no less than 48 hours prior to the submission deadline (excluding weekends and holidays),” they said. “This is increased to 72 hours for minors.” There are also limitations created for how many industry standard pages actors can be expected to read for auditions and callbacks, and compensation for memorization requirements.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">The guild’s president, Fran Drescher, said the deal “broke pattern, established new revenue streams and passed a historic $1 billion plus dollar deal with the most progressive AI protections ever written,” <a href=\"https://nam12.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sagaftra.org%2Fsag-aftra-national-board-approves-tentative-agreement-recommends-ratification-2023-tvtheatrical%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%2520SAG-AFTRA%2520National%2520Board%2C)%2520on%2520November%25208%252C%25202023.&amp;data=05%7C01%7Clgarci26%40oldwestbury.edu%7C33da018ab96b408cf9a008dbe30bb31e%7Cf5089034f2334f12a71638b7f4904370%7C0%7C0%7C638353411601363407%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&amp;sdata=lsAnnNfZ5kss4LLhB1dEmvNUJn6UjlJJe7YatVkALDs%3D&amp;reserved=0\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">according to SAG-AFTRA</a>. It also provides further protections to prevent sexual harassment and is based around principles of equity.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">The contract is awaiting ratification. The deadline to vote is Tuesday, December 5 and informational meetings about the tentative deal will begin the week of November 13, 2023.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Drescher told Geoff Bennett of <a href=\"https://nam12.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pbs.org%2Fnewshour%2Fshow%2Fwhy-the-screen-actors-guild-agreed-to-a-end-a-strike-that-crippled-hollywood%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%2520actors%2520union%2520SAG-AFTRA%2Cfirst%2520protections%2520against%2520artificial%2520intelligence.&amp;data=05%7C01%7Clgarci26%40oldwestbury.edu%7C33da018ab96b408cf9a008dbe30bb31e%7Cf5089034f2334f12a71638b7f4904370%7C0%7C0%7C638353411601363407%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&amp;sdata=RP62Pdsiac7jKfPPZdp77p2ZVdkaFehmrca%2FsxHnbmE%3D&amp;reserved=0\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\"><em>PBS NewsHour</em></a> that there’s still some strides to be made. She explained, “even when it comes to auditions and interviews on home self-tapes, that has to be redefined.” Still, she&#8217;s content with the partial advancements made.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">“We knew it was a historic time because of the digitization of our industry, and we knew that we needed a seminal deal,” <a href=\"https://nam12.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pbs.org%2Fnewshour%2Fshow%2Fwhy-the-screen-actors-guild-agreed-to-a-end-a-strike-that-crippled-hollywood%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%2520actors%2520union%2520SAG-AFTRA%2Cfirst%2520protections%2520against%2520artificial%2520intelligence.&amp;data=05%7C01%7Clgarci26%40oldwestbury.edu%7C33da018ab96b408cf9a008dbe30bb31e%7Cf5089034f2334f12a71638b7f4904370%7C0%7C0%7C638353411601363407%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&amp;sdata=RP62Pdsiac7jKfPPZdp77p2ZVdkaFehmrca%2FsxHnbmE%3D&amp;reserved=0\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Drescher expressed</a> to Bennett. “And I feel very proud to say we got one.”</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Actors can now resume practices they couldn’t engage in during the strike, which include but are not limited to on-camera acting, singing, dancing, and stunt-work, reported <a href=\"https://nam12.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.today.com%2Fnews%2Fsag-aftra-strike-rules-2023-rcna94259&amp;data=05%7C01%7Clgarci26%40oldwestbury.edu%7C33da018ab96b408cf9a008dbe30bb31e%7Cf5089034f2334f12a71638b7f4904370%7C0%7C0%7C638353411601363407%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&amp;sdata=NYpZ8chU45%2FARYd2S7aROtROrFnsqnMT1mdb%2ByHPAF8%3D&amp;reserved=0\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\"><em>Today</em></a>. Actors can also now promote their work and do other off-camera work such as voice acting and narration.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Even though the strike is now over, audiences will still have to wait a while before enjoying new shows and movies. The pre-production process of “scriptwriting to set building and costume design” needs to be established and created. “There will be a scramble to get every show and film back to set at once” that will create battles for shooting locations and crew members, <a href=\"https://nam12.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.usatoday.com%2Fstory%2Fentertainment%2Ftv%2F2023%2F11%2F09%2Fhollywood-actors-strike-is-done-when-you-can-expect-tv-and-movies-back%2F71502956007%2F&amp;data=05%7C01%7Clgarci26%40oldwestbury.edu%7C33da018ab96b408cf9a008dbe30bb31e%7Cf5089034f2334f12a71638b7f4904370%7C0%7C0%7C638353411601519174%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&amp;sdata=MsHb5vUGH%2FbS9t6mD8dNfIAAHyTuMKIHONI9Y%2FE5NTA%3D&amp;reserved=0\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">according to<em> USAToday</em></a>.</p>\n', NULL, 'APPROVED', 'JV368', NULL, '2023-11-12 00:50:29', 0, 'Some social media users may have been confused to see their favorite stars promoting their shows and movies on Friday. Others may have received the message loud and clear through celebratory posts, such as Noah Schnapp’s TikTok video: the SAG-AFTRA strike is over. Variety reported that at a press conference on Friday, November 9, 2023, SAG-AFTRA announced that 86%…\n', NULL, NULL, 1),
('ed92e377-61ed-11f1-98fa-60cf847a2597', 'article', '“The Pen is Mightier than the Sword” is it so Mighty That We Must Ban Books?', 'the-pen-is-mightier-than-the-sword-is-it-so-mighty-that-we-must-ban-books', NULL, '\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\"><strong> </strong></p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" src=\"uploads/image-329-300x300.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-8512\" style=\"width:283px;height:auto\" srcset=\"https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/image-329-300x300.png 300w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/image-329-600x600.png 600w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/image-329-70x70.png 70w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/image-329-768x768.png 768w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/image-329.png 1080w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" /><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\"><sup>Photo Credit: American Library Association.</sup></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Book bans are not a new thing, but the fight to ban books and censorship has increased dramatically in the past 2 years. This year, in 2023, book bans are up by 38%, according to the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://nam12.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ala.org%2Fadvocacy%2Fbbooks%2Fbook-ban-data&amp;data=05%7C01%7Clgarci26%40oldwestbury.edu%7C7b53e19a547d4e1669c408dbe480d4b9%7Cf5089034f2334f12a71638b7f4904370%7C0%7C0%7C638355014226897263%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&amp;sdata=TfH6WIY1YeMjk3%2BtB7R4QtYa0Cu7YmSanlNTI2HqzQg%3D&amp;reserved=0\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">American Library Association&#8217;s Office for Intellectual Freedom</a>&nbsp;(ALA OIF). They reported that this year, 3,923 books have been challenged as inappropriate. When books are challenged, they can be “retained, restricted, or revoked at a school or public library.”</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">The books that are deemed inappropriate were mostly “written by or about a person of color or a member of the LGBTQIA+ community,” which was on the ALA’s preliminary<a href=\"https://nam12.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ala.org%2Fnews%2Fpress-releases%2F2023%2F09%2Famerican-library-association-releases-preliminary-data-2023-book-challenges&amp;data=05%7C01%7Clgarci26%40oldwestbury.edu%7C7b53e19a547d4e1669c408dbe480d4b9%7Cf5089034f2334f12a71638b7f4904370%7C0%7C0%7C638355014226897263%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&amp;sdata=2JeoxGtmnkONNEVO6hG%2BfIMEJf9jLOUVDw11RpWOnMM%3D&amp;reserved=0\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">&nbsp;data report</a>&nbsp;of this year’s challenges. The challenged books include content that are being deeming as violent, pornographic, and sexually explicit content. This includes topics regarding race, gender identity, sexual orientation, and sexual education.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Some states have involved their government and have been implementing laws that allow this to happen. One example is the state of Florida’s House Bill&nbsp;<a href=\"https://nam12.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Flegiscan.com%2FFL%2Ftext%2FH1557%2Fid%2F2541706&amp;data=05%7C01%7Clgarci26%40oldwestbury.edu%7C7b53e19a547d4e1669c408dbe480d4b9%7Cf5089034f2334f12a71638b7f4904370%7C0%7C0%7C638355014226897263%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&amp;sdata=2KMoPI1Vc5vV%2BcZpzOnj%2BryO%2BnTI5Rej7w7iJeMkWI0%3D&amp;reserved=0\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">1557</a>, also known as the “Don’t Say Gay” bill. It is a long list of prohibitions in schools. To mention a few, it gives parental rights “to make decisions regarding the upbringing and control of their children in a specified manner.” The bill also forbids “classroom discussion about sexual orientation or gender identity in certain grade levels or in a specified manner.”</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">While parents have the right to be concerned about what their children are being exposed to and learning in the classroom, especially the younger ones, they do not realize how this can affect children who may be experiencing similar things that they can read about in books. The censorship of others&#8217; experiences in books is prohibiting children from knowing experiences outside of their own or experiences that are like their own lives.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Some books that are being challenged are <em>The Bluest Eye </em>and <em>Beloved </em>by Toni Morrison, and <em>Charlotte’s Web</em> by E.B. White. These challenges and bans vary from state to state, and even vary in school districts, as well. Taking away these books or censoring them takes away from their education.  </p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">School districts, public libraries, and bookstores are the targets of these conservative groups like “<a href=\"https://nam12.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.momsforliberty.org%2Fabout%2F&amp;data=05%7C01%7Clgarci26%40oldwestbury.edu%7C7b53e19a547d4e1669c408dbe480d4b9%7Cf5089034f2334f12a71638b7f4904370%7C0%7C0%7C638355014226897263%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&amp;sdata=3gqKYsiIVl3WM7oCUTk9Ob8ueNk0KOUlUXzA0aABNL8%3D&amp;reserved=0\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Moms For Liberty,</a>” whose mission statement is “dedicated to fighting for the survival of America by unifying, educating and empowering parents to defend their parental rights at all levels of government.” Some people argue that book banning is against the First Amendment (the freedom of speech) while others are saying it is their right as parents, like in the case of “Moms for Liberty,” to fight for what content they do or don’t want their children to read.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">One article from <a href=\"https://nam12.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wusf.org%2Feducation%2F2023-07-12%2Fflorida-school-district-removed-5-books-after-moms-for-liberty-raised-concern-more-could-follow&amp;data=05%7C01%7Clgarci26%40oldwestbury.edu%7C7b53e19a547d4e1669c408dbe480d4b9%7Cf5089034f2334f12a71638b7f4904370%7C0%7C0%7C638355014226897263%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&amp;sdata=qHTValcsuCbuG2UFWWiYSvLY%2FaeJGY48K5abYkb5TEs%3D&amp;reserved=0\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\"><em>WSUF</em></a> mentions how a local chapter in Florida is hard at work on their book challenges, saying, “[they have] put out a list of more than a dozen other books in the school district it says needs to be scrapped. That list includes novels such as ‘Water for Elephants,’ and ‘All Boys Aren’t Blue.’” This attack seems to grow, and it will not get any better since these conservative groups are being so loud about it. In response to the book ban, the <a href=\"https://nam12.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bklynlibrary.org%2Fbooks-unbanned&amp;data=05%7C01%7Clgarci26%40oldwestbury.edu%7C7b53e19a547d4e1669c408dbe480d4b9%7Cf5089034f2334f12a71638b7f4904370%7C0%7C0%7C638355014227053521%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&amp;sdata=NRP7sVFr86S%2F0T1XhSumnTI5S%2F5fH0BHSO%2B1k%2BewnMA%3D&amp;reserved=0\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Brooklyn Public Library</a> has made its catalog available to all children in the country to provide these books to kids who want to read them. While the internet is a place where everything can be found, for children to have books taken away from them implies that something is not right with the book. That thinking might lead the child to wonder if something about them is not right. </p>\n', NULL, 'APPROVED', 'TP434', NULL, '2023-11-13 23:30:03', 0, '  Book bans are not a new thing, but the fight to ban books and censorship has increased dramatically in the past 2 years. This year, in 2023, book bans are up by 38%, according to the American Library Association’s Office for Intellectual Freedom (ALA OIF). They reported that this year, 3,923 books have been challenged as…\n', NULL, NULL, 1),
('ed93be62-61ed-11f1-98fa-60cf847a2597', 'article', 'Grounded', 'grounded', NULL, '\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"514\" height=\"618\" src=\"uploads/image-332.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-8519\" style=\"width:402px;height:auto\" srcset=\"https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/image-332.png 514w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/image-332-499x600.png 499w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/image-332-250x300.png 250w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 514px) 100vw, 514px\" /><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\"><sup><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; font-size: 16px; white-space-collapse: collapse;\">Photo by Liselle Powder</span>.</sup></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">When at last your roots were water?</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">To spread, to grow and reach heights.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Heights that move you to the next level.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Yes, you can dream.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Dream the impossible.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Be grounded, be unshakable</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">be unmovable.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Let the waters move through&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">your souls and burst your&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">energy to shine.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Root out those weeds and vines</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">that want to choke you.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Choke your dreams and visions.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Get rid of the thorns and thistles.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">They are distractions to your purpose.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Just breath and climb.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Climb to the pinnacle and</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">strip anything from your path,</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">that is not worth fighting for.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Just let that water flow in depths</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">and be refreshed as you</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">&nbsp;dance to your music.</p>\n', NULL, 'APPROVED', 'LP665', NULL, '2023-11-17 22:29:19', 0, 'When at last your roots were water? To spread, to grow and reach heights. Heights that move you to the next level. Yes, you can dream. Dream the impossible. Be grounded, be unshakable be unmovable. Let the waters move through  your souls and burst your  energy to shine. Root out those weeds and vines that…\n', NULL, NULL, 1),
('ed9495e1-61ed-11f1-98fa-60cf847a2597', 'podcast', 'Thanks for the Media!', 'thanks-for-the-media', NULL, '<p><a href=\"https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/NMB-7-Red-Leaves-Nations-Rectangle-scaled.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-6577\" src=\"https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/NMB-7-Red-Leaves-Nations-Rectangle-scaled.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1440\" /></a></p>\n<audio class=\"wp-audio-shortcode\" id=\"audio-8525-1\" preload=\"none\" style=\"width: 100%;\" controls=\"controls\"><source type=\"audio/mpeg\" src=\"https://www.oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/NMB-7-Web-2023-11-16.mp3?_=1\" /><a href=\"https://www.oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/NMB-7-Web-2023-11-16.mp3\">https://www.oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/NMB-7-Web-2023-11-16.mp3</a></audio>\n<p><h2><strong>This Week on New Media Beat:</strong></h2></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Gaza:  </strong>What&#8217;s Left of the Internet?</li>\n<li><strong>Canada: </strong>Why Does Meta Hate the Online News Act?</li>\n<li><strong>Ethiopia: </strong>Did Hate Speech on Facebook Incite Violence?</li>\n<li><strong>North Korea: </strong>Any Chance of a Free Press?</li>\n<li><strong>Mexico: </strong>Are Journalists Safe Yet?</li>\n<li><strong>China: </strong>How Big Is that Great Firewall?</li>\n<li><strong>Global:</strong> Is Violence Against Journalists Increasing?</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\"><a href=\"https://www.newmediabeat.org/\"><strong>New Media Beat</strong></a> covers new media news from around the world.&nbsp;NMB&nbsp;is a production of&nbsp; Media Studies students from the <a href=\"https://www.oldwestbury.edu/\" target=\"_self\" rel=\"noopener\">SUNY College @ Old Westbury.</a>&nbsp;&nbsp; We scour the web for news about about the world of media, journalism and technology.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">NMB is co-produced by Alex Hajko, Demetrik Hylton &amp; Cody Werner. Our engineer is Demetrik Hylton.&nbsp; Our hosts are Aidan Bongiorno and Criastaly Almanzar.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">The NMB Podcast streams live on <a href=\"http://www.owwrny.org/\">Old Westbury Web Radio</a> Thursdays from 10:00-11:00 AM EST.&nbsp; Can&#8217;t listen live? Our podcast will be <a href=\"https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/?cat=17\">posted</a> for your listening pleasure every Friday afternoon.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Follow<strong> <a href=\"https://twitter.com/OWWRGMN\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">@OWWRGMN</a></strong> for a curated feed of the latest new media news for aspiring media professionals.</p>\n', NULL, 'APPROVED', 'TC527', NULL, '2023-11-20 22:10:15', 0, 'This Week on New Media Beat: Gaza:  What’s Left of the Internet? Canada: Why Does Meta Hate the Online News Act? Ethiopia: Did Hate Speech on Facebook Incite Violence? North Korea: Any Chance of a Free Press? Mexico: Are Journalists Safe Yet? China: How Big Is that Great Firewall? Global: Is Violence Against Journalists Increasing?…\n', NULL, NULL, 1),
('ed9623a7-61ed-11f1-98fa-60cf847a2597', 'article', 'A Historic Miss Universe Celebration', 'a-historic-miss-universe-celebration', NULL, '\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"173\" height=\"300\" src=\"uploads/image-335-173x300.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-8540\" style=\"width:168px;height:auto\" srcset=\"https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/image-335-173x300.png 173w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/image-335-345x600.png 345w, https://oldwestburycatalyst.org/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/image-335.png 640w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 173px) 100vw, 173px\" /><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\"><sup>Photo Credit: <a href=\"https://nam12.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.missuniverse.com%2F&amp;data=05%7C01%7Clgarci26%40oldwestbury.edu%7Ccf1d315f90544a7ec57708dbeab7c8ef%7Cf5089034f2334f12a71638b7f4904370%7C0%7C0%7C638361847345402494%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&amp;sdata=%2F22HoJk%2FQFR%2BlYohN%2FBP3gBMqP8mJaoIuQRSxDA66gU%3D&amp;reserved=0\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Missuniverse.com</a>.</sup></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">The country of Nicaragua is in celebration after a historic Miss Universe win. Sheynnis Palacio was crowned Miss Universe 2023 on November 18, 2023. This win means a lot to the Nicaraguans because it is not only the farthest a contestant from the country has gone, but it’s also the first time they have won.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">The Miss Universe event was held in El Salvador this year. El Salvador being the host country has sparked a lot of talks about the government of El Salvador under the leadership of Nayib Bukele. This is the first time the competition is held in El Salvador, or any Central American country for that matter.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">For many years, the pageant has a long history of people questioning whether it’s demeaning to have these women representing their countries, parading around in bathing suits. I say not.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">The event consists of three sections: the swimsuit parade, the evening gown, and the personal interview. Before, the contest used to be almost purely about looks and confidence in a woman. However, a contestant’s knowledge now plays a huge factor in their victory. As the women were being introduced, I noticed that many had or were getting their college diploma. Some women had their masters and many stated that they were studying to be lawyers. I think that every category is well diving into showing every woman and what they might shine at.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">My favorite part of the competition is the national costume. Every year, I look forward to seeing how the delegates have chosen to represent what their country stands for. In my opinion, the best costume of the night came from Miss El Salvador. The dress upon first look is absolutely stunning. Miss Salvador looks like she is covered in flames. The dress’ volcanic ambiance is supposed to symbolize transformative power that nature has and the rebirth of the nation. The dress further impressed me when the flames were illuminated by light. The dress reminds me of the movie “The Hunger Games,” when Katniss lights her dress on fire, making it one of the most iconic movie scenes ever.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">This year is a year of many milestones. It is the first year that mothers are represented in the Miss Universe competition. Miss Colombia and Miss Guatemala are both married mothers, which was never seen before in the competition’s history. There had been rules set in place, restricting the women that could apply to be Miss Universe. Having to be childless and unwed has been removed as a rule, alongside the age restriction. This year is also the first year to be open to any female above the age of 18. Prior to this competition, the ages to be able to compete were 18-28. Miss USA, who won the competition in 2023, was one of the oldest winners at 28, just barely missing the cut off.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">The biggest change in rules that has resulted to be controversial is allowing transgender women to participate. Miss Portugal, Marina Machete, and Miss Netherlands, Rikkie Kolle, are both making history as the first transgender women to participate in Miss Universe celebration, making people take to Twitter to give their opinions on it. The event’s inclusivity has also further increased, as this is also the first the audience has seen a plus-sized woman strutting the Miss Universe runway.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">At the end of every Miss Universe event, it is announced where the competition will be held the following year. The event will be held in Mexico next year.</p>\n', NULL, 'APPROVED', 'FR779', NULL, '2023-11-22 14:18:59', 0, 'The country of Nicaragua is in celebration after a historic Miss Universe win. Sheynnis Palacio was crowned Miss Universe 2023 on November 18, 2023. This win means a lot to the Nicaraguans because it is not only the farthest a contestant from the country has gone, but it’s also the first time they have won.  …\n', NULL, NULL, 1);
